{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017L9qKiuVXHHcVQ2QJfYtu7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import javax.persistence.Column;\n     5→import javax.persistence.Embeddable;\n     6→import javax.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n     7→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n     8→\n     9→/** Uniquely identifies a particular cargo. Automatically generated by the application. */\n    10→@Embeddable\n    11→public class TrackingId implements Serializable {\n    12→\n    13→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    14→\n    15→  @Column(name = \"tracking_id\", unique = true, updatable = false)\n    16→  @NotEmpty(message = \"Tracking ID cannot be empty.\")\n    17→  private String id;\n    18→\n    19→  public TrackingId() {}\n    20→\n    21→  public TrackingId(String id) {\n    22→    Validate.notNull(id);\n    23→    this.id = id;\n    24→  }\n    25→\n    26→  public String getIdString() {\n    27→    return id;\n    28→  }\n    29→\n    30→  @Override\n    31→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    32→    if (this == o) {\n    33→      return true;\n    34→    }\n    35→\n    36→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof TrackingId)) {\n    37→      return false;\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    TrackingId other = (TrackingId) o;\n    41→\n    42→    return sameValueAs(other);\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  @Override\n    46→  public int hashCode() {\n    47→    return id.hashCode();\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  boolean sameValueAs(TrackingId other) {\n    51→    return other != null && this.id.equals(other.id);\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  @Override\n    55→  public String toString() {\n    56→    return id;\n    57→  }\n    58→}\n    59→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"bb296bb4-f12d-4184-b61d-326efbc8b3a1"}
