{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0167WXTULV38EYkMaM6ame2f","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n     3→        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n     4→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     5→  xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     6→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\"\n     7→  xmlns:f=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/core\" xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\">\n     8→<ui:composition template=\"/WEB-INF/templates/common/admin.xhtml\">\n     9→  <ui:define name=\"title\">Cargo Dashboard</ui:define>\n    10→  <ui:define name=\"content\">\n    11→    <div class=\"ui-g-2\"></div>\n    12→    <div class=\"ui-g-8\" id=\"container\" style=\"display: none\">\n    13→      <h:form id=\"mainDash\">\n    14→        <ui:include src=\"/admin/tables/list_routed.xhtml\" class=\"clearCargoBkg\" />\n    15→        <br />\n    16→        <br />\n    17→        <ui:include src=\"/admin/tables/list_not_routed.xhtml\" />\n    18→        <br />\n    19→        <br />\n    20→        <ui:include src=\"/admin/tables/list_claimed.xhtml\" />\n    21→      </h:form>\n    22→    </div>\n    23→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/topbar.min.js\" />\n    24→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/topbar.js\" />\n    25→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/progress.js\" />\n    26→  </ui:define>\n    27→</ui:composition>\n    28→</html>\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CeohoG4JHS9obNcGYJWBuV","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"96192e7d-f632-49e0-95ec-b06d4540153a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WGKTZC8tvEFFDmVo37j1QS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     2→  xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     3→  xmlns:f=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/core\"\n     4→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\">\n     5→<ui:composition template=\"/WEB-INF/templates/common/admin.xhtml\">\n     6→  <ui:define name=\"title\">Cargo Administration</ui:define>\n     7→\n     8→  <ui:define name=\"content\">\n     9→    <f:metadata>\n    10→      <f:viewParam name=\"trackingId\" value=\"#{itinerarySelection.trackingId}\" />\n    11→      <f:viewAction action=\"#{itinerarySelection.load}\" />\n    12→    </f:metadata>\n    13→\n    14→    <div class=\"ui-g-2\"></div>\n    15→    <div class=\"ui-g-8\">\n    16→      <h:panelGroup rendered=\"#{empty itinerarySelection.routeCandidates}\">\n    17→        <p>No routes found that satisfy the route specification. Try setting\n    18→          an arrival deadline further into the future (a few weeks at least).</p>\n    19→      </h:panelGroup>\n    20→    </div>\n    21→  </ui:define>\n    22→</ui:composition>\n    23→</html>\n    24→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CeohoG4JHS9obNcGYJWBuV","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"04b29527-166f-45bb-be97-f28cce993d2f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NyqocU1M1oGMEdjBxyUQbU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     2→  xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     3→  xmlns:f=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/core\"\n     4→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\"\n     5→  xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\"\n     6→  xmlns:fn=\"http://java.sun.com/jsp/jstl/functions\">\n     7→<ui:composition template=\"/WEB-INF/templates/common/admin.xhtml\">\n     8→  <f:metadata>\n     9→    <f:viewParam name=\"trackingId\" value=\"#{cargoDetails.trackingId}\" />\n    10→    <f:event type=\"preRenderView\" listener=\"#{cargoDetails.load}\" />\n    11→    <f:viewParam name=\"trackingId\" value=\"#{itinerarySelection.trackingId}\" />\n    12→    <f:event type=\"preRenderView\" listener=\"#{itinerarySelection.load}\" />\n    13→  </f:metadata>\n    14→  <ui:define name=\"title\">Route Cargo #{cargoDetails.trackingId}</ui:define>\n    15→  <ui:define name=\"content\">\n    16→    <div class=\"ui-grid-col-2\" id=\"leftCol\"></div>\n    17→    <div class=\"ui-grid-col-8\" id=\"mainCol\">\n    18→      <br />\n    19→      <p:outputLabel\n    20→        value=\"Set Route for Cargo #{cargoDetails.cargo.trackingId}\"\n    21→        style=\"font-size: 2em; font-weight: bold;\" />\n    22→      <p:separator />\n    23→      <h:panelGrid columns=\"2\" styleClass=\"registrationPanelGrid\"\n    24→        cellpadding=\"5\">\n    25→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Origin:\" style=\"color:#5392c3;font-weight: bold;\" />\n    26→        <h:panelGroup>\n    27→          <p:outputLabel value=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.originName}\" />\n    28→          <p:outputLabel value=\"&#160;&#160;#{cargoDetails.cargo.originCode}\"\n    29→            style=\"color: #999999;font-size:.9em;\" />\n    30→        </h:panelGroup>\n    31→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Destination:\"\n    32→          style=\"color: #5392c3;font-weight: bold;\" />\n    33→        <h:panelGroup>\n    34→          <p:outputLabel value=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.finalDestinationName}\" />\n    35→          <p:outputLabel\n    36→            value=\"&#160;&#160;#{cargoDetails.cargo.finalDestinationCode}\"\n    37→            style=\"color: #999999;font-size:.9em;\" />\n    38→        </h:panelGroup>\n    39→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Arrival deadline:\"\n    40→          style=\"color: #5392c3;font-weight: bold;\" />\n    41→        <h:panelGroup>\n    42→          <p:outputLabel value=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.arrivalDeadline}\" />\n    43→        </h:panelGroup>\n    44→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Potential routes:\"\n    45→          style=\"color: #5392c3;font-weight: bold;\" />\n    46→        <h:panelGroup>\n    47→          <p:outputLabel value=\"#{itinerarySelection.routeCandidates.size()}\" />\n    48→        </h:panelGroup>\n    49→      </h:panelGrid>\n    50→      <p:separator />\n    51→      <h:panelGroup rendered=\"#{empty itinerarySelection.routeCandidates}\">\n    52→        <p>\n    53→          <i class=\"fa fa-exclamation-triangle\" style=\"color: #9b2332\" /> No\n    54→          routes found that satisfy the route specification. Try setting an\n    55→          arrival deadline further into the future.\n    56→        </p>\n    57→      </h:panelGroup>\n    58→\n    59→      <ui:repeat value=\"#{itinerarySelection.routeCandidates}\" var=\"itinerary\"\n    60→        varStatus=\"itineraryStatus\">\n    61→        <div class=\"ui-g ui-g-12\">\n    62→          <div class=\"ui-g-3\" style=\"font-size: 1.5em; padding: 10px;\">\n    63→            <span class=\"success label\">Route option\n    64→              ##{itineraryStatus.index + 1}</span>\n    65→          </div>\n    66→          <div class=\"ui-g-1 ui-g-offset-8\"\n    67→            style=\"font-size: 1.5em; padding: 10px;\">\n    68→            <p:commandLink\n    69→              action=\"#{itinerarySelection.assignItinerary(itineraryStatus.index)}\"\n    70→              style=\"text-decoration: none;\">\n    71→              <span style=\"color: #e8b44b; font-weight: bold;\">Select</span>\n    72→            </p:commandLink>\n    73→          </div>\n    74→          <div class=\"ui-g-12\">\n    75→            <p:dataTable var=\"legs\" value=\"#{itinerary.legs}\"\n    76→              style=\"text-align: center;\" id=\"legs\">\n    77→\n    78→              <p:column headerText=\"Voyage\" width=\"64\"\n    79→                style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    80→                <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.voyageNumber}\"\n    81→                  style=\"color: #9b2332\" />\n    82→              </p:column>\n    83→\n    84→              <p:column headerText=\"Load\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    85→                <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.fromName}\"\n    86→                  style=\"font-weight: #{fn:startsWith(cargoDetails.cargo.originName, legs.fromName) ? 'bold' : 'normal'}\" />\n    87→                <ui:fragment\n    88→                  rendered=\"${fn:startsWith(cargoDetails.cargo.originName, legs.fromName)}\">\n    89→                  <i class=\"fa fa-arrow-right\" />\n    90→                </ui:fragment>\n    91→\n    92→              </p:column>\n    93→\n    94→              <p:column headerText=\"Time\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    95→                <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.loadTime}\" />\n    96→              </p:column>\n    97→\n    98→              <p:column headerText=\"Unload\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    99→                <ui:fragment\n   100→                  rendered=\"${fn:startsWith(cargoDetails.cargo.finalDestination, legs.toName)}\">\n   101→                  <i class=\"fa fa-arrow-right\" />\n   102→                </ui:fragment>\n   103→                <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.toName}\"\n   104→                  style=\"font-weight: #{fn:startsWith(cargoDetails.cargo.finalDestination, legs.toName) ?'bolder' : 'normal'}\" />\n   105→              </p:column>\n   106→\n   107→              <p:column headerText=\"Time\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n   108→                <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.unloadTime}\" />\n   109→              </p:column>\n   110→\n   111→            </p:dataTable>\n   112→            <p:tooltip for=\"legs\"\n   113→              value=\"Hit 'Select' to assign this candidate itinerary to the cargo\"\n   114→              trackMouse=\"true\" />\n   115→            <br />\n   116→          </div>\n   117→        </div>\n   118→      </ui:repeat>\n   119→    </div>\n   120→  </ui:define>\n   121→</ui:composition>\n   122→</html>\n   123→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CeohoG4JHS9obNcGYJWBuV","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"1cfc970f-7009-49c4-bf55-e1d2c58eebe3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015zvTzmdgSykp8AWxrLXSyc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     2→  xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     3→  xmlns:f=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/core\"\n     4→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\"\n     5→  xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\">\n     6→<ui:composition template=\"/WEB-INF/templates/common/admin.xhtml\">\n     7→  <f:metadata>\n     8→    <f:viewParam name=\"trackingId\" value=\"#{cargoDetails.trackingId}\" />\n     9→    <f:event type=\"preRenderView\" listener=\"#{cargoDetails.load()}\" />\n    10→  </f:metadata>\n    11→  <ui:define name=\"title\">Cargo Details</ui:define>\n    12→  <ui:define name=\"content\">\n    13→    <div class=\"ui-grid-col-3\" id=\"leftCol\"></div>\n    14→    <div class=\"ui-grid-col-6\" id=\"mainCol\">\n    15→      <br />\n    16→      <p:outputLabel\n    17→        value=\"Routing Details for Cargo #{cargoDetails.cargo.trackingId}\"\n    18→        style=\"font-size: 2em; font-weight: bold\" />\n    19→      <p:separator />\n    20→      <h:panelGrid columns=\"2\" styleClass=\"registrationPanelGrid\"\n    21→        cellpadding=\"5\">\n    22→\n    23→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Origin:\" style=\"color:#5392c3;font-weight: bold;\" />\n    24→        <h:panelGroup>\n    25→          <p:outputLabel value=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.originName}\" />\n    26→          <p:outputLabel value=\"&#160;&#160;#{cargoDetails.cargo.originCode}\"\n    27→            style=\"color: #999999;font-size:.9em;\" />\n    28→        </h:panelGroup>\n    29→\n    30→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Destination:\"\n    31→          style=\"color: #5392c3;font-weight: bold;\" />\n    32→        <h:panelGroup>\n    33→          <p:outputLabel value=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.finalDestinationName}\" />\n    34→          <p:outputLabel\n    35→            value=\"&#160;&#160;#{cargoDetails.cargo.finalDestinationCode}\"\n    36→            style=\"color: #999999;font-size:.9em;\" />\n    37→        </h:panelGroup>\n    38→\n    39→        <p:outputLabel value=\"Arrival deadline:\"\n    40→          style=\"color: #5392c3;font-weight: bold;\" />\n    41→        <h:panelGroup>\n    42→          <p:outputLabel value=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.arrivalDeadline}\" />\n    43→        </h:panelGroup>\n    44→      </h:panelGrid>\n    45→      <p:separator />\n    46→      <br />\n    47→      <div class=\"row\">\n    48→        <div class=\"large-12 columns\">\n    49→          <div id=\"container\" class=\"panel\">\n    50→            <h:panelGroup rendered=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.routed}\">\n    51→              <h:panelGroup rendered=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.misrouted}\">\n    52→                <h:panelGrid columns=\"3\" style=\"font-size: 1.2em\"\n    53→                  cellpadding=\"5\">\n    54→                  <p:outputLabel value=\"Misrouted cargo!\"\n    55→                    style=\"vertical-align: top;\" />\n    56→                  <h:form>\n    57→                    <p:button value=\"Reroute\"\n    58→                      outcome=\"selectItinerary.xhtml?faces-redirect=true\"\n    59→                      style=\"font-size:.9em;\">\n    60→                      <f:param name=\"trackingId\"\n    61→                        value=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.trackingId}\" />\n    62→                    </p:button>\n    63→                  </h:form>\n    64→                  <p:outputLabel />\n    65→                </h:panelGrid>\n    66→              </h:panelGroup>\n    67→              <p:outputLabel value=\"Itinerary\"\n    68→                style=\"font-size: x-large; font-weight: bold;\" />\n    69→              <br />\n    70→              <br />\n    71→              <p:dataTable var=\"legs\" value=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.legs}\"\n    72→                style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    73→                <p:column headerText=\"Voyage\" width=\"64\"\n    74→                  style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    75→                  <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.voyageNumber}\" />\n    76→                </p:column>\n    77→\n    78→                <p:column headerText=\"Load\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    79→                  <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.fromName}  \" />\n    80→                  <br />\n    81→                  <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.fromUnLocode}\"\n    82→                    style=\"color: #999999;font-size:.8em;\" />\n    83→                </p:column>\n    84→\n    85→                <p:column headerText=\"Time\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    86→                  <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.loadTime}\" />\n    87→                </p:column>\n    88→\n    89→                <p:column headerText=\"Unload\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    90→                  <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.toName}\" />\n    91→                  <br />\n    92→                  <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.toUnLocode}\"\n    93→                    style=\"color: #999999;font-size:.8em;\" />\n    94→                </p:column>\n    95→\n    96→                <p:column headerText=\"Time\" style=\"text-align: center;\">\n    97→                  <h:outputText value=\"#{legs.unloadTime}\" />\n    98→                </p:column>\n    99→              </p:dataTable>\n   100→\n   101→            </h:panelGroup>\n   102→            <h:panelGroup rendered=\"#{not cargoDetails.cargo.routed}\">\n   103→              <p>\n   104→                <strong>Not routed</strong> -\n   105→                <h:link value=\"route this cargo\"\n   106→                  outcome=\"selectItinerary.xhtml?faces-redirect=true\">\n   107→                  <f:param name=\"trackingId\"\n   108→                    value=\"#{cargoDetails.cargo.trackingId}\" />\n   109→                </h:link>\n   110→              </p>\n   111→            </h:panelGroup>\n   112→          </div>\n   113→        </div>\n   114→      </div>\n   115→    </div>\n   116→  </ui:define>\n   117→</ui:composition>\n   118→</html>\n   119→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CeohoG4JHS9obNcGYJWBuV","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"04cc154b-58f0-4ee4-bc56-8658861a3f81"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01H7hgqqquMFy99umgnmWXVN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     2→  xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     3→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\">\n     4→<ui:composition template=\"/WEB-INF/templates/common/admin.xhtml\">\n     5→  <ui:define name=\"title\">Cargo Administration</ui:define>\n     6→  <ui:define name=\"content\">\n     7→\n     8→    <div class=\"ui-grid-col-3\"></div>\n     9→    <div class=\"ui-grid-col-6\">\n    10→      <br />\n    11→      <div id=\"container\" style=\"display: none\" class=\"panel\">\n    12→        <h3>This interface includes several features for Cargo\n    13→          Administrators:</h3>\n    14→        <ul>\n    15→          <li>View the current status of all registered cargo.</li>\n    16→          <li>View details for cargo such as origin, destination, deadline\n    17→            and itinerary.</li>\n    18→          <li>Change cargo destination/deadline.</li>\n    19→          <li>Book new cargo.</li>\n    20→          <li>Assign route to cargo.</li>\n    21→          <li>Track cargo via the internal tracking interface.</li>\n    22→          <li>View a live map that continuously monitors all cargo in real\n    23→            time.</li>\n    24→        </ul>\n    25→        <p>\n    26→          Visit <a href=\"https://eclipse-ee4j.github.io/cargotracker/\">https://eclipse-ee4j.github.io/cargotracker/</a>\n    27→          for more information about Eclipse Cargo Tracker.\n    28→        </p>\n    29→        <hr />\n    30→      </div>\n    31→    </div>\n    32→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/topbar.min.js\" />\n    33→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/topbar.js\" />\n    34→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/progress.js\" />\n    35→  </ui:define>\n    36→</ui:composition>\n    37→</html>\n    38→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CeohoG4JHS9obNcGYJWBuV","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"94cae7d5-c3fe-4cb5-ac0a-ef8d4c3d8cc9"}
