{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015Koeskr36Y3sgVzXrmMJym","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     2→  xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     3→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\"\n     4→  xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\" xmlns:f=\"http://java.sun.com/jsf/core\">\n     5→<ui:composition template=\"/WEB-INF/templates/common/public.xhtml\">\n     6→  <ui:define name=\"title\">Track Cargo</ui:define>\n     7→  <ui:define name=\"content\">\n     8→    <div class=\"ui-grid-col-2\" id=\"leftCol\"></div>\n     9→    <div class=\"ui-grid-col-8\" id=\"container\" style=\"display: none\">\n    10→      <br />\n    11→      <div class=\"ui-g ui-g-12\">\n    12→        <div class=\"ui-g-6 ui-g-offset-3\">\n    13→          <h:form id=\"trackingForm\">\n    14→            <h:panelGrid columns=\"3\" cellpadding=\"15\">\n    15→              <p>Enter your tracking ID:</p>\n    16→              <p:inputText id=\"trackingIdInput\"\n    17→                value=\"#{public.track.trackingId}\" required=\"true\"\n    18→                placeholder=\"XYZ789\" title=\"Valid tracking ID\" />\n    19→              <h:commandButton value=\"Track!\"\n    20→                action=\"#{public.track.onTrackById()}\">\n    21→                <f:ajax execute=\"trackingIdInput\" render=\"cargo-status\" />\n    22→              </h:commandButton>\n    23→            </h:panelGrid>\n    24→          </h:form>\n    25→        </div>\n    26→      </div>\n    27→      <div class=\"ui-g-12\">\n    28→        <p:separator />\n    29→      </div>\n    30→      <h:panelGroup id=\"cargo-status\">\n    31→        <div class=\"ui-g-12\">\n    32→          <h:panelGroup rendered=\"#{not empty public.track.cargo}\">\n    33→            <div id=\"result\">\n    34→              <p>\n    35→                Cargo <strong>#{public.track.cargo.trackingId}</strong> is\n    36→                currently <strong>#{public.track.cargo.statusText}</strong>\n    37→              </p>\n    38→\n    39→              <p>\n    40→                Estimated time of arrival in <strong>#{public.track.cargo.destinationName}</strong>:\n    41→                #{public.track.cargo.eta}\n    42→              </p>\n    43→              <ui:fragment\n    44→                rendered=\"#{not empty public.track.cargo.nextExpectedActivity}\">\n    45→                <p>#{public.track.cargo.nextExpectedActivity}</p>\n    46→              </ui:fragment>\n    47→\n    48→              <p:panel rendered=\"#{public.track.cargo.misdirected}\">\n    49→                <p>\n    50→                  <i class=\"fa fa-exclamation-triangle\" style=\"color: #9b2332\"></i>\n    51→                  Cargo is misdirected.\n    52→                </p>\n    53→              </p:panel>\n    54→            </div>\n    55→          </h:panelGroup>\n    56→\n    57→          <p:outputLabel\n    58→            value=\"Cargo with tracking ID #{public.track.trackingId} not found.\"\n    59→            rendered=\"#{empty public.track.cargo and not empty public.track.trackingId}\" />\n    60→        </div>\n    61→\n    62→        <h:panelGroup rendered=\"#{not empty public.track.cargo}\">\n    63→          <div class=\"ui-g ui-g-12\">\n    64→            <div class=\"ui-g-3\">\n    65→              <p:outputLabel value=\"Handling History\"\n    66→                style=\"font-size: 2em; font-weight: bold\" />\n    67→            </div>\n    68→\n    69→            <div class=\"ui-g-12\">\n    70→              <p:separator />\n    71→              <br /> <br />\n    72→            </div>\n    73→\n    74→            <div class=\"ui-g-12\">\n    75→              <ui:repeat value=\"#{public.track.cargo.events}\" var=\"leg\">\n    76→                <div>\n    77→                  <ui:fragment rendered=\"#{leg.expected}\">\n    78→                                &#160;&#160;<i class=\"fa fa-check\"\n    79→                      style=\"color: green\" />&#160;#{leg.description}, at #{leg.time}\n    80→                            </ui:fragment>\n    81→                  <ui:fragment rendered=\"#{!leg.expected}\">\n    82→                                &#160;&#160;<em class=\"fa fa-flag\"\n    83→                      style=\"color: #9b2332\" />&#160;#{leg.description}, at #{leg.time}\n    84→                            </ui:fragment>\n    85→                </div>\n    86→              </ui:repeat>\n    87→\n    88→              <p:outputLabel\n    89→                value=\"There are no events recorded for the tracking ID #{public.track.cargo.trackingId}.\"\n    90→                rendered=\"#{empty public.track.cargo.events}\" />\n    91→            </div>\n    92→          </div>\n    93→\n    94→          <div id=\"map\" class=\"ui-g-12\">\n    95→            <iframe class=\"mapFrame\" width=\"100%\" height=\"960\"\n    96→              src=\"#{request.contextPath}/public/mapFrame.xhtml?cargo=#{public.track.cargoAsJson}\" />\n    97→          </div>\n    98→        </h:panelGroup>\n    99→      </h:panelGroup>\n   100→    </div>\n   101→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/topbar.min.js\" />\n   102→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/topbar.js\" />\n   103→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/progress.js\" />\n   104→  </ui:define>\n   105→</ui:composition>\n   106→</html>\n   107→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CeohoG4JHS9obNcGYJWBuV","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"c16303ad-876c-4e1c-bcdc-4982f0617e2f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BhvKxCTGvyiFEMYcMviPjd","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<!DOCTYPE html>\n     3→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n     4→<head>\n     5→<title>Cargo Live Map</title>\n     6→<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n     7→\n     8→<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"#{resource['/css/dd.css']}\" />\n     9→\n    10→<link rel=\"stylesheet\"\n    11→  href=\"//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/twitter-bootstrap/2.3.2/css/bootstrap-combined.min.css\" />\n    12→\n    13→<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"#{resource['/leaflet/leaflet.css']}\" />\n    14→<script src=\"#{resource['/leaflet/leaflet.js']}\" />\n    15→\n    16→<script type=\"text/javascript\">\n    17→\t//<![CDATA[\n    18→\tfunction getUrlParameter(name) {\n    19→\t\tname = name.replace(/[\\[]/, '\\\\[').replace(/[\\]]/, '\\\\]');\n    20→\t\tvar regex = new RegExp('[\\\\?&]' + name + '=([^&#]*)');\n    21→\t\tvar results = regex.exec(location.search);\n    22→\t\treturn results === null ? '' : decodeURIComponent(results[1].replace(\n    23→\t\t\t\t/\\+/g, ' '));\n    24→\t};\n    25→\t//]]>\n    26→</script>\n    27→<script type=\"text/javascript\">\n    28→\t//  load the icons for the map\n    29→\tconst greenIcon = new L.Icon(\n    30→\t\t\t{\n    31→\t\t\t\ticonUrl : 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pointhi/leaflet-color-markers/master/img/marker-icon-2x-green.png',\n    32→\t\t\t\tshadowUrl : 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/leaflet/0.7.7/images/marker-shadow.png',\n    33→\t\t\t\ticonSize : [ 25, 41 ],\n    34→\t\t\t\ticonAnchor : [ 12, 41 ],\n    35→\t\t\t\tpopupAnchor : [ 1, -34 ],\n    36→\t\t\t\tshadowSize : [ 41, 41 ]\n    37→\t\t\t});\n    38→\n    39→\tconst greyIcon = new L.Icon(\n    40→\t\t\t{\n    41→\t\t\t\ticonUrl : 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pointhi/leaflet-color-markers/master/img/marker-icon-2x-grey.png',\n    42→\t\t\t\tshadowUrl : 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/leaflet/0.7.7/images/marker-shadow.png',\n    43→\t\t\t\ticonSize : [ 25, 41 ],\n    44→\t\t\t\ticonAnchor : [ 12, 41 ],\n    45→\t\t\t\tpopupAnchor : [ 1, -34 ],\n    46→\t\t\t\tshadowSize : [ 41, 41 ]\n    47→\t\t\t});\n    48→\n    49→\tconst redIcon = new L.Icon(\n    50→\t\t\t{\n    51→\t\t\t\ticonUrl : 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pointhi/leaflet-color-markers/master/img/marker-icon-2x-red.png',\n    52→\t\t\t\tshadowUrl : 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/leaflet/0.7.7/images/marker-shadow.png',\n    53→\t\t\t\ticonSize : [ 25, 41 ],\n    54→\t\t\t\ticonAnchor : [ 12, 41 ],\n    55→\t\t\t\tpopupAnchor : [ 1, -34 ],\n    56→\t\t\t\tshadowSize : [ 41, 41 ]\n    57→\t\t\t});\n    58→\n    59→\tconst blackIcon = new L.Icon(\n    60→\t\t\t{\n    61→\t\t\t\ticonUrl : 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pointhi/leaflet-color-markers/master/img/marker-icon-2x-black.png',\n    62→\t\t\t\tshadowUrl : 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/leaflet/0.7.7/images/marker-shadow.png',\n    63→\t\t\t\ticonSize : [ 25, 41 ],\n    64→\t\t\t\ticonAnchor : [ 12, 41 ],\n    65→\t\t\t\tpopupAnchor : [ 1, -34 ],\n    66→\t\t\t\tshadowSize : [ 41, 41 ]\n    67→\t\t\t});\n    68→\n    69→\tconst goldIcon = new L.Icon(\n    70→\t\t\t{\n    71→\t\t\t\ticonUrl : 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pointhi/leaflet-color-markers/master/img/marker-icon-2x-gold.png',\n    72→\t\t\t\tshadowUrl : 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/leaflet/0.7.7/images/marker-shadow.png',\n    73→\t\t\t\ticonSize : [ 25, 41 ],\n    74→\t\t\t\ticonAnchor : [ 12, 41 ],\n    75→\t\t\t\tpopupAnchor : [ 1, -34 ],\n    76→\t\t\t\tshadowSize : [ 41, 41 ]\n    77→\t\t\t});\n    78→\n    79→\tconst colorCodes = {\n    80→\t\t\"NOT_ROUTED\" : greyIcon,\n    81→\t\t\"NOT_RECEIVED\" : goldIcon,\n    82→\t\t\"IN_PORT\" : greenIcon,\n    83→\t\t\"ONBOARD_CARRIER\" : greenIcon,\n    84→\t\t\"MISDIRECTED\" : redIcon,\n    85→\t\t\"AT_DESTINATION\" : blackIcon,\n    86→\t\t\"CLAIMED\" : blackIcon,\n    87→\t\t\"UNKNOWN\" : redIcon\n    88→\t};\n    89→</script>\n    90→</head>\n    91→<body style=\"background-color: white\">\n    92→  <div>\n    93→    <div id=\"map\"\n    94→      style=\"height: 600px; border: #FFF; border-style: solid; border-width: 8px;\">\n    95→    </div>\n    96→  </div>\n    97→\n    98→  <script type=\"text/javascript\">\n    99→\t\t\twindow.onload = function init() {\n   100→\t\t\t\tvar cargo = JSON.parse(getUrlParameter('cargo'));\n   101→\n   102→\t\t\t\tconst originCoordinates = {\n   103→\t\t\t\t\tposition : {\n   104→\t\t\t\t\t\tlon : cargo.originCoordinates.longitude\n   105→\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t+ (Math.floor((Math.random() * 3) - 3)),\n   106→\t\t\t\t\t\tlat : cargo.originCoordinates.latitude\n   107→\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t+ (Math.floor((Math.random() * 3) - 3))\n   108→\t\t\t\t\t},\n   109→\t\t\t\t\tstyle : blackIcon\n   110→\t\t\t\t};\n   111→\n   112→\t\t\t\tconst destinationCoordinates = {\n   113→\t\t\t\t\tposition : {\n   114→\t\t\t\t\t\tlon : cargo.destinationCoordinates.longitude\n   115→\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t+ (Math.floor((Math.random() * 3) - 3)),\n   116→\t\t\t\t\t\tlat : cargo.destinationCoordinates.latitude\n   117→\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t+ (Math.floor((Math.random() * 3) - 3))\n   118→\t\t\t\t\t},\n   119→\t\t\t\t\tstyle : blackIcon\n   120→\t\t\t\t};\n   121→\n   122→\t\t\t\tconst lastKnownCoordinates = {\n   123→\t\t\t\t\tposition : {\n   124→\t\t\t\t\t\tlon : cargo.lastKnownLocationCoordinates.longitude\n   125→\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t+ (Math.floor((Math.random() * 3) - 3)),\n   126→\t\t\t\t\t\tlat : cargo.lastKnownLocationCoordinates.latitude\n   127→\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t+ (Math.floor((Math.random() * 3) - 3))\n   128→\t\t\t\t\t},\n   129→\t\t\t\t\tstyle : colorCodes[cargo.statusCode]\n   130→\t\t\t\t};\n   131→\n   132→\t\t\t\tconst map = L.map('map').setView({\n   133→\t\t\t\t\tlon : 0,\n   134→\t\t\t\t\tlat : 0\n   135→\t\t\t\t}, 2);\n   136→\n   137→\t\t\t\t// add the OpenStreetMap tiles\n   138→\t\t\t\tL\n   139→\t\t\t\t\t\t.tileLayer(\n   140→\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t'https://{s}.tile.openstreetmap.org/{z}/{x}/{y}.png',\n   141→\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t{\n   142→\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tmaxZoom : 19,\n   143→\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tattribution : '&#xA9;; &lt;a href=\"https://openstreetmap.org/copyright\">OpenStreetMap contributors&lt;/a>'\n   144→\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t}).addTo(map);\n   145→\n   146→\t\t\t\t// show the scale bar on the lower left corner\n   147→\t\t\t\tL.control.scale().addTo(map);\n   148→\n   149→\t\t\t\tL.marker(originCoordinates['position'], {\n   150→\t\t\t\t\ticon : originCoordinates.style\n   151→\t\t\t\t}).bindTooltip('Origin: ' + cargo.originName).addTo(map);\n   152→\n   153→\t\t\t\tL.marker(destinationCoordinates['position'], {\n   154→\t\t\t\t\ticon : destinationCoordinates.style\n   155→\t\t\t\t}).bindTooltip('Destination: ' + cargo.destinationName).addTo(\n   156→\t\t\t\t\t\tmap);\n   157→\n   158→\t\t\t\tL.marker(lastKnownCoordinates['position'], {\n   159→\t\t\t\t\ticon : lastKnownCoordinates.style\n   160→\t\t\t\t}).bindTooltip(\n   161→\t\t\t\t\t\t'Last known location: ' + cargo.lastKnownLocationName)\n   162→\t\t\t\t\t\t.addTo(map);\n   163→\t\t\t}\n   164→\t\t</script>\n   165→</body>\n   166→</html>\n   167→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CeohoG4JHS9obNcGYJWBuV","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"e0df6a36-48b2-420d-ac53-a9470a594162"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MdoB6kMW3mUZgemzp2stNb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     2→  xmlns:h=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/html\"\n     3→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\">\n     4→<ui:composition template=\"/WEB-INF/templates/common/public.xhtml\">\n     5→  <ui:define name=\"title\">About</ui:define>\n     6→  <ui:define name=\"content\">\n     7→    <div class=\"ui-grid-col-3\"></div>\n     8→    <div class=\"ui-grid-col-6\">\n     9→      <br />\n    10→      <div id=\"container\" style=\"display: none\" class=\"panel\">\n    11→        <h3>Tracking Your Cargo</h3>\n    12→        <p>The public tracking interface allows you to track your cargo and\n    13→          receive information such as current status, estimated time of arrival\n    14→          and detailed handling history.</p>\n    15→        <p>The interface does not require a login but you are expected to\n    16→          know your registered tracking ID - please contact your booking agent\n    17→          if you do not know your tracking ID. You should also contact your\n    18→          booking agent to make any modifications to your cargo such as a change\n    19→          in destination, a correction, etc or if your cargo is misdirected,\n    20→          delayed or held at customs.</p>\n    21→        <p>\n    22→          Visit <a href=\"https://eclipse-ee4j.github.io/cargotracker/\">https://eclipse-ee4j.github.io/cargotracker/</a>\n    23→          for more information about Eclipse Cargo Tracker.\n    24→        </p>\n    25→        <hr />\n    26→      </div>\n    27→    </div>\n    28→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/topbar.min.js\" />\n    29→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/topbar.js\" />\n    30→    <h:outputScript name=\"js/progress.js\" />\n    31→  </ui:define>\n    32→</ui:composition>\n    33→</html>\n    34→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CeohoG4JHS9obNcGYJWBuV","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"3061185e-2d70-4c36-9e66-740228d06e06"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MwWPxCoD2FAmpDUUsR1BZd","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<!DOCTYPE html>\n     2→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     3→  xmlns:h=\"http://java.sun.com/jsf/html\" xmlns:f=\"http://java.sun.com/jsf/core\"\n     4→  xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\">\n     5→<h:head>\n     6→  <title>Event Logger</title>\n     7→  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\" />\n     8→  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n     9→  <h:outputStylesheet name=\"css/app.css\" />\n    10→  <link rel=\"stylesheet\"\n    11→    href=\"//maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.3.0/css/font-awesome.min.css\" />\n    12→</h:head>\n    13→<h:body>\n    14→  <h:form>\n    15→    <p:growl id=\"growl\" showDetail=\"true\" life=\"1000\" />\n    16→    <p:wizard flowListener=\"#{eventLogger.onFlowProcess}\"\n    17→      onnext=\"hideBackButton()\" widgetVar=\"eventLogger\">\n    18→\n    19→      <p:tab id=\"trackingIdTab\" title=\"Tracking ID\">\n    20→        <p:panel header=\"Tracking ID\">\n    21→          <p:messages />\n    22→          <h:panelGrid columns=\"1\">\n    23→            <p:selectOneMenu id=\"trackingId\" value=\"#{eventLogger.trackingId}\"\n    24→              required=\"true\" requiredMessage=\"Tracking ID missing\">\n    25→              <f:selectItem itemLabel=\"Tracking ID\" itemValue=\"\"\n    26→                noSelectionOption=\"true\" />\n    27→              <f:selectItems value=\"#{eventLogger.trackingIds}\" />\n    28→            </p:selectOneMenu>\n    29→          </h:panelGrid>\n    30→        </p:panel>\n    31→      </p:tab>\n    32→      <p:tab id=\"locationTab\" title=\"Location\">\n    33→        <p:panel header=\"Location\">\n    34→          <p:messages />\n    35→          <h:panelGrid columns=\"1\">\n    36→            <p:selectOneMenu id=\"locationId\" value=\"#{eventLogger.location}\"\n    37→              required=\"true\" requiredMessage=\"Location missing\">\n    38→              <f:selectItem itemLabel=\"Location\" itemValue=\"\"\n    39→                noSelectionOption=\"true\" />\n    40→              <f:selectItems value=\"#{eventLogger.locations}\" />\n    41→            </p:selectOneMenu>\n    42→          </h:panelGrid>\n    43→        </p:panel>\n    44→      </p:tab>\n    45→      <p:tab id=\"eventTypeTab\" title=\"Event Type\">\n    46→        <p:panel header=\"Event Type\">\n    47→          <p:messages />\n    48→          <h:panelGrid columns=\"1\">\n    49→            <p:selectOneMenu id=\"eventType\" value=\"#{eventLogger.eventType}\"\n    50→              requiredMessage=\"Event type missing\" required=\"true\">\n    51→              <f:selectItem itemLabel=\"Event Type\" itemValue=\"\"\n    52→                noSelectionOption=\"true\" />\n    53→              <f:selectItems value=\"#{eventLogger.eventTypes}\" />\n    54→            </p:selectOneMenu>\n    55→          </h:panelGrid>\n    56→        </p:panel>\n    57→      </p:tab>\n    58→\n    59→      <p:tab id=\"voyageTab\" title=\"Voyage\">\n    60→        <p:panel header=\"Voyage\">\n    61→          <p:messages />\n    62→          <h:panelGrid columns=\"1\">\n    63→            <p:selectOneMenu id=\"voyage\" value=\"#{eventLogger.voyageNumber}\"\n    64→              required=\"false\">\n    65→              <f:selectItem itemLabel=\"Voyage\" itemValue=\"\"\n    66→                noSelectionOption=\"true\" />\n    67→              <f:selectItems value=\"#{eventLogger.voyages}\" />\n    68→            </p:selectOneMenu>\n    69→          </h:panelGrid>\n    70→        </p:panel>\n    71→      </p:tab>\n    72→      <p:tab id=\"dateTab\" title=\"Completion Date\">\n    73→        <p:panel header=\"Completion Date\">\n    74→          <p:messages />\n    75→          <h:panelGrid columns=\"1\">\n    76→            <p:calendar id=\"completionDate\"\n    77→              value=\"#{eventLogger.completionTime}\"\n    78→              pattern=\"#{eventLogger.completionTimePattern}\"\n    79→              requiredMessage=\"A date is needed\" required=\"true\">\n    80→            </p:calendar>\n    81→          </h:panelGrid>\n    82→        </p:panel>\n    83→      </p:tab>\n    84→      <p:tab id=\"confirm\" title=\"Confirmation\">\n    85→        <p:panel header=\"Confirmation\">\n    86→          <h:panelGrid id=\"confirmation\" columns=\"1\" columnClasses=\"grid\">\n    87→            <h:panelGrid columns=\"2\" columnClasses=\"label, value\">\n    88→              <h:outputText value=\"Tracking ID: \" />\n    89→              <h:outputText value=\"#{eventLogger.trackingId}\"\n    90→                styleClass=\"outputLabel\" />\n    91→              <h:outputText value=\"Location: \" />\n    92→              <h:outputText value=\"#{eventLogger.location}\"\n    93→                styleClass=\"outputLabel\" />\n    94→              <h:outputText value=\"Event type: \" />\n    95→              <h:outputText value=\"#{eventLogger.eventType}\"\n    96→                styleClass=\"outputLabel\" />\n    97→              <h:outputText value=\"Voyage number: \" />\n    98→              <h:outputText value=\"#{eventLogger.voyageNumber}\"\n    99→                styleClass=\"outputLabel\" />\n   100→              <h:outputText value=\"Date: \" />\n   101→              <h:outputText value=\"#{eventLogger.completionTimeValue}\"\n   102→                styleClass=\"outputLabel\" />\n   103→            </h:panelGrid>\n   104→          </h:panelGrid>\n   105→          <p:commandButton value=\"Submit\" action=\"#{eventLogger.submit}\"\n   106→            update=\"growl\" process=\"@this\"\n   107→            oncomplete=\"PF('eventLogger').loadStep('trackingIdTab', true)\" />\n   108→        </p:panel>\n   109→      </p:tab>\n   110→    </p:wizard>\n   111→  </h:form>\n   112→  <div class=\"ui-g ui-g-12\">\n   113→    <div class=\"ui-g-offset-5 ui-g-1\">\n   114→      <h:graphicImage value=\"#{resource['/images/CTlogobadge128.png']}\"\n   115→        height=\"68\" alt=\"Cargo Tracker logo badge\" />\n   116→    </div>\n   117→  </div>\n   118→  <script>\n   119→\t\t\tfunction hideBackButton() {\n   120→\t\t\t\t$(\"div.ui-wizard-navbar>button.ui-wizard-nav-back\").css(\n   121→\t\t\t\t\t\t\"display\", \"none\");\n   122→\t\t\t}\n   123→\t\t</script>\n   124→</h:body>\n   125→</html>\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CeohoG4JHS9obNcGYJWBuV","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"1ec77321-ce5a-4fec-9625-e4c96cbe6a30"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Y5DWY1JUeaPPi2bsrHw9JL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     2→  xmlns:h=\"http://java.sun.com/jsf/html\" xmlns:f=\"http://java.sun.com/jsf/core\"\n     3→  xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\"\n     4→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\">\n     5→<ui:composition template=\"/WEB-INF/templates/common/admin.xhtml\">\n     6→  <ui:define name=\"title\">Cargo Registration</ui:define>\n     7→  <ui:define name=\"content\">\n     8→    <div class=\"ui-g-2\" id=\"leftCol\"></div>\n     9→    <div class=\"ui-g-8\" id=\"mainCol\">\n    10→      <br />\n    11→      <h:form id=\"container\" style=\"display: none\">\n    12→        <p:outputLabel value=\"1. Choose the origin of the new cargo\" />\n    13→        <hr />\n    14→        <p:selectOneMenu id=\"origin\" value=\"#{booking.originUnlocode}\">\n    15→          <f:selectItems value=\"#{booking.locations}\" var=\"location\"\n    16→            itemLabel=\"#{location.name}\" itemValue=\"#{location.unLocode}\" />\n    17→        </p:selectOneMenu>\n    18→        <hr />\n    19→        <h:panelGrid columns=\"2\" style=\"margin: 0 auto;\">\n    20→          <p:commandButton value=\"Cancel\" action=\"/admin/dashboard\" />\n    21→          <p:commandButton value=\"Next\" action=\"booking-destination\" />\n    22→        </h:panelGrid>\n    23→      </h:form>\n    24→      <h:outputScript name=\"js/topbar.min.js\" />\n    25→      <h:outputScript name=\"js/topbar.js\" />\n    26→      <h:outputScript name=\"js/progress.js\" />\n    27→    </div>\n    28→  </ui:define>\n    29→</ui:composition>\n    30→</html>\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CeohoG4JHS9obNcGYJWBuV","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"d2c83e1b-490d-44fc-8359-a2f4802f7f7e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01K357Fx8uty8oma7bTiaWEe","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<!DOCTYPE html>\n     2→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     3→  xmlns:h=\"http://java.sun.com/jsf/html\" xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\"\n     4→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\">\n     5→<ui:composition template=\"/WEB-INF/templates/common/admin.xhtml\">\n     6→  <ui:define name=\"title\">Cargo Registration</ui:define>\n     7→  <ui:define name=\"content\">\n     8→    <div class=\"ui-g-2\" id=\"leftCol\"></div>\n     9→    <div class=\"ui-g-8\" id=\"mainCol\">\n    10→      <br />\n    11→      <h:form id=\"dateForm\">\n    12→        <p:outputLabel\n    13→          value=\"3. Set the arrival deadline for this new #{booking.originName}-#{booking.destinationName} cargo \" />\n    14→        <hr />\n    15→        <h:panelGrid columns=\"1\" styleClass=\"registrationPanelGrid\"\n    16→          style=\"margin: 0 auto;\">\n    17→          <p:calendar id=\"deadline\" value=\"#{booking.arrivalDeadline}\"\n    18→            mindate=\"#{booking.today}\" mode=\"inline\" pattern=\"yyyy-MM-dd\">\n    19→            <p:ajax event=\"dateSelect\" listener=\"#{booking.deadlineUpdated}\" />\n    20→          </p:calendar>\n    21→        </h:panelGrid>\n    22→        <h:panelGrid columns=\"1\" id=\"durationPanel\"\n    23→          styleClass=\"registrationPanelGrid\" style=\"margin: 0 auto;\">\n    24→          <p:outputLabel value=\"A journey can't start and end the same day!\"\n    25→            rendered=\"#{booking.duration eq 0}\" />\n    26→          <p:outputLabel value=\"Journey duration is one day.\"\n    27→            rendered=\"#{booking.duration eq 1}\" />\n    28→          <p:outputLabel value=\"Journey duration is #{booking.duration} days.\"\n    29→            rendered=\"#{booking.duration gt 1}\" />\n    30→        </h:panelGrid>\n    31→        <hr />\n    32→        <h:panelGrid columns=\"3\" styleClass=\"registrationPanelGrid\"\n    33→          style=\"margin: 0 auto;\">\n    34→          <p:commandButton value=\"Back\" action=\"booking-destination\" />\n    35→          <p:commandButton value=\"Cancel\" action=\"/admin/dashboard\" />\n    36→          <p:commandButton value=\"Book Cargo\" id=\"bookBtn\"\n    37→            action=\"#{booking.register()}\" disabled=\"#{!booking.bookable}\" />\n    38→        </h:panelGrid>\n    39→      </h:form>\n    40→    </div>\n    41→  </ui:define>\n    42→</ui:composition>\n    43→</html>\n    44→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CeohoG4JHS9obNcGYJWBuV","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"a24ef16a-fb39-43ea-aee1-df680d506c6b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DpmycRKTa1t9eEtVqF5fx6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<!DOCTYPE html>\n     2→<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n     3→  xmlns:h=\"http://java.sun.com/jsf/html\" xmlns:f=\"http://java.sun.com/jsf/core\"\n     4→  xmlns:p=\"http://primefaces.org/ui\"\n     5→  xmlns:ui=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/jsf/facelets\">\n     6→<ui:composition template=\"/WEB-INF/templates/common/admin.xhtml\">\n     7→  <ui:define name=\"title\">Cargo Registration</ui:define>\n     8→  <h:head>\n     9→    <style>\n    10→<!--\n    11→work around to fix selectonemenu bug in Chrome & Safari\n    12→\n    13→            -->.ui-selectonemenu-label {\n    14→  width: 90% !important;\n    15→}\n    16→</style>\n    17→  </h:head>\n    18→  <ui:define name=\"content\">\n    19→    <div class=\"ui-g-2\" id=\"leftCol\"></div>\n    20→    <div class=\"ui-g-8\" id=\"mainCol\">\n    21→      <br />\n    22→      <h:form>\n    23→        <p:outputLabel\n    24→          value=\"2. Set the destination for this new cargo coming from #{booking.originName}\" />\n    25→        <hr />\n    26→        <p:selectOneMenu id=\"destination\" value=\"#{booking.destinationUnlocode}\">\n    27→          <f:selectItems value=\"#{booking.locations}\" var=\"location\"\n    28→            itemLabel=\"#{location.name} \" itemValue=\"#{location.unLocode}\" />\n    29→        </p:selectOneMenu>\n    30→        <hr />\n    31→        <h:panelGrid columns=\"3\" styleClass=\"registrationPanelGrid\"\n    32→          style=\"margin: 0 auto;\">\n    33→          <p:commandButton value=\"Back\" action=\"booking\" />\n    34→          <p:commandButton value=\"Cancel\" action=\"/admin/dashboard\" />\n    35→          <p:commandButton value=\"Next\" action=\"booking-date\" />\n    36→        </h:panelGrid>\n    37→      </h:form>\n    38→    </div>\n    39→  </ui:define>\n    40→</ui:composition>\n    41→</html>\n    42→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CeohoG4JHS9obNcGYJWBuV","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"ede2f432-5582-40a3-a729-84d3972e8ace"}
