{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929","id":"msg_bdrk_015rtHipTgwG6gmowriq9nvf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_017UCU5cnzLxcpLEewuiQU3K","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/internal/assembler/CargoRouteDtoAssembler.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9826,"cache_read_input_tokens":85955,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":9826,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1184},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"51ab54bc-d1a0-4578-9e8f-6acc5b1e31b7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YW5WdoUqig8Lvpsk5kM5Bq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import javax.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n     6→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     7→import javax.inject.Named;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    11→import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    12→\n    13→/**\n    14→ * Handles changing the cargo destination. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could\n    15→ * easily be rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike\n    16→ * the tracking user interface.\n    17→ *\n    18→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    19→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there\n    20→ * is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    21→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    22→ */\n    23→@Named\n    24→@ViewScoped\n    25→public class ChangeArrivalDeadline implements Serializable {\n    26→\n    27→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    28→\n    29→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    30→\n    31→  private String trackingId;\n    32→  private CargoRoute cargo;\n    33→  private LocalDate arrivalDeadline;\n    34→\n    35→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    36→    return trackingId;\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    40→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    41→  }\n    42→\n    43→  public CargoRoute getCargo() {\n    44→    return cargo;\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  public LocalDate getArrivalDeadline() {\n    48→    return arrivalDeadline;\n    49→  }\n    50→\n    51→  public void setArrivalDeadline(LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n    52→    this.arrivalDeadline = arrivalDeadline;\n    53→  }\n    54→\n    55→  public void load() {\n    56→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    57→    arrivalDeadline = DateConverter.toDate(cargo.getArrivalDeadline());\n    58→  }\n    59→\n    60→  public void changeArrivalDeadline() {\n    61→    bookingServiceFacade.changeDeadline(trackingId, arrivalDeadline);\n    62→    PrimeFaces.current().dialog().closeDynamic(\"DONE\");\n    63→  }\n    64→}\n    65→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"621b8de3-8b03-4921-9780-6d22c6a6cedd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XfNeG4aTMvHreKCM5kR4Zw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import javax.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n     4→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     5→import javax.inject.Named;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n     8→\n     9→/**\n    10→ * Handles viewing cargo details. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be\n    11→ * rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the\n    12→ * tracking user interface.\n    13→ *\n    14→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    15→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there\n    16→ * is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    17→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    18→ */\n    19→@Named\n    20→@RequestScoped\n    21→public class CargoDetails {\n    22→\n    23→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    24→\n    25→  private String trackingId;\n    26→  private CargoRoute cargo;\n    27→\n    28→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    29→    return trackingId;\n    30→  }\n    31→\n    32→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    33→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  public CargoRoute getCargo() {\n    37→    return cargo;\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  public void load() {\n    41→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    42→  }\n    43→}\n    44→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"a03363d6-734f-4e68-b963-c36d68bb3c75"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Ga7Nf5KL4hw7w9Ngkn9oDi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n     6→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→import javax.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     9→import javax.faces.application.FacesMessage;\n    10→import javax.faces.context.FacesContext;\n    11→import javax.faces.flow.FlowScoped;\n    12→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    13→import javax.inject.Named;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location;\n    16→import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ * Handles booking cargo. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be rewritten\n    20→ * as a thick client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the tracking user\n    21→ * interface.\n    22→ *\n    23→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    24→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there\n    25→ * is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    26→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    27→ */\n    28→@Named\n    29→@FlowScoped(\"booking\")\n    30→public class Booking implements Serializable {\n    31→\n    32→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    33→\n    34→  private static final long MIN_JOURNEY_DURATION = 1; // Journey should be 1 day minimum.\n    35→\n    36→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    37→  @Inject private FacesContext context;\n    38→\n    39→  private LocalDate today = null;\n    40→  private List<Location> locations;\n    41→\n    42→  private String originUnlocode;\n    43→  private String originName;\n    44→  private String destinationName;\n    45→  private String destinationUnlocode;\n    46→  private LocalDate arrivalDeadline;\n    47→\n    48→  private boolean bookable = false;\n    49→  private long duration = -1;\n    50→\n    51→  @PostConstruct\n    52→  public void init() {\n    53→    today = LocalDate.now();\n    54→    locations = bookingServiceFacade.listShippingLocations();\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  public List<Location> getLocations() {\n    58→    List<Location> filteredLocations = new ArrayList<>();\n    59→    String locationToRemove = null;\n    60→\n    61→    if (context.getViewRoot().getViewId().endsWith(\"destination.xhtml\")) {\n    62→      // In the destination menu, origin can't be selected.\n    63→      locationToRemove = originUnlocode;\n    64→    } else { // Vice-versa.\n    65→      if (destinationUnlocode != null) {\n    66→        locationToRemove = destinationUnlocode;\n    67→      }\n    68→    }\n    69→\n    70→    for (Location location : locations) {\n    71→      if (!location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(locationToRemove)) {\n    72→        filteredLocations.add(location);\n    73→      }\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    return filteredLocations;\n    77→  }\n    78→\n    79→  public String getOriginUnlocode() {\n    80→    return originUnlocode;\n    81→  }\n    82→\n    83→  public void setOriginUnlocode(String originUnlocode) {\n    84→    this.originUnlocode = originUnlocode;\n    85→    this.originName =\n    86→        locations\n    87→            .stream()\n    88→            .filter(location -> location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(originUnlocode))\n    89→            .findAny()\n    90→            .get()\n    91→            .getName();\n    92→  }\n    93→\n    94→  public String getOriginName() {\n    95→    return originName;\n    96→  }\n    97→\n    98→  public String getDestinationUnlocode() {\n    99→    return destinationUnlocode;\n   100→  }\n   101→\n   102→  public void setDestinationUnlocode(String destinationUnlocode) {\n   103→    this.destinationUnlocode = destinationUnlocode;\n   104→    this.destinationName =\n   105→        locations\n   106→            .stream()\n   107→            .filter(location -> location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(destinationUnlocode))\n   108→            .findAny()\n   109→            .get()\n   110→            .getName();\n   111→  }\n   112→\n   113→  public String getDestinationName() {\n   114→    return destinationName;\n   115→  }\n   116→\n   117→  public LocalDate getToday() {\n   118→    return today;\n   119→  }\n   120→\n   121→  public LocalDate getArrivalDeadline() {\n   122→    return arrivalDeadline;\n   123→  }\n   124→\n   125→  public void setArrivalDeadline(LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n   126→    this.arrivalDeadline = arrivalDeadline;\n   127→  }\n   128→\n   129→  public long getDuration() {\n   130→    return duration;\n   131→  }\n   132→\n   133→  public boolean isBookable() {\n   134→    return bookable;\n   135→  }\n   136→\n   137→  public void deadlineUpdated() {\n   138→    duration = ChronoUnit.DAYS.between(today, arrivalDeadline);\n   139→\n   140→    if (duration >= MIN_JOURNEY_DURATION) {\n   141→      bookable = true;\n   142→    } else {\n   143→      bookable = false;\n   144→    }\n   145→\n   146→    PrimeFaces.current().ajax().update(\"dateForm:durationPanel\");\n   147→    PrimeFaces.current().ajax().update(\"dateForm:bookBtn\");\n   148→  }\n   149→\n   150→  public String register() {\n   151→    if (!originUnlocode.equals(destinationUnlocode)) {\n   152→      bookingServiceFacade.bookNewCargo(originUnlocode, destinationUnlocode, arrivalDeadline);\n   153→    } else {\n   154→      // UI now prevents from selecting same origin/destination\n   155→      FacesMessage message = new FacesMessage(\"Origin and destination cannot be the same.\");\n   156→      message.setSeverity(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR);\n   157→      context.addMessage(null, message);\n   158→      return null;\n   159→    }\n   160→\n   161→    return \"/admin/dashboard.xhtml\";\n   162→  }\n   163→\n   164→  public String getReturnValue() {\n   165→    return \"/admin/dashboard.xhtml\";\n   166→  }\n   167→}\n   168→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"3524374b-a71b-4df5-96f9-8126fd529fe1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GmsBQTMLjmLH2gBj4vWEQj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.sse;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.EnumMap;\n     4→import java.util.Map;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RoutingStatus;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus;\n     8→\n     9→/** View adapter for displaying a cargo in a realtime tracking context. */\n    10→public class RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter {\n    11→\n    12→  private static final Map<RoutingStatus, String> routingStatusLabels =\n    13→      new EnumMap<>(RoutingStatus.class);\n    14→  private static final Map<TransportStatus, String> transportStatusLabels =\n    15→      new EnumMap<>(TransportStatus.class);\n    16→\n    17→  private final Cargo cargo;\n    18→\n    19→  public RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter(Cargo cargo) {\n    20→    this.cargo = cargo;\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    24→    return cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString();\n    25→  }\n    26→\n    27→  public String getRoutingStatus() {\n    28→    return routingStatusLabels.get(cargo.getDelivery().getRoutingStatus());\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  public boolean isMisdirected() {\n    32→    return cargo.getDelivery().isMisdirected();\n    33→  }\n    34→\n    35→  public String getTransportStatus() {\n    36→    return transportStatusLabels.get(cargo.getDelivery().getTransportStatus());\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  public boolean isAtDestination() {\n    40→    return cargo.getDelivery().isUnloadedAtDestination();\n    41→  }\n    42→\n    43→  public LocationViewAdapter getOrigin() {\n    44→    return new LocationViewAdapter(cargo.getOrigin());\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  public LocationViewAdapter getLastKnownLocation() {\n    48→    return new LocationViewAdapter(cargo.getDelivery().getLastKnownLocation());\n    49→  }\n    50→\n    51→  public LocationViewAdapter getLocation() {\n    52→    return cargo.getDelivery().getTransportStatus() == TransportStatus.NOT_RECEIVED\n    53→        ? getOrigin()\n    54→        : getLastKnownLocation();\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  public String getStatusCode() {\n    58→    RoutingStatus routingStatus = cargo.getDelivery().getRoutingStatus();\n    59→\n    60→    if (routingStatus == RoutingStatus.NOT_ROUTED || routingStatus == RoutingStatus.MISROUTED) {\n    61→      return routingStatus.toString();\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    if (cargo.getDelivery().isMisdirected()) {\n    65→      return \"MISDIRECTED\";\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→    if (cargo.getDelivery().isUnloadedAtDestination()) {\n    69→      return \"AT_DESTINATION\";\n    70→    }\n    71→\n    72→    return cargo.getDelivery().getTransportStatus().toString();\n    73→  }\n    74→\n    75→  static {\n    76→    routingStatusLabels.put(RoutingStatus.NOT_ROUTED, \"Not routed\");\n    77→    routingStatusLabels.put(RoutingStatus.ROUTED, \"Routed\");\n    78→    routingStatusLabels.put(RoutingStatus.MISROUTED, \"Misrouted\");\n    79→\n    80→    transportStatusLabels.put(TransportStatus.NOT_RECEIVED, \"Not received\");\n    81→    transportStatusLabels.put(TransportStatus.IN_PORT, \"In port\");\n    82→    transportStatusLabels.put(TransportStatus.ONBOARD_CARRIER, \"Onboard carrier\");\n    83→    transportStatusLabels.put(TransportStatus.CLAIMED, \"Claimed\");\n    84→    transportStatusLabels.put(TransportStatus.UNKNOWN, \"Unknown\");\n    85→  }\n    86→}\n    87→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"0e9301f3-07ea-4fb8-82b5-6f5e1cb8ad4e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EBpUnNUegJXL68X7NQQzAz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.sse;\n     2→\n     3→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n     4→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.Coordinates;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.CoordinatesFactory;\n     6→\n     7→/** View adapter for displaying a location in a real-time tracking context. */\n     8→public class LocationViewAdapter {\n     9→\n    10→  private final Location location;\n    11→\n    12→  public LocationViewAdapter(Location location) {\n    13→    this.location = location;\n    14→  }\n    15→\n    16→  public String getUnLocode() {\n    17→    return location.getUnLocode().getIdString();\n    18→  }\n    19→\n    20→  public String getName() {\n    21→    return location.getName();\n    22→  }\n    23→\n    24→  public Coordinates getCoordinates() {\n    25→    return CoordinatesFactory.find(location);\n    26→  }\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"a3a42883-a3b2-4c7f-8686-361c0c0d7c72"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UuSsmdJbKaJ1kKxWPDLDKQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.sse;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→import javax.annotation.PreDestroy;\n     6→import javax.ejb.Singleton;\n     7→import javax.enterprise.event.ObservesAsync;\n     8→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     9→import javax.ws.rs.GET;\n    10→import javax.ws.rs.Path;\n    11→import javax.ws.rs.Produces;\n    12→import javax.ws.rs.core.Context;\n    13→import javax.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    14→import javax.ws.rs.sse.OutboundSseEvent;\n    15→import javax.ws.rs.sse.Sse;\n    16→import javax.ws.rs.sse.SseBroadcaster;\n    17→import javax.ws.rs.sse.SseEventSink;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    19→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    20→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi.CargoUpdated;\n    21→\n    22→/** Sever-sent events service for tracking all cargo in real time. */\n    23→@Singleton\n    24→@Path(\"/cargo\")\n    25→public class RealtimeCargoTrackingService {\n    26→  @Inject private Logger logger;\n    27→\n    28→  @Inject private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    29→\n    30→  private Sse sse;\n    31→  private SseBroadcaster broadcaster;\n    32→\n    33→  private synchronized void ensureBroadcaster(Sse sse) {\n    34→    if (this.sse == null) {\n    35→      this.sse = sse;\n    36→    }\n    37→    if (broadcaster == null) {\n    38→      broadcaster = this.sse.newBroadcaster();\n    39→      logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE broadcaster created.\");\n    40→    }\n    41→  }\n    42→\n    43→  @GET\n    44→  @Produces(MediaType.SERVER_SENT_EVENTS)\n    45→  public void tracking(@Context SseEventSink eventSink, @Context Sse sse) {\n    46→    ensureBroadcaster(sse);\n    47→\n    48→    cargoRepository.findAll().stream().map(this::cargoToSseEvent).forEach(eventSink::send);\n    49→\n    50→    broadcaster.register(eventSink);\n    51→    logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE event sink registered.\");\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  @PreDestroy\n    55→  public void close() {\n    56→    if (broadcaster != null) {\n    57→      broadcaster.close();\n    58→      logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE broadcaster closed.\");\n    59→    }\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  public void onCargoUpdated(@ObservesAsync @CargoUpdated Cargo cargo) {\n    63→    if (broadcaster != null) {\n    64→      logger.log(Level.FINEST, \"SSE event broadcast for cargo: {0}\", cargo);\n    65→      broadcaster.broadcast(cargoToSseEvent(cargo));\n    66→    }\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  private OutboundSseEvent cargoToSseEvent(Cargo cargo) {\n    70→    return sse.newEventBuilder()\n    71→        .mediaType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON_TYPE)\n    72→        .data(new RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter(cargo))\n    73→        .build();\n    74→  }\n    75→}\n    76→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"3d952775-dd4a-440d-b6cd-0349f16b8d26"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Kev5d5V8orvDUbvbUfCD9p","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler;\n     2→\n     3→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.TrackingEvents;\n     9→\n    10→@ApplicationScoped\n    11→public class TrackingEventsDtoAssembler {\n    12→\n    13→  public TrackingEvents toDto(Cargo cargo, HandlingEvent handlingEvent) {\n    14→    String location = locationFrom(handlingEvent);\n    15→    HandlingEvent.Type type = handlingEvent.getType();\n    16→    String voyageNumber = voyageNumberFrom(handlingEvent);\n    17→    return new TrackingEvents(\n    18→        cargo.getItinerary().isExpected(handlingEvent),\n    19→        descriptionFrom(type, location, voyageNumber),\n    20→        timeFrom(handlingEvent));\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  private String timeFrom(HandlingEvent event) {\n    24→    return DateConverter.toString(event.getCompletionTime());\n    25→  }\n    26→\n    27→  private String descriptionFrom(HandlingEvent.Type type, String location, String voyageNumber) {\n    28→    switch (type) {\n    29→      case LOAD:\n    30→        return \"Loaded onto voyage \" + voyageNumber + \" in \" + location;\n    31→      case UNLOAD:\n    32→        return \"Unloaded off voyage \" + voyageNumber + \" in \" + location;\n    33→      case RECEIVE:\n    34→        return \"Received in \" + location;\n    35→      case CLAIM:\n    36→        return \"Claimed in \" + location;\n    37→      case CUSTOMS:\n    38→        return \"Cleared customs in \" + location;\n    39→      default:\n    40→        return \"[Unknown]\";\n    41→    }\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  private String voyageNumberFrom(HandlingEvent handlingEvent) {\n    45→    Voyage voyage = handlingEvent.getVoyage();\n    46→    return voyage.getVoyageNumber().getIdString();\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  private String locationFrom(HandlingEvent handlingEvent) {\n    50→    return handlingEvent.getLocation().getName();\n    51→  }\n    52→}\n    53→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"1c68ea39-bb5e-4d0a-b163-5916a3a6b155"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01V73ko3bqxiUt85EUMZvS3S","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     6→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Leg;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.RouteCandidate;\n    18→\n    19→@ApplicationScoped\n    20→public class ItineraryCandidateDtoAssembler {\n    21→\n    22→  @Inject private LocationDtoAssembler locationDtoAssembler;\n    23→\n    24→  public RouteCandidate toDto(Itinerary itinerary) {\n    25→    List<org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Leg> legDTOs =\n    26→        itinerary.getLegs().stream().map(this::toLegDTO).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    27→    return new RouteCandidate(legDTOs);\n    28→  }\n    29→\n    30→  protected org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Leg toLegDTO(Leg leg) {\n    31→    VoyageNumber voyageNumber = leg.getVoyage().getVoyageNumber();\n    32→    return new org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Leg(\n    33→        voyageNumber.getIdString(),\n    34→        locationDtoAssembler.toDto(leg.getLoadLocation()),\n    35→        locationDtoAssembler.toDto(leg.getUnloadLocation()),\n    36→        leg.getLoadTime(),\n    37→        leg.getUnloadTime());\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  public Itinerary fromDTO(\n    41→      RouteCandidate routeCandidateDTO,\n    42→      VoyageRepository voyageRepository,\n    43→      LocationRepository locationRepository) {\n    44→    List<Leg> legs = new ArrayList<>(routeCandidateDTO.getLegs().size());\n    45→\n    46→    for (org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Leg legDTO :\n    47→        routeCandidateDTO.getLegs()) {\n    48→      VoyageNumber voyageNumber = new VoyageNumber(legDTO.getVoyageNumber());\n    49→      Voyage voyage = voyageRepository.find(voyageNumber);\n    50→      Location from = locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(legDTO.getFromUnLocode()));\n    51→      Location to = locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(legDTO.getToUnLocode()));\n    52→\n    53→      legs.add(\n    54→          new Leg(\n    55→              voyage,\n    56→              from,\n    57→              to,\n    58→              DateConverter.toDateTime(legDTO.getLoadTime()),\n    59→              DateConverter.toDateTime(legDTO.getUnloadTime())));\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    return new Itinerary(legs);\n    63→  }\n    64→}\n    65→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"c82b9637-44bb-47f8-b673-c1330e6bce1d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01P3DB8fdvYVZwZ93axK6q8L","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.Comparator;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     6→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n     8→\n     9→@ApplicationScoped\n    10→public class LocationDtoAssembler {\n    11→\n    12→  public org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location toDto(Location location) {\n    13→    return new org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location(\n    14→        location.getUnLocode().getIdString(), location.getName());\n    15→  }\n    16→\n    17→  public List<org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location> toDtoList(\n    18→      List<Location> allLocations) {\n    19→    List<org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location> dtoList =\n    20→        allLocations\n    21→            .stream()\n    22→            .map(this::toDto)\n    23→            .sorted(\n    24→                Comparator.comparing(\n    25→                    org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location::getUnLocode))\n    26→            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    27→    return dtoList;\n    28→  }\n    29→}\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"bada916f-27d6-4a3f-9541-a4f4fc314232"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017UCU5cnzLxcpLEewuiQU3K","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.internal.assembler;\n     2→\n     3→import static java.util.stream.Collectors.toList;\n     4→\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RoutingStatus;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Leg;\n    13→\n    14→@ApplicationScoped\n    15→public class CargoRouteDtoAssembler {\n    16→\n    17→  @Inject private LocationDtoAssembler locationDtoAssembler;\n    18→\n    19→  public CargoRoute toDto(Cargo cargo) {\n    20→    List<Leg> legs =\n    21→        cargo\n    22→            .getItinerary()\n    23→            .getLegs()\n    24→            .stream()\n    25→            .map(\n    26→                leg ->\n    27→                    new Leg(\n    28→                        leg.getVoyage().getVoyageNumber().getIdString(),\n    29→                        locationDtoAssembler.toDto(leg.getLoadLocation()),\n    30→                        locationDtoAssembler.toDto(leg.getUnloadLocation()),\n    31→                        leg.getLoadTime(),\n    32→                        leg.getUnloadTime()))\n    33→            .collect(toList());\n    34→\n    35→    return new CargoRoute(\n    36→        cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString(),\n    37→        locationDtoAssembler.toDto(cargo.getOrigin()),\n    38→        locationDtoAssembler.toDto(cargo.getRouteSpecification().getDestination()),\n    39→        cargo.getRouteSpecification().getArrivalDeadline(),\n    40→        cargo.getDelivery().getRoutingStatus().sameValueAs(RoutingStatus.MISROUTED),\n    41→        cargo.getDelivery().getTransportStatus().sameValueAs(TransportStatus.CLAIMED),\n    42→        locationDtoAssembler.toDto(cargo.getDelivery().getLastKnownLocation()),\n    43→        cargo.getDelivery().getTransportStatus().name(),\n    44→        legs);\n    45→  }\n    46→}\n    47→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"11eb27ca-901c-4625-b08f-694a17902108"}
