{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Dr39M721vkTPnb4MrCygTs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import static java.util.stream.Collectors.toList;\n     4→\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import javax.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     7→import javax.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n     8→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     9→import javax.inject.Named;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    12→\n    13→/**\n    14→ * Handles listing cargo. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be rewritten\n    15→ * as a thick client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the tracking user\n    16→ * interface.\n    17→ *\n    18→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    19→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there\n    20→ * is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    21→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    22→ */\n    23→@Named\n    24→@RequestScoped\n    25→public class ListCargo {\n    26→\n    27→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    28→\n    29→  private List<CargoRoute> notRoutedCargos;\n    30→  private List<CargoRoute> routedUnclaimedCargos;\n    31→  private List<CargoRoute> claimedCargos;\n    32→\n    33→  @PostConstruct\n    34→  public void init() {\n    35→    List<CargoRoute> cargos = bookingServiceFacade.listAllCargos();\n    36→    notRoutedCargos = cargos.stream().filter(route -> !route.isRouted()).collect(toList());\n    37→    routedUnclaimedCargos =\n    38→        cargos.stream().filter(route -> route.isRouted() && !route.isClaimed()).collect(toList());\n    39→    claimedCargos = cargos.stream().filter(CargoRoute::isClaimed).collect(toList());\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  public List<CargoRoute> getNotRoutedCargos() {\n    43→    return notRoutedCargos;\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  public List<CargoRoute> getRoutedUnclaimedCargos() {\n    47→    return routedUnclaimedCargos;\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  public List<CargoRoute> getClaimedCargos() {\n    51→    return claimedCargos;\n    52→  }\n    53→}\n    54→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"3107f746-583e-4410-8c41-7a9281e2e161"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CfmPqaJiHXEuxRRNh7WDnF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import javax.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     6→import javax.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n     7→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     8→import javax.inject.Named;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoStatus;\n    11→\n    12→/**\n    13→ * Handles tracking cargo. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be\n    14→ * rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the public\n    15→ * tracking user interface.\n    16→ *\n    17→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    18→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the public tracking controller. However,\n    19→ * there is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    20→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    21→ */\n    22→@Named(\"admin.track\")\n    23→@ViewScoped\n    24→public class Track implements Serializable {\n    25→\n    26→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    27→\n    28→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    29→\n    30→  private List<String> trackingIds;\n    31→  private String trackingId;\n    32→  private CargoStatus cargo;\n    33→\n    34→  public List<String> getTrackingIds(String query) {\n    35→    return trackingIds;\n    36→  }\n    37→\n    38→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    39→    return trackingId;\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    43→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  public CargoStatus getCargo() {\n    47→    return this.cargo;\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  @PostConstruct\n    51→  public void init() {\n    52→    trackingIds = bookingServiceFacade.listAllTrackingIds();\n    53→  }\n    54→\n    55→  public void onTrackById() {\n    56→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForTracking(this.trackingId);\n    57→  }\n    58→}\n    59→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"ba0c7c4a-e047-4479-a3d3-0c6db2009c27"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018JcxdMfvX2jZxNaThmrpdR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     6→import javax.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n     7→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     8→import javax.inject.Named;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location;\n    12→import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    13→\n    14→/**\n    15→ * Handles changing the cargo destination. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could\n    16→ * easily be rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike\n    17→ * the tracking user interface.\n    18→ *\n    19→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    20→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there\n    21→ * is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    22→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    23→ */\n    24→@Named\n    25→@ViewScoped\n    26→public class ChangeDestination implements Serializable {\n    27→\n    28→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    29→\n    30→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    31→\n    32→  private String trackingId;\n    33→  private CargoRoute cargo;\n    34→  private List<Location> locations;\n    35→  private String destinationUnlocode;\n    36→\n    37→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    38→    return trackingId;\n    39→  }\n    40→\n    41→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    42→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  public CargoRoute getCargo() {\n    46→    return cargo;\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  public List<Location> getLocations() {\n    50→    return locations;\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  public List<Location> getPotentialDestinations() {\n    54→    // Potential destination = All Locations - Origin - Current Destination\n    55→    List<Location> destinationsToRemove =\n    56→        locations\n    57→            .stream()\n    58→            .filter(\n    59→                location ->\n    60→                    location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(cargo.getOriginCode())\n    61→                        || location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(cargo.getFinalDestinationCode()))\n    62→            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    63→\n    64→    locations.removeAll(destinationsToRemove);\n    65→\n    66→    return locations;\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  public String getDestinationUnlocode() {\n    70→    return destinationUnlocode;\n    71→  }\n    72→\n    73→  public void setDestinationUnlocode(String destinationUnlocode) {\n    74→    this.destinationUnlocode = destinationUnlocode;\n    75→  }\n    76→\n    77→  public void load() {\n    78→    locations = bookingServiceFacade.listShippingLocations();\n    79→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    80→  }\n    81→\n    82→  public void changeDestination() {\n    83→    bookingServiceFacade.changeDestination(trackingId, destinationUnlocode);\n    84→    // PF.current().dialog().closeDynamic(\"DONE\");\n    85→    PrimeFaces.current().dialog().closeDynamic(\"DONE\");\n    86→    // RequestContext.getCurrentInstance().closeDialog(\"DONE\");\n    87→  }\n    88→}\n    89→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"2a0df913-bea8-4e8c-9ba5-9356d7234d39"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Q7vhuD4NFc4fw3zb12a8Nt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.HashMap;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import java.util.Map;\n     8→import javax.enterprise.context.SessionScoped;\n     9→import javax.inject.Named;\n    10→import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    11→import org.primefaces.event.SelectEvent;\n    12→\n    13→@Named\n    14→@SessionScoped\n    15→public class ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog implements Serializable {\n    16→\n    17→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    18→\n    19→  public void showDialog(String trackingId) {\n    20→    Map<String, Object> options = new HashMap<>();\n    21→    options.put(\"modal\", true);\n    22→    options.put(\"draggable\", true);\n    23→    options.put(\"resizable\", false);\n    24→    options.put(\"contentWidth\", 410);\n    25→    options.put(\"contentHeight\", 280);\n    26→\n    27→    Map<String, List<String>> params = new HashMap<>();\n    28→    List<String> values = new ArrayList<>();\n    29→    values.add(trackingId);\n    30→    params.put(\"trackingId\", values);\n    31→\n    32→    PrimeFaces.current()\n    33→        .dialog()\n    34→        .openDynamic(\"/admin/dialogs/change_arrival_deadline.xhtml\", options, params);\n    35→  }\n    36→\n    37→  public void handleReturn(@SuppressWarnings(\"rawtypes\") SelectEvent event) {}\n    38→\n    39→  public void cancel() {\n    40→    // just kill the dialog\n    41→    PrimeFaces.current().dialog().closeDynamic(\"\");\n    42→  }\n    43→}\n    44→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"4a958ffb-b0ed-4837-8f53-00ca3b601350"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01S9K4RFkX7QrhmEUFXzD6ix","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import javax.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n     6→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     7→import javax.inject.Named;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.RouteCandidate;\n    11→\n    12→/**\n    13→ * Handles itinerary selection. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be\n    14→ * rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the\n    15→ * tracking user interface.\n    16→ *\n    17→ * <p>In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations,\n    18→ * this approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there\n    19→ * is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    20→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    21→ */\n    22→@Named\n    23→@ViewScoped\n    24→public class ItinerarySelection implements Serializable {\n    25→\n    26→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    27→\n    28→  @Inject private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    29→\n    30→  List<RouteCandidate> routeCandidates;\n    31→  private String trackingId;\n    32→  private CargoRoute cargo;\n    33→\n    34→  public List<RouteCandidate> getRouteCandidates() {\n    35→    return routeCandidates;\n    36→  }\n    37→\n    38→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    39→    return trackingId;\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    43→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  public CargoRoute getCargo() {\n    47→    return cargo;\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  public List<RouteCandidate> getRouteCanditates() {\n    51→    return routeCandidates;\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  public void load() {\n    55→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    56→    routeCandidates = bookingServiceFacade.requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(trackingId);\n    57→  }\n    58→\n    59→  public String assignItinerary(int routeIndex) {\n    60→    RouteCandidate route = routeCandidates.get(routeIndex);\n    61→    bookingServiceFacade.assignCargoToRoute(trackingId, route);\n    62→\n    63→    return \"show.html?faces-redirect=true&trackingId=\" + trackingId;\n    64→  }\n    65→}\n    66→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"a17708c3-9b4c-4ed0-ab34-fb59ea88ebe8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Y3D6R6MBik7Y8CnQGQSpFg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.HashMap;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import java.util.Map;\n     8→import javax.enterprise.context.SessionScoped;\n     9→import javax.inject.Named;\n    10→import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    11→import org.primefaces.event.SelectEvent;\n    12→\n    13→@Named\n    14→@SessionScoped\n    15→public class ChangeDestinationDialog implements Serializable {\n    16→\n    17→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    18→\n    19→  public void showDialog(String trackingId) {\n    20→    Map<String, Object> options = new HashMap<>();\n    21→    options.put(\"modal\", true);\n    22→    options.put(\"draggable\", true);\n    23→    options.put(\"resizable\", false);\n    24→    options.put(\"contentWidth\", 410);\n    25→    options.put(\"contentHeight\", 280);\n    26→\n    27→    Map<String, List<String>> params = new HashMap<>();\n    28→    List<String> values = new ArrayList<>();\n    29→    values.add(trackingId);\n    30→    params.put(\"trackingId\", values);\n    31→\n    32→    PrimeFaces.current()\n    33→        .dialog()\n    34→        .openDynamic(\"/admin/dialogs/change_destination.xhtml\", options, params);\n    35→  }\n    36→\n    37→  public void handleReturn(@SuppressWarnings(\"rawtypes\") SelectEvent event) {}\n    38→\n    39→  public void cancel() {\n    40→    // just kill the dialog\n    41→    PrimeFaces.current().dialog().closeDynamic(\"\");\n    42→  }\n    43→}\n    44→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"e9c9ad28-7acd-4b2a-8002-87e7dfd9841c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CgRfTTCbo5eTQZ826HpD4T","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.pathfinder.internal;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.Arrays;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import java.util.Random;\n     8→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     9→\n    10→@ApplicationScoped\n    11→public class GraphDao implements Serializable {\n    12→\n    13→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    14→\n    15→  private final Random random = new Random();\n    16→\n    17→  public List<String> listLocations() {\n    18→    return new ArrayList<>(\n    19→        Arrays.asList(\n    20→            \"CNHKG\", \"AUMEL\", \"SESTO\", \"FIHEL\", \"USCHI\", \"JNTKO\", \"DEHAM\", \"CNSHA\", \"NLRTM\",\n    21→            \"SEGOT\", \"CNHGH\", \"USNYC\", \"USDAL\"));\n    22→  }\n    23→\n    24→  public String getVoyageNumber(String from, String to) {\n    25→    int i = random.nextInt(5);\n    26→\n    27→    switch (i) {\n    28→      case 0:\n    29→        return \"0100S\";\n    30→      case 1:\n    31→        return \"0200T\";\n    32→      case 2:\n    33→        return \"0300A\";\n    34→      case 3:\n    35→        return \"0301S\";\n    36→      default:\n    37→        return \"0400S\";\n    38→    }\n    39→  }\n    40→}\n    41→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"1fea4576-f55b-4be9-a210-34e0a43bd14a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Saycv5X5WJFZQzMWec7kP8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.pathfinder.api;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import javax.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement;\n     7→\n     8→@XmlRootElement\n     9→public class TransitPath implements Serializable {\n    10→\n    11→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    12→\n    13→  private List<TransitEdge> transitEdges;\n    14→\n    15→  public TransitPath() {\n    16→    this.transitEdges = new ArrayList<>();\n    17→  }\n    18→\n    19→  public TransitPath(List<TransitEdge> transitEdges) {\n    20→    this.transitEdges = transitEdges;\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  public List<TransitEdge> getTransitEdges() {\n    24→    return transitEdges;\n    25→  }\n    26→\n    27→  public void setTransitEdges(List<TransitEdge> transitEdges) {\n    28→    this.transitEdges = transitEdges;\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  @Override\n    32→  public String toString() {\n    33→    return \"TransitPath{\" + \"transitEdges=\" + transitEdges + '}';\n    34→  }\n    35→}\n    36→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"c4b80161-5486-435b-ae0f-72cdd4bac542"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FNuarHX1Ja7HiUgRT4T4Rk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.pathfinder.api;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→\n     6→/** Represents an edge in a path through a graph, describing the route of a cargo. */\n     7→public class TransitEdge implements Serializable {\n     8→\n     9→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    10→\n    11→  private String voyageNumber;\n    12→  private String fromUnLocode;\n    13→  private String toUnLocode;\n    14→  private LocalDateTime fromDate;\n    15→  private LocalDateTime toDate;\n    16→\n    17→  public TransitEdge() {\n    18→    // Nothing to do.\n    19→  }\n    20→\n    21→  public TransitEdge(\n    22→      String voyageNumber,\n    23→      String fromUnLocode,\n    24→      String toUnLocode,\n    25→      LocalDateTime fromDate,\n    26→      LocalDateTime toDate) {\n    27→    this.voyageNumber = voyageNumber;\n    28→    this.fromUnLocode = fromUnLocode;\n    29→    this.toUnLocode = toUnLocode;\n    30→    this.fromDate = fromDate;\n    31→    this.toDate = toDate;\n    32→  }\n    33→\n    34→  public String getVoyageNumber() {\n    35→    return voyageNumber;\n    36→  }\n    37→\n    38→  public void setVoyageNumber(String voyageNumber) {\n    39→    this.voyageNumber = voyageNumber;\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  public String getFromUnLocode() {\n    43→    return fromUnLocode;\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  public void setFromUnLocode(String fromUnLocode) {\n    47→    this.fromUnLocode = fromUnLocode;\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  public String getToUnLocode() {\n    51→    return toUnLocode;\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  public void setToUnLocode(String toUnLocode) {\n    55→    this.toUnLocode = toUnLocode;\n    56→  }\n    57→\n    58→  public LocalDateTime getFromDate() {\n    59→    return fromDate;\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  public void setFromDate(LocalDateTime fromDate) {\n    63→    this.fromDate = fromDate;\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  public LocalDateTime getToDate() {\n    67→    return toDate;\n    68→  }\n    69→\n    70→  public void setToDate(LocalDateTime toDate) {\n    71→    this.toDate = toDate;\n    72→  }\n    73→\n    74→  @Override\n    75→  public String toString() {\n    76→    return \"TransitEdge{\"\n    77→        + \"voyageNumber=\"\n    78→        + voyageNumber\n    79→        + \", fromUnLocode=\"\n    80→        + fromUnLocode\n    81→        + \", toUnLocode=\"\n    82→        + toUnLocode\n    83→        + \", fromDate=\"\n    84→        + fromDate\n    85→        + \", toDate=\"\n    86→        + toDate\n    87→        + '}';\n    88→  }\n    89→}\n    90→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"5e500f2f-2e31-48d7-9c3c-783d6e55696f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01R8VCXJhHRHLf4Bt3qJsSdi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.pathfinder.api;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     4→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.Collections;\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→import java.util.Random;\n     9→import javax.ejb.Stateless;\n    10→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    11→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    12→import javax.validation.constraints.Pattern;\n    13→import javax.validation.constraints.Size;\n    14→import javax.ws.rs.GET;\n    15→import javax.ws.rs.Path;\n    16→import javax.ws.rs.Produces;\n    17→import javax.ws.rs.QueryParam;\n    18→import org.eclipse.pathfinder.internal.GraphDao;\n    19→\n    20→@Stateless\n    21→@Path(\"/graph-traversal\")\n    22→public class GraphTraversalService {\n    23→\n    24→  private static final long ONE_MIN_MS = 1000 * 60;\n    25→  private static final long ONE_DAY_MS = ONE_MIN_MS * 60 * 24;\n    26→  private static final String UNLOCODE_PATTERN_VIOLATION_MESSAGE =\n    27→      \"UN location code value must be five characters long, \"\n    28→          + \"the first two must be alphabetic and \"\n    29→          + \"the last three must be alphanumeric (excluding 0 and 1).\";\n    30→  private final Random random = new Random();\n    31→  @Inject private GraphDao dao;\n    32→\n    33→  @GET\n    34→  @Path(\"/shortest-path\")\n    35→  @Produces({\"application/json\", \"application/xml; qs=.75\"})\n    36→  public List<TransitPath> findShortestPath(\n    37→      @NotNull(message = \"Missing origin UN location code.\")\n    38→          @Pattern(\n    39→              regexp = \"[a-zA-Z]{2}[a-zA-Z2-9]{3}\",\n    40→              message = \"Origin \" + UNLOCODE_PATTERN_VIOLATION_MESSAGE)\n    41→          @QueryParam(\"origin\")\n    42→          String originUnLocode,\n    43→      @NotNull(message = \"Missing destination UN location code.\")\n    44→          @Pattern(\n    45→              regexp = \"[a-zA-Z]{2}[a-zA-Z2-9]{3}\",\n    46→              message = \"Destination \" + UNLOCODE_PATTERN_VIOLATION_MESSAGE)\n    47→          @QueryParam(\"destination\")\n    48→          String destinationUnLocode,\n    49→      // TODO [DDD] Apply regular expression validation.\n    50→      @Size(min = 8, max = 8, message = \"Deadline value must be eight characters long.\")\n    51→          @QueryParam(\"deadline\")\n    52→          String deadline) {\n    53→\n    54→    List<String> allVertices = dao.listLocations();\n    55→    allVertices.remove(originUnLocode);\n    56→    allVertices.remove(destinationUnLocode);\n    57→\n    58→    int candidateCount = getRandomNumberOfCandidates();\n    59→    List<TransitPath> candidates = new ArrayList<>(candidateCount);\n    60→\n    61→    for (int i = 0; i < candidateCount; i++) {\n    62→      allVertices = getRandomChunkOfLocations(allVertices);\n    63→      List<TransitEdge> transitEdges = new ArrayList<>(allVertices.size() - 1);\n    64→      String fromUnLocode = originUnLocode;\n    65→      LocalDateTime date = LocalDateTime.now();\n    66→\n    67→      for (int j = 0; j <= allVertices.size(); ++j) {\n    68→        LocalDateTime fromDate = nextDate(date);\n    69→        LocalDateTime toDate = nextDate(fromDate);\n    70→        String toUnLocode = (j >= allVertices.size() ? destinationUnLocode : allVertices.get(j));\n    71→        transitEdges.add(\n    72→            new TransitEdge(\n    73→                dao.getVoyageNumber(fromUnLocode, toUnLocode),\n    74→                fromUnLocode,\n    75→                toUnLocode,\n    76→                fromDate,\n    77→                toDate));\n    78→        fromUnLocode = toUnLocode;\n    79→        date = nextDate(toDate);\n    80→      }\n    81→      candidates.add(new TransitPath(transitEdges));\n    82→    }\n    83→    return candidates;\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  private LocalDateTime nextDate(LocalDateTime date) {\n    87→    return date.plus(ONE_DAY_MS + (random.nextInt(1000) - 500) * ONE_MIN_MS, ChronoUnit.MILLIS);\n    88→  }\n    89→\n    90→  private int getRandomNumberOfCandidates() {\n    91→    return 3 + random.nextInt(3);\n    92→  }\n    93→\n    94→  private List<String> getRandomChunkOfLocations(List<String> allLocations) {\n    95→    Collections.shuffle(allLocations);\n    96→    int total = allLocations.size();\n    97→    int chunk = total > 4 ? 1 + random.nextInt(5) : total;\n    98→    return allLocations.subList(0, chunk);\n    99→  }\n   100→}\n   101→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015xY2XDHV9vTQQdv1Xp54tY","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"803719f4-558f-45da-9d08-1f7af716d2ce"}
