ation/util/SampleDataGenerator.java** - Loads sample data for demo (354 lines)\n\n6. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/ApplicationSettings.java** - Application settings entity (26 lines)\n\n7. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/DateConverter.java** - Date conversion utilities (36 lines)\n\n8. **/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/RestConfiguration.java** - Jakarta REST configuration (19 lines)\n\n### Application Internal (3 files)\n\n9-11. Default implementations for HandlingEventService, CargoInspectionService, and BookingService\n\n### Domain Model - Handling (11 files)\n\n12-22. Core handling event models including HandlingEvent, HandlingHistory, HandlingEventRepository, HandlingEventFactory, and exception classes\n\n### Domain Model - Cargo (10 files)\n\n23-32. Cargo domain models including Cargo, TrackingId, Itinerary, Leg, RouteSpecification, Delivery, HandlingActivity, TransportStatus, RoutingStatus, and CargoRepository\n\n### Domain Model - Voyage (6 files)\n\n33-38. Voyage models including Voyage, VoyageNumber, Schedule, CarrierMovement, SampleVoyages, and VoyageRepository\n\n### Domain Model - Location (6 files)\n\n39-44. Location models including Location, UnLocode, SampleLocations, and LocationRepository\n\n### Domain Shared (6 files)\n\n45-50. Specification pattern implementations and domain utilities\n\n### Domain Service (1 file)\n\n51. RoutingService interface\n\n### Infrastructure (15 files)\n\n52-66. Infrastructure components including:\n- CDI events\n- Logger producer\n- JPA repositories (Cargo, Voyage, Location, HandlingEvent)\n- JMS messaging consumers and events\n- Routing service implementation\n\n### Interfaces (30 files)\n\n67-96. User interface components including:\n- Faces configuration\n- Coordinates factory and class\n- Booking facade and DTOs\n- Web controllers (Booking, CargoDetails, Track, ChangeDestination, etc.)\n- SSE real-time tracking\n- Handling event registration\n- File processing batch jobs\n- Assemblers for DTOs\n\n### Pathfinder API (4 files)\n\n93-96. External pathfinding service components (GraphDao, TransitPath, TransitEdge, GraphTraversalService)\n\nAll files have been read in their entirety with complete source code as shown in the read operations above. The application appears to be a Domain-Driven Design (DDD) implementation of a cargo tracking system using Jakarta EE technologies, demonstrating concepts like aggregates, repositories, services, and event-driven architecture."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"85b96616-9f4f-4825-a676-21cb8f0e25cb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CeohoG4JHS9obNcGYJWBuV","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have now read all configuration and resource files. Let me create a comprehensive summary of all the files I've read.\n\n## Summary of All Configuration and Resource Files\n\nI have successfully read ALL configuration and resource files in the `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/` directory. There is **no smoke/ directory** in the project root.\n\n### Complete File Inventory:\n\n---\n\n## XML Configuration Files (13 files)\n\n### 1. **Web Application Configuration Files**\n\n**File:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/web.xml`\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<web-app xmlns=\"http://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee\"\n  xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\" version=\"4.0\"\n  xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee https://xmlns.jcp.org/xml/ns/javaee/web-app_4_0.xsd\">\n  <!-- Context parameters for JSF -->\n  <context-param>\n    <param-name>javax.faces.PROJECT_STAGE</param-name>\n    <param-value>Development</param-value>\n  </context-param>\n  <context-param>\n    <param-name>javax.faces.CLIENT_WINDOW_MODE</param-name>\n    <param-value>url</param-value>\n  </context-param>\n  <context-param>\n    <param-name>primefaces.THEME</param-name>\n    <param-value>saga</param-value>\n  </context-param>\n  <context-param>\n    <param-name>primefaces.FONT_AWESOME</param-name>\n    <param-value>true</param-value>\n  </context-param>\n  <context-param>\n    <param-name>primefaces.MOVE_SCRIPTS_TO_BOTTOM</param-name>\n    <param-value>true</param-value>\n  </context-param>\n  <!-- MIME mappings, servlet configuration, JMS queues, and data sour