{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WH1RwX82peTi3Jc6raP2WQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n     2→\n     3→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     4→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n     6→\n     7→/**\n     8→ * This interface provides a way to let other parts of the system know about events that have\n     9→ * occurred.\n    10→ *\n    11→ * <p>It may be implemented synchronously or asynchronously, using for example JMS.\n    12→ */\n    13→public interface ApplicationEvents {\n    14→\n    15→  void cargoWasHandled(HandlingEvent event);\n    16→\n    17→  void cargoWasMisdirected(Cargo cargo);\n    18→\n    19→  void cargoHasArrived(Cargo cargo);\n    20→\n    21→  void receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt);\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"244f4afb-726d-4930-8d8d-964348edc97e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01AthrgzyPWi45NFVYX72NQu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import javax.validation.Valid;\n     6→import javax.validation.constraints.Future;\n     7→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    11→\n    12→/** Cargo booking service. */\n    13→public interface BookingService {\n    14→\n    15→  /** Registers a new cargo in the tracking system, not yet routed. */\n    16→  TrackingId bookNewCargo(\n    17→      @NotNull(message = \"Origin is required.\") @Valid UnLocode origin,\n    18→      @NotNull(message = \"Destination is required.\") @Valid UnLocode destination,\n    19→      @NotNull(message = \"Deadline is required.\")\n    20→          @Future(message = \"Deadline must be in the future.\")\n    21→          LocalDate arrivalDeadline);\n    22→\n    23→  /**\n    24→   * Requests a list of itineraries describing possible routes for this cargo.\n    25→   *\n    26→   * @param trackingId Cargo tracking ID\n    27→   * @return A list of possible itineraries for this cargo\n    28→   */\n    29→  List<Itinerary> requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(\n    30→      @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId);\n    31→\n    32→  void assignCargoToRoute(\n    33→      @NotNull(message = \"Itinerary is required.\") @Valid Itinerary itinerary,\n    34→      @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId);\n    35→\n    36→  void changeDestination(\n    37→      @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId,\n    38→      @NotNull(message = \"Destination is required.\") @Valid UnLocode unLocode);\n    39→\n    40→  void changeDeadline(\n    41→      @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\") @Valid TrackingId trackingId,\n    42→      @NotNull(message = \"Deadline is required.\")\n    43→          @Future(message = \"Deadline must be in the future.\")\n    44→          LocalDate deadline);\n    45→}\n    46→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"dca004e2-960d-4efa-99ed-b71424e53425"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017LHL1bK5nivg4ZP9v3yvoF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.util.Arrays;\n     6→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     7→import javax.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     8→import javax.ejb.Singleton;\n     9→import javax.ejb.Startup;\n    10→import javax.ejb.TransactionAttribute;\n    11→import javax.ejb.TransactionAttributeType;\n    12→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    13→import javax.persistence.EntityManager;\n    14→import javax.persistence.LockModeType;\n    15→import javax.persistence.NoResultException;\n    16→import javax.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n    19→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Leg;\n    20→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    22→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.CannotCreateHandlingEventException;\n    23→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    24→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventFactory;\n    25→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventRepository;\n    26→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingHistory;\n    27→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations;\n    28→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.SampleVoyages;\n    29→\n    30→/** Loads sample data for demo. */\n    31→@Singleton\n    32→@Startup\n    33→public class SampleDataGenerator {\n    34→\n    35→  @Inject private Logger logger;\n    36→\n    37→  @PersistenceContext private EntityManager entityManager;\n    38→  @Inject private HandlingEventFactory handlingEventFactory;\n    39→  @Inject private HandlingEventRepository handlingEventRepository;\n    40→\n    41→  @PostConstruct\n    42→  @TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED)\n    43→  public void loadSampleData() {\n    44→    if (!isSampleLoaded()) {\n    45→      logger.info(\"Loading sample data.\");\n    46→      loadSampleLocations();\n    47→      loadSampleVoyages();\n    48→      loadSampleCargos();\n    49→    } else {\n    50→      logger.info(\"Sample data already loaded, skipping.\");\n    51→    }\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  private boolean isSampleLoaded() {\n    55→    boolean sampleLoaded = false;\n    56→\n    57→    try {\n    58→      ApplicationSettings settings =\n    59→          entityManager.find(ApplicationSettings.class, 1L, LockModeType.PESSIMISTIC_WRITE);\n    60→      sampleLoaded = settings.isSampleLoaded();\n    61→      settings.setSampleLoaded(true);\n    62→    } catch (NoResultException e) {\n    63→      throw new RuntimeException(\"Could not retrieve application settings.\", e);\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    return sampleLoaded;\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  private void loadSampleLocations() {\n    70→    logger.info(\"Loading sample locations.\");\n    71→\n    72→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.HONGKONG);\n    73→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.MELBOURNE);\n    74→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM);\n    75→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.HELSINKI);\n    76→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.CHICAGO);\n    77→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.TOKYO);\n    78→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.HAMBURG);\n    79→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.SHANGHAI);\n    80→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.ROTTERDAM);\n    81→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.GOTHENBURG);\n    82→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.HANGZOU);\n    83→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.NEWYORK);\n    84→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.DALLAS);\n    85→  }\n    86→\n    87→  private void loadSampleVoyages() {\n    88→    logger.info(\"Loading sample voyages.\");\n    89→\n    90→    entityManager.persist(SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK);\n    91→    entityManager.persist(SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS);\n    92→    entityManager.persist(SampleVoyages.DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI);\n    93→    entityManager.persist(SampleVoyages.HELSINKI_TO_HONGKONG);\n    94→    entityManager.persist(SampleVoyages.DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI_ALT);\n    95→  }\n    96→\n    97→  private void loadSampleCargos() {\n    98→    logger.info(\"Loading sample cargo data.\");\n    99→\n   100→    // Cargo ABC123. This one is en-route.\n   101→    TrackingId trackingId1 = new TrackingId(\"ABC123\");\n   102→\n   103→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification1 =\n   104→        new RouteSpecification(\n   105→            SampleLocations.HONGKONG, SampleLocations.HELSINKI, LocalDate.now().plusDays(15));\n   106→    Cargo abc123 = new Cargo(trackingId1, routeSpecification1);\n   107→\n   108→    Itinerary itinerary1 =\n   109→        new Itinerary(\n   110→            Arrays.asList(\n   111→                new Leg(\n   112→                    SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK,\n   113→                    SampleLocations.HONGKONG,\n   114→                    SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n   115→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(7).minusHours(2).minusMinutes(4),\n   116→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(1).minusHours(10).minusMinutes(52)),\n   117→                new Leg(\n   118→                    SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS,\n   119→                    SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n   120→                    SampleLocations.DALLAS,\n   121→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(2).minusHours(18).minusMinutes(38),\n   122→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(6).minusHours(3).minusMinutes(22)),\n   123→                new Leg(\n   124→                    SampleVoyages.DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI,\n   125→                    SampleLocations.DALLAS,\n   126→                    SampleLocations.HELSINKI,\n   127→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(8).minusHours(8).minusMinutes(18),\n   128→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(14).minusHours(12).minusMinutes(29))));\n   129→    abc123.assignToRoute(itinerary1);\n   130→\n   131→    entityManager.persist(abc123);\n   132→\n   133→    try {\n   134→      HandlingEvent event1 =\n   135→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   136→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(5).minusMinutes(5),\n   137→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(10).minusHours(9).minusMinutes(11),\n   138→              trackingId1,\n   139→              null,\n   140→              SampleLocations.HONGKONG.getUnLocode(),\n   141→              HandlingEvent.Type.RECEIVE);\n   142→      entityManager.persist(event1);\n   143→\n   144→      HandlingEvent event2 =\n   145→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   146→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(6).minusMinutes(46),\n   147→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(7).minusHours(2).minusMinutes(50),\n   148→              trackingId1,\n   149→              SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK.getVoyageNumber(),\n   150→              SampleLocations.HONGKONG.getUnLocode(),\n   151→              HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD);\n   152→      entityManager.persist(event2);\n   153→\n   154→      HandlingEvent event3 =\n   155→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   156→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(15).minusMinutes(26),\n   157→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(1).minusHours(4).minusMinutes(32),\n   158→              trackingId1,\n   159→              SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK.getVoyageNumber(),\n   160→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK.getUnLocode(),\n   161→              HandlingEvent.Type.UNLOAD);\n   162→      entityManager.persist(event3);\n   163→    } catch (CannotCreateHandlingEventException e) {\n   164→      throw new RuntimeException(e);\n   165→    }\n   166→\n   167→    HandlingHistory handlingHistory1 =\n   168→        handlingEventRepository.lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(trackingId1);\n   169→    abc123.deriveDeliveryProgress(handlingHistory1);\n   170→\n   171→    entityManager.persist(abc123);\n   172→\n   173→    // Cargo JKL567. This one was loaded on the wrong voyage.\n   174→    TrackingId trackingId2 = new TrackingId(\"JKL567\");\n   175→\n   176→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification2 =\n   177→        new RouteSpecification(\n   178→            SampleLocations.HANGZOU, SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM, LocalDate.now().plusDays(18));\n   179→    Cargo jkl567 = new Cargo(trackingId2, routeSpecification2);\n   180→\n   181→    Itinerary itinerary2 =\n   182→        new Itinerary(\n   183→            Arrays.asList(\n   184→                new Leg(\n   185→                    SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK,\n   186→                    SampleLocations.HANGZOU,\n   187→                    SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n   188→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(10).minusHours(1).minusMinutes(19),\n   189→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(3).minusHours(7).minusMinutes(2)),\n   190→                new Leg(\n   191→                    SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS,\n   192→                    SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n   193→                    SampleLocations.DALLAS,\n   194→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(2).minusHours(17).minusMinutes(3),\n   195→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(2).minusHours(5).minusMinutes(20)),\n   196→                new Leg(\n   197→                    SampleVoyages.DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI,\n   198→                    SampleLocations.DALLAS,\n   199→                    SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM,\n   200→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(6).minusHours(11).minusMinutes(38),\n   201→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(15).minusHours(4).minusMinutes(1))));\n   202→    jkl567.assignToRoute(itinerary2);\n   203→\n   204→    entityManager.persist(jkl567);\n   205→\n   206→    try {\n   207→      HandlingEvent event1 =\n   208→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   209→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(2).minusMinutes(44),\n   210→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(15).minusHours(14).minusMinutes(33),\n   211→              trackingId2,\n   212→              null,\n   213→              SampleLocations.HANGZOU.getUnLocode(),\n   214→              HandlingEvent.Type.RECEIVE);\n   215→      entityManager.persist(event1);\n   216→\n   217→      HandlingEvent event2 =\n   218→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   219→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(3).minusMinutes(12),\n   220→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(10).minusHours(3).minusMinutes(17),\n   221→              trackingId2,\n   222→              SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK.getVoyageNumber(),\n   223→              SampleLocations.HANGZOU.getUnLocode(),\n   224→              HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD);\n   225→      entityManager.persist(event2);\n   226→\n   227→      HandlingEvent event3 =\n   228→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   229→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(3).minusMinutes(21),\n   230→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(3).minusHours(22).minusMinutes(1),\n   231→              trackingId2,\n   232→              SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK.getVoyageNumber(),\n   233→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK.getUnLocode(),\n   234→              HandlingEvent.Type.UNLOAD);\n   235→      entityManager.persist(event3);\n   236→\n   237→      // The wrong voyage!\n   238→      HandlingEvent event4 =\n   239→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   240→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(18).minusMinutes(36),\n   241→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(2).minusHours(8).minusMinutes(7),\n   242→              trackingId2,\n   243→              SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK.getVoyageNumber(),\n   244→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK.getUnLocode(),\n   245→              HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD);\n   246→      entityManager.persist(event4);\n   247→    } catch (CannotCreateHandlingEventException e) {\n   248→      throw new RuntimeException(e);\n   249→    }\n   250→\n   251→    HandlingHistory handlingHistory2 =\n   252→        handlingEventRepository.lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(trackingId2);\n   253→    jkl567.deriveDeliveryProgress(handlingHistory2);\n   254→\n   255→    entityManager.persist(jkl567);\n   256→\n   257→    // Cargo definition DEF789. This one will remain un-routed.\n   258→    TrackingId trackingId3 = new TrackingId(\"DEF789\");\n   259→\n   260→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification3 =\n   261→        new RouteSpecification(\n   262→            SampleLocations.HONGKONG, SampleLocations.MELBOURNE, LocalDate.now().plusMonths(2));\n   263→\n   264→    Cargo def789 = new Cargo(trackingId3, routeSpecification3);\n   265→    entityManager.persist(def789);\n   266→\n   267→    // Cargo definition MNO456. This one will be claimed properly.\n   268→    TrackingId trackingId4 = new TrackingId(\"MNO456\");\n   269→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification4 =\n   270→        new RouteSpecification(\n   271→            SampleLocations.NEWYORK, SampleLocations.DALLAS, LocalDate.now().minusDays(24));\n   272→\n   273→    Cargo mno456 = new Cargo(trackingId4, routeSpecification4);\n   274→\n   275→    Itinerary itinerary4 =\n   276→        new Itinerary(\n   277→            Arrays.asList(\n   278→                new Leg(\n   279→                    SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS,\n   280→                    SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n   281→                    SampleLocations.DALLAS,\n   282→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(34).minusHours(1).minusMinutes(1),\n   283→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(28).minusHours(10).minusMinutes(1))));\n   284→\n   285→    mno456.assignToRoute(itinerary4);\n   286→    entityManager.persist(mno456);\n   287→\n   288→    try {\n   289→      HandlingEvent event1 =\n   290→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   291→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(16).minusMinutes(9),\n   292→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(37).minusHours(2).minusMinutes(21),\n   293→              trackingId4,\n   294→              null,\n   295→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK.getUnLocode(),\n   296→              HandlingEvent.Type.RECEIVE);\n   297→\n   298→      entityManager.persist(event1);\n   299→\n   300→      HandlingEvent event2 =\n   301→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   302→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(3).minusMinutes(9),\n   303→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(34).minusHours(3).minusMinutes(8),\n   304→              trackingId4,\n   305→              SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS.getVoyageNumber(),\n   306→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK.getUnLocode(),\n   307→              HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD);\n   308→\n   309→      entityManager.persist(event2);\n   310→\n   311→      HandlingEvent event3 =\n   312→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   313→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(14).minusMinutes(10),\n   314→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(28).minusHours(7).minusMinutes(7),\n   315→              trackingId4,\n   316→              SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS.getVoyageNumber(),\n   317→              SampleLocations.DALLAS.getUnLocode(),\n   318→              HandlingEvent.Type.UNLOAD);\n   319→\n   320→      entityManager.persist(event3);\n   321→\n   322→      HandlingEvent event4 =\n   323→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   324→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(22).minusMinutes(1),\n   325→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(27).minusHours(18).minusMinutes(3),\n   326→              trackingId4,\n   327→              null,\n   328→              SampleLocations.DALLAS.getUnLocode(),\n   329→              HandlingEvent.Type.CUSTOMS);\n   330→\n   331→      entityManager.persist(event4);\n   332→\n   333→      HandlingEvent event5 =\n   334→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   335→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(9).minusMinutes(30),\n   336→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(26).minusHours(14).minusMinutes(15),\n   337→              trackingId4,\n   338→              null,\n   339→              SampleLocations.DALLAS.getUnLocode(),\n   340→              HandlingEvent.Type.CLAIM);\n   341→\n   342→      entityManager.persist(event5);\n   343→\n   344→      HandlingHistory handlingHistory3 =\n   345→          handlingEventRepository.lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(trackingId4);\n   346→\n   347→      mno456.deriveDeliveryProgress(handlingHistory3);\n   348→\n   349→      entityManager.persist(mno456);\n   350→    } catch (CannotCreateHandlingEventException e) {\n   351→      throw new RuntimeException(e);\n   352→    }\n   353→  }\n   354→}\n   355→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"9a087214-95d0-43c1-ac95-4fefc3821094"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012PkbgQnLefqRh1J6iQ8SFo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.HashMap;\n     4→import java.util.Map;\n     5→import javax.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n     6→import javax.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     7→import org.glassfish.jersey.server.ServerProperties;\n     8→\n     9→/** Jakarta REST configuration. */\n    10→@ApplicationPath(\"rest\")\n    11→public class RestConfiguration extends Application {\n    12→\n    13→  @Override\n    14→  public Map<String, Object> getProperties() {\n    15→    Map<String, Object> properties = new HashMap<String, Object>();\n    16→    properties.put(ServerProperties.BV_SEND_ERROR_IN_RESPONSE, true);\n    17→    return properties;\n    18→  }\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"8a2a6115-152c-492f-9cb9-0ef9edd6a148"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KkbLNL7GUVWzGNLGetgoUP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.time.ZoneId;\n     6→import java.time.format.DateTimeFormatter;\n     7→\n     8→// TODO [Clean Code] Make this a CDI singleton?\n     9→public class DateConverter {\n    10→  public static final String DATE_FORMAT = \"M/d/yyyy\";\n    11→  public static final String DATE_TIME_FORMAT = \"M/d/yyyy h:m a\";\n    12→\n    13→  private static final DateTimeFormatter DATE_FORMATTER =\n    14→      DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern(DATE_FORMAT).withZone(ZoneId.systemDefault());\n    15→\n    16→  private static final DateTimeFormatter DATE_TIME_FORMATTER =\n    17→      DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern(DATE_TIME_FORMAT).withZone(ZoneId.systemDefault());\n    18→\n    19→  private DateConverter() {}\n    20→\n    21→  public static LocalDate toDate(String date) {\n    22→    return LocalDate.parse(date, DATE_FORMATTER);\n    23→  }\n    24→\n    25→  public static LocalDateTime toDateTime(String datetime) {\n    26→    return LocalDateTime.parse(datetime, DATE_TIME_FORMATTER);\n    27→  }\n    28→\n    29→  public static String toString(LocalDateTime dateTime) {\n    30→    return dateTime.format(DATE_TIME_FORMATTER);\n    31→  }\n    32→\n    33→  public static String toString(LocalDate date) {\n    34→    return date.format(DATE_FORMATTER);\n    35→  }\n    36→}\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"cdffe134-f3c9-4a5f-8883-dbe7126a4033"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KANrEMRhEurzp5Kmknqth5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n     5→import javax.persistence.Id;\n     6→\n     7→/**\n     8→ * Application settings. Although this is stored in the database, it is not a true part of the\n     9→ * domain model but simply an application infrastructure artifact.\n    10→ */\n    11→@Entity\n    12→public class ApplicationSettings implements Serializable {\n    13→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    14→\n    15→  @Id private Long id;\n    16→\n    17→  private boolean sampleLoaded = false;\n    18→\n    19→  public boolean isSampleLoaded() {\n    20→    return sampleLoaded;\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  public void setSampleLoaded(boolean sampleLoaded) {\n    24→    this.sampleLoaded = sampleLoaded;\n    25→  }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"c2e97311-fbf0-4afd-9e66-b7625f9e7cd2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019cSWvXcSDnYi2PxQhaQVS8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.internal;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→import javax.ejb.Stateless;\n     6→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.HandlingEventService;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.CannotCreateHandlingEventException;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventFactory;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventRepository;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    16→\n    17→@Stateless\n    18→public class DefaultHandlingEventService implements HandlingEventService {\n    19→\n    20→  @Inject private ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n    21→  @Inject private HandlingEventRepository handlingEventRepository;\n    22→  @Inject private HandlingEventFactory handlingEventFactory;\n    23→  @Inject private Logger logger;\n    24→\n    25→  @Override\n    26→  public void registerHandlingEvent(\n    27→      LocalDateTime completionTime,\n    28→      TrackingId trackingId,\n    29→      VoyageNumber voyageNumber,\n    30→      UnLocode unLocode,\n    31→      HandlingEvent.Type type)\n    32→      throws CannotCreateHandlingEventException {\n    33→    LocalDateTime registrationTime = LocalDateTime.now();\n    34→\n    35→    /*\n    36→     * Using a factory to create a HandlingEvent (aggregate). This is where it is\n    37→     * determined wether the incoming data, the attempt, actually is capable of\n    38→     * representing a real handling event.\n    39→     */\n    40→    HandlingEvent event =\n    41→        handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n    42→            registrationTime, completionTime, trackingId, voyageNumber, unLocode, type);\n    43→\n    44→    /*\n    45→     * Store the new handling event, which updates the persistent state of the\n    46→     * handling event aggregate (but not the cargo aggregate - that happens\n    47→     * asynchronously!)\n    48→     */\n    49→    handlingEventRepository.store(event);\n    50→\n    51→    /* Publish an event stating that a cargo has been handled. */\n    52→    applicationEvents.cargoWasHandled(event);\n    53→\n    54→    logger.info(\"Registered handling event\");\n    55→  }\n    56→}\n    57→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"19883c94-bfa7-46f1-bae0-97a825dee324"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HyECkPHZ37nymomEQD7emZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.internal;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→import javax.ejb.Stateless;\n     6→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.CargoInspectionService;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventRepository;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingHistory;\n    14→\n    15→@Stateless\n    16→public class DefaultCargoInspectionService implements CargoInspectionService {\n    17→\n    18→  @Inject private Logger logger;\n    19→  @Inject private ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n    20→  @Inject private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    21→  @Inject private HandlingEventRepository handlingEventRepository;\n    22→\n    23→  @Override\n    24→  public void inspectCargo(TrackingId trackingId) {\n    25→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    26→\n    27→    if (cargo == null) {\n    28→      logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"Can't inspect non-existing cargo {0}\", trackingId);\n    29→      return;\n    30→    }\n    31→\n    32→    HandlingHistory handlingHistory =\n    33→        handlingEventRepository.lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(trackingId);\n    34→\n    35→    cargo.deriveDeliveryProgress(handlingHistory);\n    36→\n    37→    if (cargo.getDelivery().isMisdirected()) {\n    38→      applicationEvents.cargoWasMisdirected(cargo);\n    39→    }\n    40→\n    41→    if (cargo.getDelivery().isUnloadedAtDestination()) {\n    42→      applicationEvents.cargoHasArrived(cargo);\n    43→    }\n    44→\n    45→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n    46→  }\n    47→}\n    48→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"aed1435a-0580-4da3-8d94-e8f857128a1f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XzebdBuEqL7nyvBnN6Q9n5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.internal;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.util.Collections;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     7→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     8→import javax.ejb.Stateless;\n     9→import javax.inject.Inject;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.BookingService;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    19→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.service.RoutingService;\n    20→\n    21→@Stateless\n    22→public class DefaultBookingService implements BookingService {\n    23→\n    24→  @Inject private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    25→  @Inject private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n    26→  @Inject private RoutingService routingService;\n    27→  @Inject private Logger logger;\n    28→\n    29→  @Override\n    30→  public TrackingId bookNewCargo(\n    31→      UnLocode originUnLocode, UnLocode destinationUnLocode, LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n    32→    TrackingId trackingId = cargoRepository.nextTrackingId();\n    33→    Location origin = locationRepository.find(originUnLocode);\n    34→    Location destination = locationRepository.find(destinationUnLocode);\n    35→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification =\n    36→        new RouteSpecification(origin, destination, arrivalDeadline);\n    37→\n    38→    Cargo cargo = new Cargo(trackingId, routeSpecification);\n    39→\n    40→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n    41→    logger.log(\n    42→        Level.INFO, \"Booked new cargo with tracking ID {0}\", cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString());\n    43→\n    44→    return cargo.getTrackingId();\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  @Override\n    48→  public List<Itinerary> requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(TrackingId trackingId) {\n    49→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    50→\n    51→    if (cargo == null) {\n    52→      return Collections.emptyList();\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    return routingService.fetchRoutesForSpecification(cargo.getRouteSpecification());\n    56→  }\n    57→\n    58→  @Override\n    59→  public void assignCargoToRoute(Itinerary itinerary, TrackingId trackingId) {\n    60→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    61→\n    62→    cargo.assignToRoute(itinerary);\n    63→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n    64→\n    65→    logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Assigned cargo {0} to new route\", trackingId);\n    66→  }\n    67→\n    68→  @Override\n    69→  public void changeDestination(TrackingId trackingId, UnLocode unLocode) {\n    70→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    71→    Location newDestination = locationRepository.find(unLocode);\n    72→\n    73→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification =\n    74→        new RouteSpecification(\n    75→            cargo.getOrigin(), newDestination, cargo.getRouteSpecification().getArrivalDeadline());\n    76→    cargo.specifyNewRoute(routeSpecification);\n    77→\n    78→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n    79→\n    80→    logger.log(\n    81→        Level.INFO,\n    82→        \"Changed destination for cargo {0} to {1}\",\n    83→        new Object[] {trackingId, routeSpecification.getDestination()});\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  @Override\n    87→  public void changeDeadline(TrackingId trackingId, LocalDate newDeadline) {\n    88→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    89→\n    90→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification =\n    91→        new RouteSpecification(\n    92→            cargo.getOrigin(), cargo.getRouteSpecification().getDestination(), newDeadline);\n    93→    cargo.specifyNewRoute(routeSpecification);\n    94→\n    95→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n    96→\n    97→    logger.log(\n    98→        Level.INFO,\n    99→        \"Changed deadline for cargo {0} to {1}\",\n   100→        new Object[] {trackingId, newDeadline});\n   101→  }\n   102→}\n   103→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"a863ada1-c35a-44c5-ac39-dcc5d37d341d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01M51FGtk7r4okiZ6GUdCYMX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import javax.persistence.Embedded;\n     5→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n     6→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n     7→import javax.persistence.Id;\n     8→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n     9→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    10→import javax.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    11→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    12→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingHistory;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared.DomainObjectUtils;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ * A Cargo. This is the central class in the domain model, and it is the root of the\n    20→ * Cargo-Itinerary-Leg-Delivery-RouteSpecification aggregate.\n    21→ *\n    22→ * <p>A cargo is identified by a unique tracking ID, and it always has an origin and a route\n    23→ * specification. The life cycle of a cargo begins with the booking procedure, when the tracking ID\n    24→ * is assigned. During a (short) period of time, between booking and initial routing, the cargo has\n    25→ * no itinerary.\n    26→ *\n    27→ * <p>The booking clerk requests a list of possible routes, matching the route specification, and\n    28→ * assigns the cargo to one route. The route to which a cargo is assigned is described by an\n    29→ * itinerary.\n    30→ *\n    31→ * <p>A cargo can be re-routed during transport, on demand of the customer, in which case a new\n    32→ * route is specified for the cargo and a new route is requested. The old itinerary, being a value\n    33→ * object, is discarded and a new one is attached.\n    34→ *\n    35→ * <p>It may also happen that a cargo is accidentally misrouted, which should notify the proper\n    36→ * personnel and also trigger a re-routing procedure.\n    37→ *\n    38→ * <p>When a cargo is handled, the status of the delivery changes. Everything about the delivery of\n    39→ * the cargo is contained in the Delivery value object, which is replaced whenever a cargo is\n    40→ * handled by an asynchronous event triggered by the registration of the handling event.\n    41→ *\n    42→ * <p>The delivery can also be affected by routing changes, i.e. when a the route specification\n    43→ * changes, or the cargo is assigned to a new route. In that case, the delivery update is performed\n    44→ * synchronously within the cargo aggregate.\n    45→ *\n    46→ * <p>The life cycle of a cargo ends when the cargo is claimed by the customer.\n    47→ *\n    48→ * <p>The cargo aggregate, and the entire domain model, is built to solve the problem of booking and\n    49→ * tracking cargo. All important business rules for determining whether or not a cargo is\n    50→ * misdirected, what the current status of the cargo is (on board carrier, in port etc), are\n    51→ * captured in this aggregate.\n    52→ */\n    53→@Entity\n    54→@NamedQuery(name = \"Cargo.findAll\", query = \"Select c from Cargo c\")\n    55→@NamedQuery(\n    56→    name = \"Cargo.findByTrackingId\",\n    57→    query = \"Select c from Cargo c where c.trackingId = :trackingId\")\n    58→public class Cargo implements Serializable {\n    59→\n    60→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    61→\n    62→  @Id @GeneratedValue private Long id;\n    63→\n    64→  @Embedded\n    65→  @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\")\n    66→  private TrackingId trackingId;\n    67→\n    68→  @ManyToOne\n    69→  @JoinColumn(name = \"origin_id\", updatable = false)\n    70→  @NotNull\n    71→  private Location origin;\n    72→\n    73→  @Embedded\n    74→  @NotNull(message = \"Route specification is required.\")\n    75→  private RouteSpecification routeSpecification;\n    76→\n    77→  @Embedded @NotNull private Itinerary itinerary;\n    78→  @Embedded @NotNull private Delivery delivery;\n    79→\n    80→  public Cargo() {\n    81→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    82→  }\n    83→\n    84→  public Cargo(TrackingId trackingId, RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n    85→    Validate.notNull(trackingId, \"Tracking ID is required.\");\n    86→    Validate.notNull(routeSpecification, \"Route specification is required.\");\n    87→\n    88→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    89→    // Cargo origin never changes, even if the route specification changes.\n    90→    // However, at creation, cargo origin can be derived from the initial\n    91→    // route specification.\n    92→    this.origin = routeSpecification.getOrigin();\n    93→    this.routeSpecification = routeSpecification;\n    94→\n    95→    this.delivery =\n    96→        Delivery.derivedFrom(this.routeSpecification, this.itinerary, HandlingHistory.EMPTY);\n    97→    this.itinerary = Itinerary.EMPTY_ITINERARY;\n    98→  }\n    99→\n   100→  public TrackingId getTrackingId() {\n   101→    return trackingId;\n   102→  }\n   103→\n   104→  public Location getOrigin() {\n   105→    return origin;\n   106→  }\n   107→\n   108→  public void setOrigin(Location origin) {\n   109→    this.origin = origin;\n   110→  }\n   111→\n   112→  public RouteSpecification getRouteSpecification() {\n   113→    return routeSpecification;\n   114→  }\n   115→\n   116→  /** @return The delivery. Never null. */\n   117→  public Delivery getDelivery() {\n   118→    return delivery;\n   119→  }\n   120→\n   121→  /** @return The itinerary. Never null. */\n   122→  public Itinerary getItinerary() {\n   123→    return DomainObjectUtils.nullSafe(this.itinerary, Itinerary.EMPTY_ITINERARY);\n   124→  }\n   125→\n   126→  /** Specifies a new route for this cargo. */\n   127→  public void specifyNewRoute(RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n   128→    Validate.notNull(routeSpecification, \"Route specification is required.\");\n   129→\n   130→    this.routeSpecification = routeSpecification;\n   131→    // Handling consistency within the Cargo aggregate synchronously\n   132→    this.delivery = delivery.updateOnRouting(this.routeSpecification, this.itinerary);\n   133→  }\n   134→\n   135→  public void assignToRoute(Itinerary itinerary) {\n   136→    Validate.notNull(itinerary, \"Itinerary is required for assignment.\");\n   137→\n   138→    this.itinerary = itinerary;\n   139→    // Handling consistency within the Cargo aggregate synchronously\n   140→    this.delivery = delivery.updateOnRouting(this.routeSpecification, this.itinerary);\n   141→  }\n   142→\n   143→  /**\n   144→   * Updates all aspects of the cargo aggregate status based on the current route specification,\n   145→   * itinerary and handling of the cargo.\n   146→   *\n   147→   * <p>When either of those three changes, i.e. when a new route is specified for the cargo, the\n   148→   * cargo is assigned to a route or when the cargo is handled, the status must be re-calculated.\n   149→   *\n   150→   * <p>{@link RouteSpecification} and {@link Itinerary} are both inside the Cargo aggregate, so\n   151→   * changes to them cause the status to be updated <b>synchronously</b>, but changes to the\n   152→   * delivery history (when a cargo is handled) cause the status update to happen\n   153→   * <b>asynchronously</b> since {@link HandlingEvent} is in a different aggregate.\n   154→   *\n   155→   * @param handlingHistory handling history\n   156→   */\n   157→  public void deriveDeliveryProgress(HandlingHistory handlingHistory) {\n   158→    this.delivery = Delivery.derivedFrom(getRouteSpecification(), getItinerary(), handlingHistory);\n   159→  }\n   160→\n   161→  /**\n   162→   * @param object to compare\n   163→   * @return True if they have the same identity\n   164→   * @see #sameIdentityAs(Cargo)\n   165→   */\n   166→  @Override\n   167→  public boolean equals(Object object) {\n   168→    if (this == object) {\n   169→      return true;\n   170→    }\n   171→    if (object == null || !(object instanceof Cargo)) {\n   172→      return false;\n   173→    }\n   174→\n   175→    Cargo other = (Cargo) object;\n   176→    return sameIdentityAs(other);\n   177→  }\n   178→\n   179→  private boolean sameIdentityAs(Cargo other) {\n   180→    return other != null && trackingId.sameValueAs(other.trackingId);\n   181→  }\n   182→\n   183→  /** @return Hash code of tracking id. */\n   184→  @Override\n   185→  public int hashCode() {\n   186→    return trackingId.hashCode();\n   187→  }\n   188→\n   189→  @Override\n   190→  public String toString() {\n   191→    return trackingId.toString();\n   192→  }\n   193→}\n   194→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"f0855b09-fc6e-46f9-9dbf-5558139e6c8e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013FmoVmQPUx29mot7fNoob6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→\n     5→public interface CargoRepository {\n     6→\n     7→  Cargo find(TrackingId trackingId);\n     8→\n     9→  List<Cargo> findAll();\n    10→\n    11→  void store(Cargo cargo);\n    12→\n    13→  TrackingId nextTrackingId();\n    14→}\n    15→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"0791236e-453a-4f9c-b001-838648e6ebee"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XbbsMb3fzZUBgenY52QuGJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import javax.persistence.Column;\n     5→import javax.persistence.Embeddable;\n     6→import javax.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n     7→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n     8→\n     9→/** Uniquely identifies a particular cargo. Automatically generated by the application. */\n    10→@Embeddable\n    11→public class TrackingId implements Serializable {\n    12→\n    13→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    14→\n    15→  @Column(name = \"tracking_id\", unique = true, updatable = false)\n    16→  @NotEmpty(message = \"Tracking ID cannot be empty.\")\n    17→  private String id;\n    18→\n    19→  public TrackingId() {}\n    20→\n    21→  public TrackingId(String id) {\n    22→    Validate.notNull(id);\n    23→    this.id = id;\n    24→  }\n    25→\n    26→  public String getIdString() {\n    27→    return id;\n    28→  }\n    29→\n    30→  @Override\n    31→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    32→    if (this == o) {\n    33→      return true;\n    34→    }\n    35→\n    36→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof TrackingId)) {\n    37→      return false;\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    TrackingId other = (TrackingId) o;\n    41→\n    42→    return sameValueAs(other);\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  @Override\n    46→  public int hashCode() {\n    47→    return id.hashCode();\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  boolean sameValueAs(TrackingId other) {\n    51→    return other != null && this.id.equals(other.id);\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  @Override\n    55→  public String toString() {\n    56→    return id;\n    57→  }\n    58→}\n    59→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"a62faa81-aa5d-434d-a2f0-ca08717cebff"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DrYxy25wXr6EXjhPKQgK38","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.util.Collections;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import javax.persistence.CascadeType;\n     8→import javax.persistence.Embeddable;\n     9→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    10→import javax.persistence.OneToMany;\n    11→import javax.persistence.OrderColumn;\n    12→import javax.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    13→import javax.validation.constraints.Size;\n    14→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    17→\n    18→@Embeddable\n    19→public class Itinerary implements Serializable {\n    20→\n    21→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    22→\n    23→  // Null object pattern.\n    24→  public static final Itinerary EMPTY_ITINERARY = new Itinerary();\n    25→\n    26→  // TODO [Clean Code] Look into why cascade delete doesn't work.\n    27→  @OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.ALL)\n    28→  @JoinColumn(name = \"cargo_id\")\n    29→  @OrderColumn(name = \"leg_order\")\n    30→  @Size(min = 1)\n    31→  @NotEmpty(message = \"Legs must not be empty.\")\n    32→  private List<Leg> legs = Collections.emptyList();\n    33→\n    34→  public Itinerary() {\n    35→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    36→  }\n    37→\n    38→  public Itinerary(List<Leg> legs) {\n    39→    Validate.notEmpty(legs);\n    40→    Validate.noNullElements(legs);\n    41→\n    42→    this.legs = legs;\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  public List<Leg> getLegs() {\n    46→    return Collections.unmodifiableList(legs);\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  /** Test if the given handling event is expected when executing this itinerary. */\n    50→  public boolean isExpected(HandlingEvent event) {\n    51→    if (legs.isEmpty()) {\n    52→      return true;\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    switch (event.getType()) {\n    56→      case RECEIVE:\n    57→        {\n    58→          // Check that the first leg's origin is the event's location\n    59→          Leg leg = legs.get(0);\n    60→          return leg.getLoadLocation().equals(event.getLocation());\n    61→        }\n    62→\n    63→      case LOAD:\n    64→        {\n    65→          return legs.stream()\n    66→              .anyMatch(\n    67→                  leg ->\n    68→                      leg.getLoadLocation().equals(event.getLocation())\n    69→                          && leg.getVoyage().equals(event.getVoyage()));\n    70→        }\n    71→\n    72→      case UNLOAD:\n    73→        {\n    74→          // Check that the there is one leg with same unload location and\n    75→          // voyage\n    76→          return legs.stream()\n    77→              .anyMatch(\n    78→                  leg ->\n    79→                      leg.getUnloadLocation().equals(event.getLocation())\n    80→                          && leg.getVoyage().equals(event.getVoyage()));\n    81→        }\n    82→\n    83→      case CLAIM:\n    84→        {\n    85→          // Check that the last leg's destination is from the event's\n    86→          // location\n    87→          Leg leg = getLastLeg();\n    88→\n    89→          return leg.getUnloadLocation().equals(event.getLocation());\n    90→        }\n    91→\n    92→      case CUSTOMS:\n    93→        {\n    94→          return true;\n    95→        }\n    96→\n    97→      default:\n    98→        throw new RuntimeException(\"Event case is not handled\");\n    99→    }\n   100→  }\n   101→\n   102→  Location getInitialDepartureLocation() {\n   103→    if (legs.isEmpty()) {\n   104→      return Location.UNKNOWN;\n   105→    } else {\n   106→      return legs.get(0).getLoadLocation();\n   107→    }\n   108→  }\n   109→\n   110→  Location getFinalArrivalLocation() {\n   111→    if (legs.isEmpty()) {\n   112→      return Location.UNKNOWN;\n   113→    } else {\n   114→      return getLastLeg().getUnloadLocation();\n   115→    }\n   116→  }\n   117→\n   118→  /** @return Date when cargo arrives at final destination. */\n   119→  LocalDateTime getFinalArrivalDate() {\n   120→    Leg lastLeg = getLastLeg();\n   121→\n   122→    if (lastLeg == null) {\n   123→      return LocalDateTime.MAX;\n   124→    } else {\n   125→      return lastLeg.getUnloadTime();\n   126→    }\n   127→  }\n   128→\n   129→  /** @return The last leg on the itinerary. */\n   130→  Leg getLastLeg() {\n   131→    if (legs.isEmpty()) {\n   132→      return null;\n   133→    } else {\n   134→      return legs.get(legs.size() - 1);\n   135→    }\n   136→  }\n   137→\n   138→  private boolean sameValueAs(Itinerary other) {\n   139→    return other != null && legs.equals(other.legs);\n   140→  }\n   141→\n   142→  @Override\n   143→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n   144→    if (this == o) {\n   145→      return true;\n   146→    }\n   147→\n   148→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof Itinerary)) {\n   149→      return false;\n   150→    }\n   151→\n   152→    Itinerary itinerary = (Itinerary) o;\n   153→\n   154→    return sameValueAs(itinerary);\n   155→  }\n   156→\n   157→  @Override\n   158→  public int hashCode() {\n   159→    return legs.hashCode();\n   160→  }\n   161→\n   162→  @Override\n   163→  public String toString() {\n   164→    return \"Itinerary{\" + \"legs=\" + legs + '}';\n   165→  }\n   166→}\n   167→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"ced86eed-9596-418f-addf-6090097284c5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011ZY9wZfuRmWE9zuYiMPssV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n     6→import javax.persistence.Column;\n     7→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n     8→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n     9→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    10→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    11→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    12→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    13→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    14→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.EqualsBuilder;\n    15→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    18→\n    19→@Entity\n    20→public class Leg implements Serializable {\n    21→\n    22→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    23→\n    24→  @Id @GeneratedValue private Long id;\n    25→\n    26→  @ManyToOne\n    27→  @JoinColumn(name = \"voyage_id\")\n    28→  @NotNull\n    29→  private Voyage voyage;\n    30→\n    31→  @ManyToOne\n    32→  @JoinColumn(name = \"load_location_id\")\n    33→  @NotNull\n    34→  private Location loadLocation;\n    35→\n    36→  @ManyToOne\n    37→  @JoinColumn(name = \"unload_location_id\")\n    38→  @NotNull\n    39→  private Location unloadLocation;\n    40→\n    41→  @Column(name = \"load_time\")\n    42→  @NotNull\n    43→  private LocalDateTime loadTime;\n    44→\n    45→  @Column(name = \"unload_time\")\n    46→  @NotNull\n    47→  private LocalDateTime unloadTime;\n    48→\n    49→  public Leg() {\n    50→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  public Leg(\n    54→      Voyage voyage,\n    55→      Location loadLocation,\n    56→      Location unloadLocation,\n    57→      LocalDateTime loadTime,\n    58→      LocalDateTime unloadTime) {\n    59→    Validate.noNullElements(\n    60→        new Object[] {voyage, loadLocation, unloadLocation, loadTime, unloadTime});\n    61→\n    62→    this.voyage = voyage;\n    63→    this.loadLocation = loadLocation;\n    64→    this.unloadLocation = unloadLocation;\n    65→\n    66→    // This is a workaround to a Hibernate issue. when the `LocalDateTime` field is persisted into\n    67→    // the DB, and retrieved from the DB, the values are different by nanoseconds.\n    68→    this.loadTime = loadTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n    69→    this.unloadTime = unloadTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n    70→  }\n    71→\n    72→  public Voyage getVoyage() {\n    73→    return voyage;\n    74→  }\n    75→\n    76→  public Location getLoadLocation() {\n    77→    return loadLocation;\n    78→  }\n    79→\n    80→  public Location getUnloadLocation() {\n    81→    return unloadLocation;\n    82→  }\n    83→\n    84→  public LocalDateTime getLoadTime() {\n    85→    return this.loadTime;\n    86→  }\n    87→\n    88→  public LocalDateTime getUnloadTime() {\n    89→    return this.unloadTime;\n    90→  }\n    91→\n    92→  private boolean sameValueAs(Leg other) {\n    93→    return other != null\n    94→        && new EqualsBuilder()\n    95→            .append(this.voyage, other.voyage)\n    96→            .append(this.loadLocation, other.loadLocation)\n    97→            .append(this.unloadLocation, other.unloadLocation)\n    98→            .append(this.loadTime, other.loadTime)\n    99→            .append(this.unloadTime, other.unloadTime)\n   100→            .isEquals();\n   101→  }\n   102→\n   103→  @Override\n   104→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n   105→    if (this == o) {\n   106→      return true;\n   107→    }\n   108→\n   109→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof Leg)) {\n   110→      return false;\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    Leg leg = (Leg) o;\n   114→\n   115→    return sameValueAs(leg);\n   116→  }\n   117→\n   118→  @Override\n   119→  public int hashCode() {\n   120→    return new HashCodeBuilder()\n   121→        .append(voyage)\n   122→        .append(loadLocation)\n   123→        .append(unloadLocation)\n   124→        .append(loadTime)\n   125→        .append(unloadTime)\n   126→        .toHashCode();\n   127→  }\n   128→\n   129→  @Override\n   130→  public String toString() {\n   131→    return \"Leg{\"\n   132→        + \"id=\"\n   133→        + id\n   134→        + \", voyage=\"\n   135→        + voyage\n   136→        + \", loadLocation=\"\n   137→        + loadLocation\n   138→        + \", unloadLocation=\"\n   139→        + unloadLocation\n   140→        + \", loadTime=\"\n   141→        + loadTime\n   142→        + \", unloadTime=\"\n   143→        + unloadTime\n   144→        + '}';\n   145→  }\n   146→}\n   147→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"a909851d-a45c-43d0-bfe2-1ac1a54bc79b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DUDfr8HaZKApx16Ny5tHxr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import javax.persistence.Column;\n     6→import javax.persistence.Embeddable;\n     7→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n     8→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n     9→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    10→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    11→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.EqualsBuilder;\n    12→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared.AbstractSpecification;\n    15→\n    16→/**\n    17→ * Route specification. Describes where a cargo origin and destination is, and the arrival deadline.\n    18→ */\n    19→@Embeddable\n    20→public class RouteSpecification extends AbstractSpecification<Itinerary> implements Serializable {\n    21→\n    22→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    23→\n    24→  @ManyToOne\n    25→  @JoinColumn(name = \"spec_origin_id\", updatable = false)\n    26→  private Location origin;\n    27→\n    28→  @ManyToOne\n    29→  @JoinColumn(name = \"spec_destination_id\")\n    30→  private Location destination;\n    31→\n    32→  @Column(name = \"spec_arrival_deadline\")\n    33→  @NotNull\n    34→  private LocalDate arrivalDeadline;\n    35→\n    36→  public RouteSpecification() {}\n    37→\n    38→  /**\n    39→   * @param origin origin location - can't be the same as the destination\n    40→   * @param destination destination location - can't be the same as the origin\n    41→   * @param arrivalDeadline arrival deadline\n    42→   */\n    43→  public RouteSpecification(Location origin, Location destination, LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n    44→    Validate.notNull(origin, \"Origin is required\");\n    45→    Validate.notNull(destination, \"Destination is required\");\n    46→    Validate.notNull(arrivalDeadline, \"Arrival deadline is required\");\n    47→    Validate.isTrue(\n    48→        !origin.sameIdentityAs(destination), \"Origin and destination can't be the same: \" + origin);\n    49→\n    50→    this.origin = origin;\n    51→    this.destination = destination;\n    52→    this.arrivalDeadline = arrivalDeadline;\n    53→  }\n    54→\n    55→  public Location getOrigin() {\n    56→    return origin;\n    57→  }\n    58→\n    59→  public Location getDestination() {\n    60→    return destination;\n    61→  }\n    62→\n    63→  public LocalDate getArrivalDeadline() {\n    64→    return arrivalDeadline;\n    65→  }\n    66→\n    67→  @Override\n    68→  public boolean isSatisfiedBy(Itinerary itinerary) {\n    69→    return itinerary != null\n    70→        && getOrigin().sameIdentityAs(itinerary.getInitialDepartureLocation())\n    71→        && getDestination().sameIdentityAs(itinerary.getFinalArrivalLocation())\n    72→        && getArrivalDeadline().isAfter(itinerary.getFinalArrivalDate().toLocalDate());\n    73→  }\n    74→\n    75→  private boolean sameValueAs(RouteSpecification other) {\n    76→    return other != null\n    77→        && new EqualsBuilder()\n    78→            .append(this.origin, other.origin)\n    79→            .append(this.destination, other.destination)\n    80→            .append(this.arrivalDeadline, other.arrivalDeadline)\n    81→            .isEquals();\n    82→  }\n    83→\n    84→  @Override\n    85→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    86→    if (this == o) {\n    87→      return true;\n    88→    }\n    89→\n    90→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof RouteSpecification)) {\n    91→      return false;\n    92→    }\n    93→\n    94→    RouteSpecification that = (RouteSpecification) o;\n    95→\n    96→    return sameValueAs(that);\n    97→  }\n    98→\n    99→  @Override\n   100→  public int hashCode() {\n   101→    return new HashCodeBuilder()\n   102→        .append(this.origin)\n   103→        .append(this.destination)\n   104→        .append(this.arrivalDeadline)\n   105→        .toHashCode();\n   106→  }\n   107→}\n   108→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"1cc9a69a-f841-4dad-9a69-1381b96cb6f4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014vMP1YTrDBzyv1teWsBJPv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RoutingStatus.MISROUTED;\n     4→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RoutingStatus.NOT_ROUTED;\n     5→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RoutingStatus.ROUTED;\n     6→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus.CLAIMED;\n     7→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus.IN_PORT;\n     8→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus.NOT_RECEIVED;\n     9→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus.ONBOARD_CARRIER;\n    10→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus.UNKNOWN;\n    11→\n    12→import java.io.Serializable;\n    13→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n    14→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n    15→import java.util.Iterator;\n    16→import javax.persistence.Column;\n    17→import javax.persistence.Embeddable;\n    18→import javax.persistence.Embedded;\n    19→import javax.persistence.EnumType;\n    20→import javax.persistence.Enumerated;\n    21→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    22→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    23→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    24→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    25→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.EqualsBuilder;\n    26→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    27→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    28→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingHistory;\n    29→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    30→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    31→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared.DomainObjectUtils;\n    32→\n    33→/**\n    34→ * The actual transportation of the cargo, as opposed to the customer requirement\n    35→ * (RouteSpecification) and the plan (Itinerary).\n    36→ */\n    37→@Embeddable\n    38→public class Delivery implements Serializable {\n    39→\n    40→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    41→\n    42→  // Null object pattern.\n    43→  public static final LocalDateTime ETA_UNKOWN = null;\n    44→  public static final HandlingActivity NO_ACTIVITY = new HandlingActivity();\n    45→\n    46→  @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)\n    47→  @Column(name = \"transport_status\")\n    48→  @NotNull\n    49→  private TransportStatus transportStatus;\n    50→\n    51→  @ManyToOne\n    52→  @JoinColumn(name = \"last_known_location_id\")\n    53→  private Location lastKnownLocation;\n    54→\n    55→  @ManyToOne\n    56→  @JoinColumn(name = \"current_voyage_id\")\n    57→  private Voyage currentVoyage;\n    58→\n    59→  @NotNull private boolean misdirected;\n    60→\n    61→  private LocalDateTime eta;\n    62→\n    63→  @Embedded private HandlingActivity nextExpectedActivity;\n    64→\n    65→  @Column(name = \"unloaded_at_dest\")\n    66→  @NotNull\n    67→  private boolean isUnloadedAtDestination;\n    68→\n    69→  @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)\n    70→  @Column(name = \"routing_status\")\n    71→  @NotNull\n    72→  private RoutingStatus routingStatus;\n    73→\n    74→  @Column(name = \"calculated_at\")\n    75→  @NotNull\n    76→  private LocalDateTime calculatedAt;\n    77→\n    78→  @ManyToOne\n    79→  @JoinColumn(name = \"last_event_id\")\n    80→  private HandlingEvent lastEvent;\n    81→\n    82→  public Delivery() {\n    83→    // Nothing to initialize\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  public Delivery(\n    87→      HandlingEvent lastEvent, Itinerary itinerary, RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n    88→    // This is a workaround to a Hibernate issue. when the `LocalDateTime` field is persisted into\n    89→    // the DB, and retrieved from the DB, the values are different by nanoseconds.\n    90→    this.calculatedAt = LocalDateTime.now().truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n    91→    this.lastEvent = lastEvent;\n    92→\n    93→    this.misdirected = calculateMisdirectionStatus(itinerary);\n    94→    this.routingStatus = calculateRoutingStatus(itinerary, routeSpecification);\n    95→    this.transportStatus = calculateTransportStatus();\n    96→    this.lastKnownLocation = calculateLastKnownLocation();\n    97→    this.currentVoyage = calculateCurrentVoyage();\n    98→    this.eta = calculateEta(itinerary);\n    99→    this.nextExpectedActivity = calculateNextExpectedActivity(routeSpecification, itinerary);\n   100→    this.isUnloadedAtDestination = calculateUnloadedAtDestination(routeSpecification);\n   101→  }\n   102→\n   103→  /**\n   104→   * Creates a new delivery snapshot based on the complete handling history of a cargo, as well as\n   105→   * its route specification and itinerary.\n   106→   *\n   107→   * @param routeSpecification route specification\n   108→   * @param itinerary itinerary\n   109→   * @param handlingHistory delivery history\n   110→   * @return An up to date delivery.\n   111→   */\n   112→  static Delivery derivedFrom(\n   113→      RouteSpecification routeSpecification, Itinerary itinerary, HandlingHistory handlingHistory) {\n   114→    Validate.notNull(routeSpecification, \"Route specification is required\");\n   115→    Validate.notNull(handlingHistory, \"Delivery history is required\");\n   116→\n   117→    HandlingEvent lastEvent = handlingHistory.getMostRecentlyCompletedEvent();\n   118→\n   119→    return new Delivery(lastEvent, itinerary, routeSpecification);\n   120→  }\n   121→\n   122→  /**\n   123→   * Creates a new delivery snapshot to reflect changes in routing, i.e. when the route\n   124→   * specification or the itinerary has changed but no additional handling of the cargo has been\n   125→   * performed.\n   126→   */\n   127→  Delivery updateOnRouting(RouteSpecification routeSpecification, Itinerary itinerary) {\n   128→    Validate.notNull(routeSpecification, \"Route specification is required\");\n   129→\n   130→    return new Delivery(this.lastEvent, itinerary, routeSpecification);\n   131→  }\n   132→\n   133→  public TransportStatus getTransportStatus() {\n   134→    return transportStatus;\n   135→  }\n   136→\n   137→  public void setTransportStatus(TransportStatus transportStatus) {\n   138→    this.transportStatus = transportStatus;\n   139→  }\n   140→\n   141→  public Location getLastKnownLocation() {\n   142→    return DomainObjectUtils.nullSafe(lastKnownLocation, Location.UNKNOWN);\n   143→  }\n   144→\n   145→  public void setLastKnownLocation(Location lastKnownLocation) {\n   146→    this.lastKnownLocation = lastKnownLocation;\n   147→  }\n   148→\n   149→  public void setLastEvent(HandlingEvent lastEvent) {\n   150→    this.lastEvent = lastEvent;\n   151→  }\n   152→\n   153→  public Voyage getCurrentVoyage() {\n   154→    return DomainObjectUtils.nullSafe(currentVoyage, Voyage.NONE);\n   155→  }\n   156→\n   157→  /**\n   158→   * Check if cargo is misdirected.\n   159→   *\n   160→   * <p>\n   161→   *\n   162→   * <ul>\n   163→   *   <li>A cargo is misdirected if it is in a location that's not in the itinerary.\n   164→   *   <li>A cargo with no itinerary can not be misdirected.\n   165→   *   <li>A cargo that has received no handling events can not be misdirected.\n   166→   * </ul>\n   167→   *\n   168→   * @return <code>true</code> if the cargo has been misdirected,\n   169→   */\n   170→  public boolean isMisdirected() {\n   171→    return misdirected;\n   172→  }\n   173→\n   174→  public void setMisdirected(boolean misdirected) {\n   175→    this.misdirected = misdirected;\n   176→  }\n   177→\n   178→  public LocalDateTime getEstimatedTimeOfArrival() {\n   179→    return eta;\n   180→  }\n   181→\n   182→  public HandlingActivity getNextExpectedActivity() {\n   183→    return nextExpectedActivity;\n   184→  }\n   185→\n   186→  /** @return True if the cargo has been unloaded at the final destination. */\n   187→  public boolean isUnloadedAtDestination() {\n   188→    return isUnloadedAtDestination;\n   189→  }\n   190→\n   191→  public void setUnloadedAtDestination(boolean isUnloadedAtDestination) {\n   192→    this.isUnloadedAtDestination = isUnloadedAtDestination;\n   193→  }\n   194→\n   195→  public RoutingStatus getRoutingStatus() {\n   196→    return routingStatus;\n   197→  }\n   198→\n   199→  public void setRoutingStatus(RoutingStatus routingStatus) {\n   200→    this.routingStatus = routingStatus;\n   201→  }\n   202→\n   203→  public LocalDateTime getCalculatedAt() {\n   204→    return calculatedAt;\n   205→  }\n   206→\n   207→  public void setCalculatedAt(LocalDateTime calculatedAt) {\n   208→    this.calculatedAt = calculatedAt;\n   209→  }\n   210→\n   211→  private TransportStatus calculateTransportStatus() {\n   212→    if (lastEvent == null) {\n   213→      return NOT_RECEIVED;\n   214→    }\n   215→\n   216→    switch (lastEvent.getType()) {\n   217→      case LOAD:\n   218→        return ONBOARD_CARRIER;\n   219→      case UNLOAD:\n   220→      case RECEIVE:\n   221→      case CUSTOMS:\n   222→        return IN_PORT;\n   223→      case CLAIM:\n   224→        return CLAIMED;\n   225→      default:\n   226→        return UNKNOWN;\n   227→    }\n   228→  }\n   229→\n   230→  private Location calculateLastKnownLocation() {\n   231→    if (lastEvent != null) {\n   232→      return lastEvent.getLocation();\n   233→    } else {\n   234→      return null;\n   235→    }\n   236→  }\n   237→\n   238→  private Voyage calculateCurrentVoyage() {\n   239→    if (getTransportStatus().equals(ONBOARD_CARRIER) && lastEvent != null) {\n   240→      return lastEvent.getVoyage();\n   241→    } else {\n   242→      return null;\n   243→    }\n   244→  }\n   245→\n   246→  private boolean calculateMisdirectionStatus(Itinerary itinerary) {\n   247→    if (lastEvent == null) {\n   248→      return false;\n   249→    } else {\n   250→      return !itinerary.isExpected(lastEvent);\n   251→    }\n   252→  }\n   253→\n   254→  private LocalDateTime calculateEta(Itinerary itinerary) {\n   255→    if (onTrack()) {\n   256→      // This is a workaround to a Hibernate issue. when the `LocalDateTime` field is persisted into\n   257→      // the DB, and retrieved from the DB, the values are different by nanoseconds.\n   258→      return itinerary.getFinalArrivalDate().truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n   259→    } else {\n   260→      return ETA_UNKOWN;\n   261→    }\n   262→  }\n   263→\n   264→  private HandlingActivity calculateNextExpectedActivity(\n   265→      RouteSpecification routeSpecification, Itinerary itinerary) {\n   266→    if (!onTrack()) {\n   267→      return NO_ACTIVITY;\n   268→    }\n   269→\n   270→    if (lastEvent == null) {\n   271→      return new HandlingActivity(HandlingEvent.Type.RECEIVE, routeSpecification.getOrigin());\n   272→    }\n   273→\n   274→    switch (lastEvent.getType()) {\n   275→      case LOAD:\n   276→        for (Leg leg : itinerary.getLegs()) {\n   277→          if (leg.getLoadLocation().sameIdentityAs(lastEvent.getLocation())) {\n   278→            return new HandlingActivity(\n   279→                HandlingEvent.Type.UNLOAD, leg.getUnloadLocation(), leg.getVoyage());\n   280→          }\n   281→        }\n   282→\n   283→        return NO_ACTIVITY;\n   284→\n   285→      case UNLOAD:\n   286→        for (Iterator<Leg> iterator = itinerary.getLegs().iterator(); iterator.hasNext(); ) {\n   287→          Leg leg = iterator.next();\n   288→\n   289→          if (leg.getUnloadLocation().sameIdentityAs(lastEvent.getLocation())) {\n   290→            if (iterator.hasNext()) {\n   291→              Leg nextLeg = iterator.next();\n   292→              return new HandlingActivity(\n   293→                  HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD, nextLeg.getLoadLocation(), nextLeg.getVoyage());\n   294→            } else {\n   295→              return new HandlingActivity(HandlingEvent.Type.CLAIM, leg.getUnloadLocation());\n   296→            }\n   297→          }\n   298→        }\n   299→\n   300→        return NO_ACTIVITY;\n   301→\n   302→      case RECEIVE:\n   303→        Leg firstLeg = itinerary.getLegs().iterator().next();\n   304→\n   305→        return new HandlingActivity(\n   306→            HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD, firstLeg.getLoadLocation(), firstLeg.getVoyage());\n   307→\n   308→      case CLAIM:\n   309→      default:\n   310→        return NO_ACTIVITY;\n   311→    }\n   312→  }\n   313→\n   314→  private RoutingStatus calculateRoutingStatus(\n   315→      Itinerary itinerary, RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n   316→    if (itinerary == null || itinerary == Itinerary.EMPTY_ITINERARY) {\n   317→      return NOT_ROUTED;\n   318→    } else {\n   319→      if (routeSpecification.isSatisfiedBy(itinerary)) {\n   320→        return ROUTED;\n   321→      } else {\n   322→        return MISROUTED;\n   323→      }\n   324→    }\n   325→  }\n   326→\n   327→  private boolean calculateUnloadedAtDestination(RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n   328→    return lastEvent != null\n   329→        && HandlingEvent.Type.UNLOAD.sameValueAs(lastEvent.getType())\n   330→        && routeSpecification.getDestination().sameIdentityAs(lastEvent.getLocation());\n   331→  }\n   332→\n   333→  private boolean onTrack() {\n   334→    return routingStatus.equals(ROUTED) && !misdirected;\n   335→  }\n   336→\n   337→  private boolean sameValueAs(Delivery other) {\n   338→    return other != null\n   339→        && new EqualsBuilder()\n   340→            .append(this.transportStatus, other.transportStatus)\n   341→            .append(this.lastKnownLocation, other.lastKnownLocation)\n   342→            .append(this.currentVoyage, other.currentVoyage)\n   343→            .append(this.misdirected, other.misdirected)\n   344→            .append(this.eta, other.eta)\n   345→            .append(this.nextExpectedActivity, other.nextExpectedActivity)\n   346→            .append(this.isUnloadedAtDestination, other.isUnloadedAtDestination)\n   347→            .append(this.routingStatus, other.routingStatus)\n   348→            .append(this.calculatedAt, other.calculatedAt)\n   349→            .append(this.lastEvent, other.lastEvent)\n   350→            .isEquals();\n   351→  }\n   352→\n   353→  @Override\n   354→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n   355→    if (this == o) {\n   356→      return true;\n   357→    }\n   358→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof Delivery)) {\n   359→      return false;\n   360→    }\n   361→\n   362→    Delivery other = (Delivery) o;\n   363→\n   364→    return sameValueAs(other);\n   365→  }\n   366→\n   367→  @Override\n   368→  public int hashCode() {\n   369→    return new HashCodeBuilder()\n   370→        .append(transportStatus)\n   371→        .append(lastKnownLocation)\n   372→        .append(currentVoyage)\n   373→        .append(misdirected)\n   374→        .append(eta)\n   375→        .append(nextExpectedActivity)\n   376→        .append(isUnloadedAtDestination)\n   377→        .append(routingStatus)\n   378→        .append(calculatedAt)\n   379→        .append(lastEvent)\n   380→        .toHashCode();\n   381→  }\n   382→}\n   383→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"dc026334-6b1d-4ac1-977f-748f540f471a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HfXzicwaKjdSHsUix4HiZk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import javax.persistence.Column;\n     5→import javax.persistence.Embeddable;\n     6→import javax.persistence.EnumType;\n     7→import javax.persistence.Enumerated;\n     8→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n     9→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    10→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    11→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    12→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.EqualsBuilder;\n    13→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ * A handling activity represents how and where a cargo can be handled, and can be used to express\n    20→ * predictions about what is expected to happen to a cargo in the future.\n    21→ */\n    22→@Embeddable\n    23→public class HandlingActivity implements Serializable {\n    24→\n    25→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    26→\n    27→  @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)\n    28→  @Column(name = \"next_expected_handling_event_type\")\n    29→  @NotNull(message = \"Handling event type is required.\")\n    30→  private HandlingEvent.Type type;\n    31→\n    32→  @ManyToOne\n    33→  @JoinColumn(name = \"next_expected_location_id\")\n    34→  @NotNull(message = \"Location is required.\")\n    35→  private Location location;\n    36→\n    37→  @ManyToOne\n    38→  @JoinColumn(name = \"next_expected_voyage_id\")\n    39→  private Voyage voyage;\n    40→\n    41→  public HandlingActivity() {}\n    42→\n    43→  public HandlingActivity(HandlingEvent.Type type, Location location) {\n    44→    Validate.notNull(type, \"Handling event type is required.\");\n    45→    Validate.notNull(location, \"Location is required.\");\n    46→\n    47→    this.type = type;\n    48→    this.location = location;\n    49→  }\n    50→\n    51→  public HandlingActivity(HandlingEvent.Type type, Location location, Voyage voyage) {\n    52→    Validate.notNull(type, \"Handling event type is required\");\n    53→    Validate.notNull(location, \"Location is required\");\n    54→    Validate.notNull(voyage, \"Voyage is required\");\n    55→\n    56→    this.type = type;\n    57→    this.location = location;\n    58→    this.voyage = voyage;\n    59→  }\n    60→\n    61→  public HandlingEvent.Type getType() {\n    62→    return type;\n    63→  }\n    64→\n    65→  public Location getLocation() {\n    66→    return location;\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  public Voyage getVoyage() {\n    70→    return voyage;\n    71→  }\n    72→\n    73→  private boolean sameValueAs(HandlingActivity other) {\n    74→    return other != null\n    75→        && new EqualsBuilder()\n    76→            .append(this.type, other.type)\n    77→            .append(this.location, other.location)\n    78→            .append(this.voyage, other.voyage)\n    79→            .isEquals();\n    80→  }\n    81→\n    82→  @Override\n    83→  public int hashCode() {\n    84→    return new HashCodeBuilder()\n    85→        .append(this.type)\n    86→        .append(this.location)\n    87→        .append(this.voyage)\n    88→        .toHashCode();\n    89→  }\n    90→\n    91→  @Override\n    92→  public boolean equals(Object obj) {\n    93→    if (obj == this) {\n    94→      return true;\n    95→    }\n    96→\n    97→    if (obj == null) {\n    98→      return false;\n    99→    }\n   100→\n   101→    if (!(obj instanceof HandlingActivity)) {\n   102→      return false;\n   103→    }\n   104→\n   105→    HandlingActivity other = (HandlingActivity) obj;\n   106→\n   107→    return sameValueAs(other);\n   108→  }\n   109→\n   110→  public boolean isEmpty() {\n   111→    if (type != null) {\n   112→      return false;\n   113→    }\n   114→\n   115→    if (location != null) {\n   116→      return false;\n   117→    }\n   118→\n   119→    return voyage == null;\n   120→  }\n   121→}\n   122→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"c1ce9046-cc32-4560-99ae-0bc1eda24d1b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01X7qkgmnjqEbRKULmbq1CW6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→public enum TransportStatus {\n     4→  NOT_RECEIVED,\n     5→  IN_PORT,\n     6→  ONBOARD_CARRIER,\n     7→  CLAIMED,\n     8→  UNKNOWN;\n     9→\n    10→  public boolean sameValueAs(TransportStatus other) {\n    11→    return this.equals(other);\n    12→  }\n    13→}\n    14→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KusfuiUjQzgrLeAj9EAZUj","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"450df423-75aa-440c-9b06-6034647a4e37"}
