{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01H9tHK1MwnWGVV2UxEwQd69","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n     6→import javax.persistence.Column;\n     7→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n     8→import javax.persistence.EnumType;\n     9→import javax.persistence.Enumerated;\n    10→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n    11→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    12→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    13→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    14→import javax.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    15→import javax.persistence.Transient;\n    16→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    17→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    18→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.EqualsBuilder;\n    19→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    20→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    22→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    23→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    24→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared.DomainObjectUtils;\n    25→\n    26→/**\n    27→ * A HandlingEvent is used to register the event when, for instance, a cargo is unloaded from a\n    28→ * carrier at a some location at a given time.\n    29→ *\n    30→ * <p>The HandlingEvent's are sent from different Incident Logging Applications some time after the\n    31→ * event occurred and contain information about the null {@link TrackingId}, {@link Location}, time\n    32→ * stamp of the completion of the event, and possibly, if applicable a {@link Voyage}.\n    33→ *\n    34→ * <p>This class is the only member, and consequently the root, of the HandlingEvent aggregate.\n    35→ *\n    36→ * <p>HandlingEvent's could contain information about a {@link Voyage} and if so, the event type\n    37→ * must be either {@link Type#LOAD} or {@link Type#UNLOAD}.\n    38→ *\n    39→ * <p>All other events must be of {@link Type#RECEIVE}, {@link Type#CLAIM} or {@link Type#CUSTOMS}.\n    40→ */\n    41→@Entity\n    42→@NamedQuery(\n    43→    name = \"HandlingEvent.findByTrackingId\",\n    44→    query = \"Select e from HandlingEvent e where e.cargo.trackingId = :trackingId\")\n    45→public class HandlingEvent implements Serializable {\n    46→\n    47→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    48→\n    49→  @Id @GeneratedValue private Long id;\n    50→\n    51→  @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)\n    52→  @NotNull\n    53→  private Type type;\n    54→\n    55→  @ManyToOne\n    56→  @JoinColumn(name = \"voyage_id\")\n    57→  private Voyage voyage;\n    58→\n    59→  @ManyToOne\n    60→  @JoinColumn(name = \"location_id\")\n    61→  @NotNull\n    62→  private Location location;\n    63→\n    64→  @NotNull\n    65→  @Column(name = \"completionTime\")\n    66→  private LocalDateTime completionTime;\n    67→\n    68→  @NotNull\n    69→  @Column(name = \"registration\")\n    70→  private LocalDateTime registrationTime;\n    71→\n    72→  @ManyToOne\n    73→  @JoinColumn(name = \"cargo_id\")\n    74→  @NotNull\n    75→  private Cargo cargo;\n    76→\n    77→  @Transient private String summary;\n    78→\n    79→  public HandlingEvent() {\n    80→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    81→  }\n    82→\n    83→  /**\n    84→   * @param cargo The cargo\n    85→   * @param completionTime completion time, the reported time that the event actually happened (e.g.\n    86→   *     the receive took place).\n    87→   * @param registrationTime registration time, the time the message is received\n    88→   * @param type type of event\n    89→   * @param location where the event took place\n    90→   * @param voyage the voyage\n    91→   */\n    92→  public HandlingEvent(\n    93→      Cargo cargo,\n    94→      LocalDateTime completionTime,\n    95→      LocalDateTime registrationTime,\n    96→      Type type,\n    97→      Location location,\n    98→      Voyage voyage) {\n    99→    Validate.notNull(cargo, \"Cargo is required\");\n   100→    Validate.notNull(completionTime, \"Completion time is required\");\n   101→    Validate.notNull(registrationTime, \"Registration time is required\");\n   102→    Validate.notNull(type, \"Handling event type is required\");\n   103→    Validate.notNull(location, \"Location is required\");\n   104→    Validate.notNull(voyage, \"Voyage is required\");\n   105→\n   106→    if (type.prohibitsVoyage()) {\n   107→      throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Voyage is not allowed with event type \" + type);\n   108→    }\n   109→\n   110→    this.voyage = voyage;\n   111→\n   112→    // This is a workaround to a Hibernate issue. when the `LocalDateTime` field is persisted into\n   113→    // the DB, and retrieved from the DB, the values are different by nanoseconds.\n   114→    this.completionTime = completionTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n   115→    this.registrationTime = registrationTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n   116→    this.type = type;\n   117→    this.location = location;\n   118→    this.cargo = cargo;\n   119→  }\n   120→\n   121→  /**\n   122→   * @param cargo cargo\n   123→   * @param completionTime completion time, the reported time that the event actually happened (e.g.\n   124→   *     the receive took place).\n   125→   * @param registrationTime registration time, the time the message is received\n   126→   * @param type type of event\n   127→   * @param location where the event took place\n   128→   */\n   129→  public HandlingEvent(\n   130→      Cargo cargo,\n   131→      LocalDateTime completionTime,\n   132→      LocalDateTime registrationTime,\n   133→      Type type,\n   134→      Location location) {\n   135→    Validate.notNull(cargo, \"Cargo is required\");\n   136→    Validate.notNull(completionTime, \"Completion time is required\");\n   137→    Validate.notNull(registrationTime, \"Registration time is required\");\n   138→    Validate.notNull(type, \"Handling event type is required\");\n   139→    Validate.notNull(location, \"Location is required\");\n   140→\n   141→    if (type.requiresVoyage()) {\n   142→      throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Voyage is required for event type \" + type);\n   143→    }\n   144→\n   145→    // This is a workaround to a Hibernate issue. when the `LocalDateTime` field is persisted into\n   146→    // the DB, and retrieved from the DB, the values are different by nanoseconds.\n   147→    this.completionTime = completionTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n   148→    this.registrationTime = registrationTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n   149→    this.type = type;\n   150→    this.location = location;\n   151→    this.cargo = cargo;\n   152→    this.voyage = null;\n   153→  }\n   154→\n   155→  public Type getType() {\n   156→    return this.type;\n   157→  }\n   158→\n   159→  public Voyage getVoyage() {\n   160→    return DomainObjectUtils.nullSafe(this.voyage, Voyage.NONE);\n   161→  }\n   162→\n   163→  public LocalDateTime getCompletionTime() {\n   164→    return completionTime;\n   165→  }\n   166→\n   167→  public LocalDateTime getRegistrationTime() {\n   168→    return registrationTime;\n   169→  }\n   170→\n   171→  public Location getLocation() {\n   172→    return this.location;\n   173→  }\n   174→\n   175→  public Cargo getCargo() {\n   176→    return this.cargo;\n   177→  }\n   178→\n   179→  public String getSummary() {\n   180→    StringBuilder builder =\n   181→        new StringBuilder(location.getName())\n   182→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   183→            .append(completionTime)\n   184→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   185→            .append(\"Type: \")\n   186→            .append(type)\n   187→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   188→            .append(\"Reg.: \")\n   189→            .append(registrationTime)\n   190→            .append(\"\\n\");\n   191→\n   192→    if (voyage != null) {\n   193→      builder.append(\"Voyage: \").append(voyage.getVoyageNumber());\n   194→    }\n   195→\n   196→    return builder.toString();\n   197→  }\n   198→\n   199→  @Override\n   200→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n   201→    if (this == o) {\n   202→      return true;\n   203→    }\n   204→\n   205→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof HandlingEvent)) {\n   206→      return false;\n   207→    }\n   208→\n   209→    HandlingEvent event = (HandlingEvent) o;\n   210→\n   211→    return sameEventAs(event);\n   212→  }\n   213→\n   214→  private boolean sameEventAs(HandlingEvent other) {\n   215→    return other != null\n   216→        && new EqualsBuilder()\n   217→            .append(this.cargo, other.cargo)\n   218→            .append(this.voyage, other.voyage)\n   219→            .append(this.completionTime, other.completionTime)\n   220→            .append(this.location, other.location)\n   221→            .append(this.type, other.type)\n   222→            .isEquals();\n   223→  }\n   224→\n   225→  @Override\n   226→  public int hashCode() {\n   227→    return new HashCodeBuilder()\n   228→        .append(cargo)\n   229→        .append(voyage)\n   230→        .append(completionTime)\n   231→        .append(location)\n   232→        .append(type)\n   233→        .toHashCode();\n   234→  }\n   235→\n   236→  @Override\n   237→  public String toString() {\n   238→    StringBuilder builder =\n   239→        new StringBuilder(\"\\n--- Handling event ---\\n\")\n   240→            .append(\"Cargo: \")\n   241→            .append(cargo.getTrackingId())\n   242→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   243→            .append(\"Type: \")\n   244→            .append(type)\n   245→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   246→            .append(\"Location: \")\n   247→            .append(location.getName())\n   248→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   249→            .append(\"Completed on: \")\n   250→            .append(completionTime)\n   251→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   252→            .append(\"Registered on: \")\n   253→            .append(registrationTime)\n   254→            .append(\"\\n\");\n   255→\n   256→    if (voyage != null) {\n   257→      builder.append(\"Voyage: \").append(voyage.getVoyageNumber()).append(\"\\n\");\n   258→    }\n   259→\n   260→    return builder.toString();\n   261→  }\n   262→\n   263→  /**\n   264→   * Handling event type. Either requires or prohibits a carrier movement association, it's never\n   265→   * optional.\n   266→   */\n   267→  public enum Type {\n   268→\n   269→    // Loaded onto voyage from port location.\n   270→    LOAD(true),\n   271→    // Unloaded from voyage to port location\n   272→    UNLOAD(true),\n   273→    // Received by carrier\n   274→    RECEIVE(false),\n   275→    // Cargo claimed by recepient\n   276→    CLAIM(false),\n   277→    // Cargo went through customs\n   278→    CUSTOMS(false);\n   279→\n   280→    private final boolean voyageRequired;\n   281→\n   282→    /**\n   283→     * Private enum constructor.\n   284→     *\n   285→     * @param voyageRequired whether or not a voyage is associated with this event type\n   286→     */\n   287→    private Type(boolean voyageRequired) {\n   288→      this.voyageRequired = voyageRequired;\n   289→    }\n   290→\n   291→    /** @return True if a voyage association is required for this event type. */\n   292→    public boolean requiresVoyage() {\n   293→      return voyageRequired;\n   294→    }\n   295→\n   296→    /** @return True if a voyage association is prohibited for this event type. */\n   297→    public boolean prohibitsVoyage() {\n   298→      return !requiresVoyage();\n   299→    }\n   300→\n   301→    public boolean sameValueAs(Type other) {\n   302→      return other != null && this.equals(other);\n   303→    }\n   304→  }\n   305→}\n   306→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"de27c608-309c-4997-99c0-245ba7fd1d14"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015orR5EGMemZ6C4g1dKuEu7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     4→import java.util.Collection;\n     5→import java.util.Collections;\n     6→import java.util.Comparator;\n     7→import java.util.HashSet;\n     8→import java.util.List;\n     9→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    10→\n    11→public class HandlingHistory {\n    12→\n    13→  // Null object pattern.\n    14→  public static final HandlingHistory EMPTY =\n    15→      new HandlingHistory(Collections.<HandlingEvent>emptyList());\n    16→  private static final Comparator<HandlingEvent> BY_COMPLETION_TIME_COMPARATOR =\n    17→      Comparator.comparing(HandlingEvent::getCompletionTime);\n    18→\n    19→  private final List<HandlingEvent> handlingEvents;\n    20→\n    21→  public HandlingHistory(Collection<HandlingEvent> handlingEvents) {\n    22→    Validate.notNull(handlingEvents, \"Handling events are required.\");\n    23→\n    24→    this.handlingEvents = new ArrayList<>(handlingEvents);\n    25→  }\n    26→\n    27→  public List<HandlingEvent> getAllHandlingEvents() {\n    28→    return handlingEvents;\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  /**\n    32→   * @return A distinct list (no duplicate registrations) of handling events, ordered by completion\n    33→   *     time.\n    34→   */\n    35→  public List<HandlingEvent> getDistinctEventsByCompletionTime() {\n    36→    List<HandlingEvent> ordered = new ArrayList<>(new HashSet<>(handlingEvents));\n    37→    ordered.sort(BY_COMPLETION_TIME_COMPARATOR);\n    38→\n    39→    return Collections.unmodifiableList(ordered);\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  /** @return Most recently completed event, or null if the delivery history is empty. */\n    43→  public HandlingEvent getMostRecentlyCompletedEvent() {\n    44→    List<HandlingEvent> distinctEvents = getDistinctEventsByCompletionTime();\n    45→\n    46→    if (distinctEvents.isEmpty()) {\n    47→      return null;\n    48→    } else {\n    49→      return distinctEvents.get(distinctEvents.size() - 1);\n    50→    }\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  private boolean sameValueAs(HandlingHistory other) {\n    54→    return other != null && this.handlingEvents.equals(other.handlingEvents);\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  @Override\n    58→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    59→    if (this == o) {\n    60→      return true;\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof HandlingHistory)) {\n    64→      return false;\n    65→    }\n    66→\n    67→    HandlingHistory other = (HandlingHistory) o;\n    68→\n    69→    return sameValueAs(other);\n    70→  }\n    71→\n    72→  @Override\n    73→  public int hashCode() {\n    74→    return handlingEvents.hashCode();\n    75→  }\n    76→}\n    77→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"fa306433-588d-4642-9516-ae991a33c8ef"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QSF48bqSss84CQsQr679a6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling;\n     2→\n     3→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n     4→\n     5→public interface HandlingEventRepository {\n     6→\n     7→  void store(HandlingEvent event);\n     8→\n     9→  HandlingHistory lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(TrackingId trackingId);\n    10→}\n    11→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"4d283301-783d-44f2-ac1e-5d4aa2dc3851"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RgT2zVpb6XUW965HQeuo7c","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import javax.inject.Inject;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\n    16→\n    17→@ApplicationScoped\n    18→public class HandlingEventFactory implements Serializable {\n    19→\n    20→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    21→\n    22→  @Inject private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    23→  @Inject private VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n    24→  @Inject private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n    25→\n    26→  /**\n    27→   * @param registrationTime time when this event was received by the system\n    28→   * @param completionTime when the event was completed, for example finished loading\n    29→   * @param trackingId cargo tracking id\n    30→   * @param voyageNumber voyage number\n    31→   * @param unlocode United Nations Location Code for the location of the event\n    32→   * @param type type of event\n    33→   * @return A handling event.\n    34→   * @throws UnknownVoyageException if there's no voyage with this number\n    35→   * @throws UnknownCargoException if there's no cargo with this tracking id\n    36→   * @throws UnknownLocationException if there's no location with this UN Locode\n    37→   */\n    38→  // TODO [Clean Code] Look at the exception handling more seriously.\n    39→  public HandlingEvent createHandlingEvent(\n    40→      LocalDateTime registrationTime,\n    41→      LocalDateTime completionTime,\n    42→      TrackingId trackingId,\n    43→      VoyageNumber voyageNumber,\n    44→      UnLocode unlocode,\n    45→      HandlingEvent.Type type)\n    46→      throws CannotCreateHandlingEventException {\n    47→    Cargo cargo = findCargo(trackingId);\n    48→    Voyage voyage = findVoyage(voyageNumber);\n    49→    Location location = findLocation(unlocode);\n    50→\n    51→    try {\n    52→      if (voyage == null) {\n    53→        return new HandlingEvent(cargo, completionTime, registrationTime, type, location);\n    54→      } else {\n    55→        return new HandlingEvent(cargo, completionTime, registrationTime, type, location, voyage);\n    56→      }\n    57→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    58→      throw new CannotCreateHandlingEventException(e);\n    59→    }\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  private Cargo findCargo(TrackingId trackingId) throws UnknownCargoException {\n    63→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    64→\n    65→    if (cargo == null) {\n    66→      throw new UnknownCargoException(trackingId);\n    67→    }\n    68→\n    69→    return cargo;\n    70→  }\n    71→\n    72→  private Voyage findVoyage(VoyageNumber voyageNumber) throws UnknownVoyageException {\n    73→    if (voyageNumber == null) {\n    74→      return null;\n    75→    }\n    76→\n    77→    Voyage voyage = voyageRepository.find(voyageNumber);\n    78→\n    79→    if (voyage == null) {\n    80→      throw new UnknownVoyageException(voyageNumber);\n    81→    }\n    82→\n    83→    return voyage;\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  private Location findLocation(UnLocode unlocode) throws UnknownLocationException {\n    87→    Location location = locationRepository.find(unlocode);\n    88→\n    89→    if (location == null) {\n    90→      throw new UnknownLocationException(unlocode);\n    91→    }\n    92→\n    93→    return location;\n    94→  }\n    95→}\n    96→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"7306b8f8-9ead-4ae2-b14c-ce53a5819aee"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019kKGjtHNz3yYgD9vTtvLpP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling;\n     2→\n     3→import javax.ejb.ApplicationException;\n     4→\n     5→/**\n     6→ * If a {@link HandlingEvent} can't be created from a given set of parameters.\n     7→ *\n     8→ * <p>It is a checked exception because it's not a programming error, but rather a special case that\n     9→ * the application is built to handle. It can occur during normal program execution.\n    10→ */\n    11→@ApplicationException(rollback = true)\n    12→public class CannotCreateHandlingEventException extends Exception {\n    13→\n    14→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    15→\n    16→  public CannotCreateHandlingEventException(Exception e) {\n    17→    super(e);\n    18→  }\n    19→\n    20→  public CannotCreateHandlingEventException() {\n    21→    super();\n    22→  }\n    23→}\n    24→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"55177726-183b-40c0-bb09-89a0ce9f877f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016BnLvj48KbWAshN9gHMJBB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling;\n     2→\n     3→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n     4→\n     5→/** Thrown when trying to register an event with an unknown carrier movement id. */\n     6→public class UnknownVoyageException extends CannotCreateHandlingEventException {\n     7→\n     8→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n     9→\n    10→  private final VoyageNumber voyageNumber;\n    11→\n    12→  public UnknownVoyageException(VoyageNumber voyageNumber) {\n    13→    this.voyageNumber = voyageNumber;\n    14→  }\n    15→\n    16→  @Override\n    17→  public String getMessage() {\n    18→    return \"No voyage with number \" + voyageNumber.getIdString() + \" exists in the system.\";\n    19→  }\n    20→}\n    21→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"135f1b44-2280-4321-8275-3faf06b3d190"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011TWThZHyWUManfxjzdjYnM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling;\n     2→\n     3→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n     4→\n     5→/** Thrown when trying to register an event with an unknown tracking id. */\n     6→public class UnknownCargoException extends CannotCreateHandlingEventException {\n     7→\n     8→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n     9→\n    10→  private final TrackingId trackingId;\n    11→\n    12→  /** @param trackingId cargo tracking id */\n    13→  public UnknownCargoException(TrackingId trackingId) {\n    14→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    15→  }\n    16→\n    17→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    18→  @Override\n    19→  public String getMessage() {\n    20→    return \"No cargo with tracking id \" + trackingId.getIdString() + \" exists in the system.\";\n    21→  }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"ab6fd1b9-6175-4197-8e9d-7b2842317c76"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01F36H7fmYGLC8ZfRTUUJ1j2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling;\n     2→\n     3→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n     4→\n     5→public class UnknownLocationException extends CannotCreateHandlingEventException {\n     6→\n     7→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n     8→\n     9→  private final UnLocode unlocode;\n    10→\n    11→  public UnknownLocationException(UnLocode unlocode) {\n    12→    this.unlocode = unlocode;\n    13→  }\n    14→\n    15→  @Override\n    16→  public String getMessage() {\n    17→    return \"No location with UN locode \" + unlocode.getIdString() + \" exists in the system.\";\n    18→  }\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"534e79f9-d7e2-4a24-ba18-0e64a969385b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012Jq7LcoWuY1pwag842A2Co","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import javax.persistence.Embedded;\n     8→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n     9→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n    10→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    11→import javax.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    12→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    13→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    15→\n    16→@Entity\n    17→@NamedQuery(\n    18→    name = \"Voyage.findByVoyageNumber\",\n    19→    query = \"Select v from Voyage v where v.voyageNumber = :voyageNumber\")\n    20→@NamedQuery(name = \"Voyage.findAll\", query = \"Select v from Voyage v order by v.voyageNumber\")\n    21→public class Voyage implements Serializable {\n    22→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    23→\n    24→  // Null object pattern\n    25→  public static final Voyage NONE = new Voyage(new VoyageNumber(\"\"), Schedule.EMPTY);\n    26→\n    27→  @Id @GeneratedValue private Long id;\n    28→\n    29→  @Embedded\n    30→  @NotNull(message = \"Voyage number is required.\")\n    31→  private VoyageNumber voyageNumber;\n    32→\n    33→  @Embedded\n    34→  @NotNull(message = \"Schedule is required.\")\n    35→  private Schedule schedule;\n    36→\n    37→  public Voyage() {\n    38→    // Nothing to initialize\n    39→  }\n    40→\n    41→  public Voyage(VoyageNumber voyageNumber, Schedule schedule) {\n    42→    Validate.notNull(voyageNumber, \"Voyage number is required.\");\n    43→    Validate.notNull(schedule, \"Schedule is required.\");\n    44→\n    45→    this.voyageNumber = voyageNumber;\n    46→    this.schedule = schedule;\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  public VoyageNumber getVoyageNumber() {\n    50→    return voyageNumber;\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  public Schedule getSchedule() {\n    54→    return schedule;\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  @Override\n    58→  public int hashCode() {\n    59→    return voyageNumber.hashCode();\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  @Override\n    63→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    64→    if (this == o) {\n    65→      return true;\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→    if (o == null) {\n    69→      return false;\n    70→    }\n    71→\n    72→    if (!(o instanceof Voyage)) {\n    73→      return false;\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    Voyage that = (Voyage) o;\n    77→\n    78→    return sameIdentityAs(that);\n    79→  }\n    80→\n    81→  public boolean sameIdentityAs(Voyage other) {\n    82→    return other != null && this.getVoyageNumber().sameValueAs(other.getVoyageNumber());\n    83→  }\n    84→\n    85→  @Override\n    86→  public String toString() {\n    87→    return \"Voyage \" + voyageNumber;\n    88→  }\n    89→\n    90→  /**\n    91→   * Builder pattern is used for incremental construction of a Voyage aggregate. This serves as an\n    92→   * aggregate factory.\n    93→   */\n    94→  public static class Builder {\n    95→\n    96→    private List<CarrierMovement> carrierMovements = new ArrayList<>();\n    97→    private VoyageNumber voyageNumber;\n    98→    private Location departureLocation;\n    99→\n   100→    public Builder(VoyageNumber voyageNumber, Location departureLocation) {\n   101→      Validate.notNull(voyageNumber, \"Voyage number is required\");\n   102→      Validate.notNull(departureLocation, \"Departure location is required\");\n   103→\n   104→      this.voyageNumber = voyageNumber;\n   105→      this.departureLocation = departureLocation;\n   106→    }\n   107→\n   108→    public Builder addMovement(\n   109→        Location arrivalLocation, LocalDateTime departureTime, LocalDateTime arrivalTime) {\n   110→      carrierMovements.add(\n   111→          new CarrierMovement(departureLocation, arrivalLocation, departureTime, arrivalTime));\n   112→\n   113→      // Next departure location is the same as this arrival location\n   114→      this.departureLocation = arrivalLocation;\n   115→\n   116→      return this;\n   117→    }\n   118→\n   119→    public Voyage build() {\n   120→      return new Voyage(voyageNumber, new Schedule(carrierMovements));\n   121→    }\n   122→  }\n   123→}\n   124→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"69ec68ec-f303-445f-90b5-4e7e6195ae20"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Y8K9FWHXDSYVspoM5W4ZSw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import javax.persistence.Column;\n     5→import javax.persistence.Embeddable;\n     6→import javax.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n     7→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n     8→\n     9→@Embeddable\n    10→public class VoyageNumber implements Serializable {\n    11→\n    12→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    13→\n    14→  @Column(name = \"voyage_number\")\n    15→  @NotEmpty(message = \"Voyage number cannot be empty.\")\n    16→  private String number;\n    17→\n    18→  public VoyageNumber() {\n    19→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    20→  }\n    21→\n    22→  public VoyageNumber(String number) {\n    23→    Validate.notNull(number);\n    24→\n    25→    this.number = number;\n    26→  }\n    27→\n    28→  @Override\n    29→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    30→    if (this == o) {\n    31→      return true;\n    32→    }\n    33→\n    34→    if (o == null) {\n    35→      return false;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    if (!(o instanceof VoyageNumber)) {\n    39→      return false;\n    40→    }\n    41→\n    42→    VoyageNumber other = (VoyageNumber) o;\n    43→\n    44→    return sameValueAs(other);\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  @Override\n    48→  public int hashCode() {\n    49→    return number.hashCode();\n    50→  }\n    51→\n    52→  boolean sameValueAs(VoyageNumber other) {\n    53→    return other != null && this.number.equals(other.number);\n    54→  }\n    55→\n    56→  @Override\n    57→  public String toString() {\n    58→    return number;\n    59→  }\n    60→\n    61→  public String getIdString() {\n    62→    return number;\n    63→  }\n    64→}\n    65→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"b9fe712a-a2c7-4207-a716-b57c024f62f9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QyRCJMeiEeFRDS6REDxWBQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→\n     5→public interface VoyageRepository {\n     6→\n     7→  Voyage find(VoyageNumber voyageNumber);\n     8→\n     9→  List<Voyage> findAll();\n    10→}\n    11→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"a5f3ad9a-5a4c-41d6-99a1-756f9fe29ec5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MnxHuPDEPUDS6PS2qs1WXG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.Collections;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import javax.persistence.CascadeType;\n     7→import javax.persistence.Embeddable;\n     8→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n     9→import javax.persistence.OneToMany;\n    10→import javax.persistence.OrderColumn;\n    11→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    12→import javax.validation.constraints.Size;\n    13→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    14→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    15→\n    16→/** A voyage schedule. */\n    17→@Embeddable\n    18→public class Schedule implements Serializable {\n    19→\n    20→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    21→\n    22→  // Null object pattern.\n    23→  public static final Schedule EMPTY = new Schedule();\n    24→\n    25→  // TODO [Clean Code] Look into why cascade delete doesn't work.\n    26→  @OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.ALL)\n    27→  @JoinColumn(name = \"voyage_id\")\n    28→  @OrderColumn(name = \"movement_order\")\n    29→  @NotNull\n    30→  @Size(min = 1)\n    31→  private List<CarrierMovement> carrierMovements = Collections.emptyList();\n    32→\n    33→  public Schedule() {\n    34→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    35→  }\n    36→\n    37→  Schedule(List<CarrierMovement> carrierMovements) {\n    38→    Validate.notNull(carrierMovements);\n    39→    Validate.noNullElements(carrierMovements);\n    40→    Validate.notEmpty(carrierMovements);\n    41→\n    42→    this.carrierMovements = carrierMovements;\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  public List<CarrierMovement> getCarrierMovements() {\n    46→    return Collections.unmodifiableList(carrierMovements);\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  private boolean sameValueAs(Schedule other) {\n    50→    return other != null && this.carrierMovements.equals(other.carrierMovements);\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  @Override\n    54→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    55→    if (this == o) {\n    56→      return true;\n    57→    }\n    58→\n    59→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof Schedule)) {\n    60→      return false;\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    Schedule that = (Schedule) o;\n    64→\n    65→    return sameValueAs(that);\n    66→  }\n    67→\n    68→  @Override\n    69→  public int hashCode() {\n    70→    return new HashCodeBuilder().append(this.carrierMovements).toHashCode();\n    71→  }\n    72→}\n    73→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"4955a0ef-7823-48da-beff-9ed095e0ad9f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017qGH6HhYGPjbgZ7NiopCu6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n     6→import javax.persistence.Column;\n     7→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n     8→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n     9→import javax.persistence.Id;\n    10→import javax.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    11→import javax.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    12→import javax.persistence.Table;\n    13→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    14→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    15→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.EqualsBuilder;\n    16→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    18→\n    19→/** A carrier movement is a vessel voyage from one location to another. */\n    20→@Entity\n    21→@Table(name = \"carrier_movement\")\n    22→public class CarrierMovement implements Serializable {\n    23→\n    24→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    25→\n    26→  // Null object pattern\n    27→  public static final CarrierMovement NONE =\n    28→      new CarrierMovement(Location.UNKNOWN, Location.UNKNOWN, LocalDateTime.MIN, LocalDateTime.MIN);\n    29→\n    30→  @Id @GeneratedValue private Long id;\n    31→\n    32→  @ManyToOne\n    33→  @JoinColumn(name = \"departure_location_id\")\n    34→  @NotNull\n    35→  private Location departureLocation;\n    36→\n    37→  @ManyToOne\n    38→  @JoinColumn(name = \"arrival_location_id\")\n    39→  @NotNull\n    40→  private Location arrivalLocation;\n    41→\n    42→  @Column(name = \"departure_time\")\n    43→  @NotNull\n    44→  private LocalDateTime departureTime;\n    45→\n    46→  @Column(name = \"arrival_time\")\n    47→  @NotNull\n    48→  private LocalDateTime arrivalTime;\n    49→\n    50→  public CarrierMovement() {\n    51→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  public CarrierMovement(\n    55→      Location departureLocation,\n    56→      Location arrivalLocation,\n    57→      LocalDateTime departureTime,\n    58→      LocalDateTime arrivalTime) {\n    59→    Validate.noNullElements(\n    60→        new Object[] {departureLocation, arrivalLocation, departureTime, arrivalTime});\n    61→\n    62→    // This is a workaround to a Hibernate issue. when the `LocalDateTime` field is persisted into\n    63→    // the DB, and retrieved from the DB, the values are different by nanoseconds.\n    64→    this.departureTime = departureTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n    65→    this.arrivalTime = arrivalTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n    66→    this.departureLocation = departureLocation;\n    67→    this.arrivalLocation = arrivalLocation;\n    68→  }\n    69→\n    70→  public Location getDepartureLocation() {\n    71→    return departureLocation;\n    72→  }\n    73→\n    74→  public Location getArrivalLocation() {\n    75→    return arrivalLocation;\n    76→  }\n    77→\n    78→  public LocalDateTime getDepartureTime() {\n    79→    return departureTime;\n    80→  }\n    81→\n    82→  public LocalDateTime getArrivalTime() {\n    83→    return arrivalTime;\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  @Override\n    87→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    88→    if (this == o) {\n    89→      return true;\n    90→    }\n    91→\n    92→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof CarrierMovement)) {\n    93→      return false;\n    94→    }\n    95→\n    96→    CarrierMovement that = (CarrierMovement) o;\n    97→\n    98→    return sameValueAs(that);\n    99→  }\n   100→\n   101→  @Override\n   102→  public int hashCode() {\n   103→    return new HashCodeBuilder()\n   104→        .append(this.departureLocation)\n   105→        .append(this.departureTime)\n   106→        .append(this.arrivalLocation)\n   107→        .append(this.arrivalTime)\n   108→        .toHashCode();\n   109→  }\n   110→\n   111→  private boolean sameValueAs(CarrierMovement other) {\n   112→    return other != null\n   113→        && new EqualsBuilder()\n   114→            .append(this.departureLocation, other.departureLocation)\n   115→            .append(this.departureTime, other.departureTime)\n   116→            .append(this.arrivalLocation, other.arrivalLocation)\n   117→            .append(this.arrivalTime, other.arrivalTime)\n   118→            .isEquals();\n   119→  }\n   120→}\n   121→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"41b70af0-4a24-45c6-a2d6-70a725616104"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MqdmZFSS3goVseNLPiRVtF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage;\n     2→\n     3→import java.lang.reflect.Field;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.Collections;\n     7→import java.util.HashMap;\n     8→import java.util.List;\n     9→import java.util.Map;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations;\n    12→\n    13→/** Sample carrier movements, for demo/test purposes. */\n    14→public class SampleVoyages {\n    15→\n    16→  public static final Voyage CM001 =\n    17→      createVoyage(\"CM001\", SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM, SampleLocations.HAMBURG);\n    18→  public static final Voyage CM002 =\n    19→      createVoyage(\"CM002\", SampleLocations.HAMBURG, SampleLocations.HONGKONG);\n    20→  public static final Voyage CM003 =\n    21→      createVoyage(\"CM003\", SampleLocations.HONGKONG, SampleLocations.NEWYORK);\n    22→  public static final Voyage CM004 =\n    23→      createVoyage(\"CM004\", SampleLocations.NEWYORK, SampleLocations.CHICAGO);\n    24→  public static final Voyage CM005 =\n    25→      createVoyage(\"CM005\", SampleLocations.CHICAGO, SampleLocations.HAMBURG);\n    26→  public static final Voyage CM006 =\n    27→      createVoyage(\"CM006\", SampleLocations.HAMBURG, SampleLocations.HANGZOU);\n    28→  public static final Voyage v100 =\n    29→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"V100\"), SampleLocations.HONGKONG)\n    30→          .addMovement(\n    31→              SampleLocations.TOKYO,\n    32→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(3).plusHours(6),\n    33→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(5).plusHours(18))\n    34→          .addMovement(\n    35→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n    36→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(6).plusHours(11),\n    37→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(9).plusHours(11))\n    38→          .build();\n    39→  public static final Voyage v200 =\n    40→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"V200\"), SampleLocations.TOKYO)\n    41→          .addMovement(\n    42→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n    43→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(6).plusHours(14),\n    44→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(8).plusHours(7))\n    45→          .addMovement(\n    46→              SampleLocations.CHICAGO,\n    47→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(10).plusHours(21),\n    48→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(14).plusHours(2))\n    49→          .addMovement(\n    50→              SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM,\n    51→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(14).plusHours(1),\n    52→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(16).plusHours(23))\n    53→          .build();\n    54→  public static final Voyage v300 =\n    55→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"V300\"), SampleLocations.TOKYO)\n    56→          .addMovement(\n    57→              SampleLocations.ROTTERDAM,\n    58→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(8).plusHours(8),\n    59→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(11).plusHours(16))\n    60→          .addMovement(\n    61→              SampleLocations.HAMBURG,\n    62→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(11).plusHours(4),\n    63→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(12).plusHours(17))\n    64→          .addMovement(\n    65→              SampleLocations.MELBOURNE,\n    66→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(14).plusHours(9),\n    67→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(18).plusHours(10))\n    68→          .addMovement(\n    69→              SampleLocations.TOKYO,\n    70→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(19).plusHours(17),\n    71→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(21).plusHours(4))\n    72→          .build();\n    73→  public static final Voyage v400 =\n    74→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"V400\"), SampleLocations.HAMBURG)\n    75→          .addMovement(\n    76→              SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM,\n    77→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(14).plusHours(9),\n    78→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(15).plusHours(18))\n    79→          .addMovement(\n    80→              SampleLocations.HELSINKI,\n    81→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(15).plusHours(11),\n    82→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(16).plusHours(16))\n    83→          .addMovement(\n    84→              SampleLocations.HAMBURG,\n    85→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(20).plusHours(18),\n    86→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(3).plusDays(22).plusHours(9))\n    87→          .build();\n    88→  /**\n    89→   * Voyage number 0100S (by ship)\n    90→   *\n    91→   * <p>Hongkong - Hangzou - Tokyo - Melbourne - New York\n    92→   */\n    93→  public static final Voyage HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK =\n    94→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"0100S\"), SampleLocations.HONGKONG)\n    95→          .addMovement(\n    96→              SampleLocations.HANGZOU,\n    97→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(10).plusDays(1).plusHours(12),\n    98→              LocalDateTime.now()\n    99→                  .minusYears(1)\n   100→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   101→                  .plusDays(3)\n   102→                  .plusHours(14)\n   103→                  .plusMinutes(30))\n   104→          .addMovement(\n   105→              SampleLocations.TOKYO,\n   106→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(10).plusDays(4).plusHours(21),\n   107→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   108→                  .minusYears(1)\n   109→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   110→                  .plusDays(6)\n   111→                  .plusHours(6)\n   112→                  .plusMinutes(15))\n   113→          .addMovement(\n   114→              SampleLocations.MELBOURNE,\n   115→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(10).plusDays(9).plusHours(11),\n   116→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   117→                  .minusYears(1)\n   118→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   119→                  .plusDays(12)\n   120→                  .plusHours(11)\n   121→                  .plusMinutes(30))\n   122→          .addMovement(\n   123→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n   124→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(10).plusDays(14).plusHours(12),\n   125→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   126→                  .minusYears(1)\n   127→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   128→                  .plusDays(23)\n   129→                  .plusHours(23)\n   130→                  .plusMinutes(10))\n   131→          .build();\n   132→  /**\n   133→   * Voyage number 0200T (by train)\n   134→   *\n   135→   * <p>New York - Chicago - Dallas\n   136→   */\n   137→  public static final Voyage NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS =\n   138→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"0200T\"), SampleLocations.NEWYORK)\n   139→          .addMovement(\n   140→              SampleLocations.CHICAGO,\n   141→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(10).plusDays(24).plusHours(7),\n   142→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   143→                  .minusYears(1)\n   144→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   145→                  .plusDays(24)\n   146→                  .plusHours(17)\n   147→                  .plusMinutes(45))\n   148→          .addMovement(\n   149→              SampleLocations.DALLAS,\n   150→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   151→                  .minusYears(1)\n   152→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   153→                  .plusDays(24)\n   154→                  .plusHours(21)\n   155→                  .plusMinutes(25),\n   156→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   157→                  .minusYears(1)\n   158→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   159→                  .plusDays(25)\n   160→                  .plusHours(19)\n   161→                  .plusMinutes(30))\n   162→          .build();\n   163→  /**\n   164→   * Voyage number 0300A (by airplane)\n   165→   *\n   166→   * <p>Dallas - Hamburg - Stockholm - Helsinki\n   167→   */\n   168→  public static final Voyage DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI =\n   169→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"0300A\"), SampleLocations.DALLAS)\n   170→          .addMovement(\n   171→              SampleLocations.HAMBURG,\n   172→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   173→                  .minusYears(1)\n   174→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   175→                  .plusDays(29)\n   176→                  .plusHours(3)\n   177→                  .plusMinutes(30),\n   178→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(10).plusDays(31).plusHours(14))\n   179→          .addMovement(\n   180→              SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM,\n   181→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   182→                  .minusYears(1)\n   183→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   184→                  .plusDays(1)\n   185→                  .plusHours(15)\n   186→                  .plusMinutes(20),\n   187→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   188→                  .minusYears(1)\n   189→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   190→                  .plusDays(1)\n   191→                  .plusHours(18)\n   192→                  .plusMinutes(40))\n   193→          .addMovement(\n   194→              SampleLocations.HELSINKI,\n   195→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(11).plusDays(2).plusHours(9),\n   196→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   197→                  .minusYears(1)\n   198→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   199→                  .plusDays(2)\n   200→                  .plusHours(11)\n   201→                  .plusMinutes(15))\n   202→          .build();\n   203→  /**\n   204→   * Voyage number 0301S (by ship)\n   205→   *\n   206→   * <p>Dallas - Hamburg - Stockholm - Helsinki, alternate route\n   207→   */\n   208→  public static final Voyage DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI_ALT =\n   209→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"0301S\"), SampleLocations.DALLAS)\n   210→          .addMovement(\n   211→              SampleLocations.HELSINKI,\n   212→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   213→                  .minusYears(1)\n   214→                  .plusMonths(10)\n   215→                  .plusDays(29)\n   216→                  .plusHours(3)\n   217→                  .plusMinutes(30),\n   218→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   219→                  .minusYears(1)\n   220→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   221→                  .plusDays(5)\n   222→                  .plusHours(15)\n   223→                  .plusMinutes(45))\n   224→          .build();\n   225→  /**\n   226→   * Voyage number 0400S (by ship)\n   227→   *\n   228→   * <p>Helsinki - Rotterdam - Shanghai - Hongkong\n   229→   */\n   230→  public static final Voyage HELSINKI_TO_HONGKONG =\n   231→      new Voyage.Builder(new VoyageNumber(\"0400S\"), SampleLocations.HELSINKI)\n   232→          .addMovement(\n   233→              SampleLocations.ROTTERDAM,\n   234→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   235→                  .minusYears(1)\n   236→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   237→                  .plusDays(4)\n   238→                  .plusHours(5)\n   239→                  .plusMinutes(50),\n   240→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   241→                  .minusYears(1)\n   242→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   243→                  .plusDays(6)\n   244→                  .plusHours(14)\n   245→                  .plusMinutes(10))\n   246→          .addMovement(\n   247→              SampleLocations.SHANGHAI,\n   248→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   249→                  .minusYears(1)\n   250→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   251→                  .plusDays(10)\n   252→                  .plusHours(21)\n   253→                  .plusMinutes(45),\n   254→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   255→                  .minusYears(1)\n   256→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   257→                  .plusDays(22)\n   258→                  .plusHours(16)\n   259→                  .plusMinutes(40))\n   260→          .addMovement(\n   261→              SampleLocations.HONGKONG,\n   262→              LocalDateTime.now().minusYears(1).plusMonths(11).plusDays(24).plusHours(7),\n   263→              LocalDateTime.now()\n   264→                  .minusYears(1)\n   265→                  .plusMonths(11)\n   266→                  .plusDays(28)\n   267→                  .plusHours(13)\n   268→                  .plusMinutes(37))\n   269→          .build();\n   270→\n   271→  public static final Map<VoyageNumber, Voyage> ALL = new HashMap<>();\n   272→\n   273→  static {\n   274→    for (Field field : SampleVoyages.class.getDeclaredFields()) {\n   275→      if (field.getType().equals(Voyage.class)) {\n   276→        try {\n   277→          Voyage voyage = (Voyage) field.get(null);\n   278→          ALL.put(voyage.getVoyageNumber(), voyage);\n   279→        } catch (IllegalAccessException e) {\n   280→          throw new RuntimeException(e);\n   281→        }\n   282→      }\n   283→    }\n   284→  }\n   285→\n   286→  private static Voyage createVoyage(String id, Location from, Location to) {\n   287→    return new Voyage(\n   288→        new VoyageNumber(id),\n   289→        new Schedule(\n   290→            Collections.singletonList(\n   291→                new CarrierMovement(from, to, LocalDateTime.now(), LocalDateTime.now()))));\n   292→  }\n   293→\n   294→  public static List<Voyage> getAll() {\n   295→    return new ArrayList<>(ALL.values());\n   296→  }\n   297→\n   298→  public static Voyage lookup(VoyageNumber voyageNumber) {\n   299→    return ALL.get(voyageNumber);\n   300→  }\n   301→}\n   302→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"14487ac7-75f7-4148-9d82-21210a1e45c2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018WURxfWVo1FSLrFZjPXepe","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import javax.persistence.Embedded;\n     5→import javax.persistence.Entity;\n     6→import javax.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n     7→import javax.persistence.Id;\n     8→import javax.persistence.NamedQuery;\n     9→import javax.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    10→import javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    11→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    12→\n    13→/**\n    14→ * A location in our model is stops on a journey, such as cargo origin or destination, or carrier\n    15→ * movement end points.\n    16→ *\n    17→ * <p>It is uniquely identified by a UN location code.\n    18→ */\n    19→@Entity\n    20→@NamedQuery(name = \"Location.findAll\", query = \"Select l from Location l\")\n    21→@NamedQuery(\n    22→    name = \"Location.findByUnLocode\",\n    23→    query = \"Select l from Location l where l.unLocode = :unLocode\")\n    24→public class Location implements Serializable {\n    25→\n    26→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    27→\n    28→  // Special Location object that marks an unknown location.\n    29→  public static final Location UNKNOWN = new Location(new UnLocode(\"XXXXX\"), \"Unknown location\");\n    30→\n    31→  @Id @GeneratedValue private Long id;\n    32→  @Embedded @NotNull private UnLocode unLocode;\n    33→  @NotEmpty private String name;\n    34→\n    35→  public Location() {\n    36→    // Nothing to do.\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  /**\n    40→   * @param unLocode UN Locode\n    41→   * @param name Location name\n    42→   * @throws IllegalArgumentException if the UN Locode or name is null\n    43→   */\n    44→  public Location(UnLocode unLocode, String name) {\n    45→    Validate.notNull(unLocode);\n    46→    Validate.notNull(name);\n    47→\n    48→    this.unLocode = unLocode;\n    49→    this.name = name;\n    50→  }\n    51→\n    52→  /** @return UN location code for this location. */\n    53→  public UnLocode getUnLocode() {\n    54→    return unLocode;\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  /** @return Actual name of this location, e.g. \"Stockholm\". */\n    58→  public String getName() {\n    59→    return name;\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  /**\n    63→   * @param object to compare\n    64→   * @return Since this is an entiy this will be true iff UN locodes are equal.\n    65→   */\n    66→  @Override\n    67→  public boolean equals(Object object) {\n    68→    if (object == null) {\n    69→      return false;\n    70→    }\n    71→\n    72→    if (this == object) {\n    73→      return true;\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    if (!(object instanceof Location)) {\n    77→      return false;\n    78→    }\n    79→\n    80→    Location other = (Location) object;\n    81→\n    82→    return sameIdentityAs(other);\n    83→  }\n    84→\n    85→  public boolean sameIdentityAs(Location other) {\n    86→    return this.unLocode.sameValueAs(other.unLocode);\n    87→  }\n    88→\n    89→  /** @return Hash code of UN locode. */\n    90→  @Override\n    91→  public int hashCode() {\n    92→    return unLocode.hashCode();\n    93→  }\n    94→\n    95→  @Override\n    96→  public String toString() {\n    97→    return name + \" [\" + unLocode + \"]\";\n    98→  }\n    99→}\n   100→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"4df31515-279b-4d0a-8e87-9a2bf396cb5f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015YvNLBHx5C7Qx1ooyym72J","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import javax.persistence.Embeddable;\n     5→import javax.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n     6→import javax.validation.constraints.Pattern;\n     7→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n     8→\n     9→/**\n    10→ * United nations location code.\n    11→ *\n    12→ * <p>http://www.unece.org/cefact/locode/\n    13→ * http://www.unece.org/cefact/locode/DocColumnDescription.htm#LOCODE\n    14→ */\n    15→@Embeddable\n    16→public class UnLocode implements Serializable {\n    17→\n    18→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    19→\n    20→  private static final java.util.regex.Pattern VALID_PATTERN =\n    21→      java.util.regex.Pattern.compile(\"[a-zA-Z]{2}[a-zA-Z2-9]{3}\");\n    22→\n    23→  @NotEmpty(message = \"Location code must not be empty.\")\n    24→  // Country code is exactly two letters.\n    25→  // Location code is usually three letters, but may contain the numbers 2-9\n    26→  // as well.\n    27→  @Pattern(regexp = \"[a-zA-Z]{2}[a-zA-Z2-9]{3}\")\n    28→  private String unlocode;\n    29→\n    30→  public UnLocode() {\n    31→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    32→  }\n    33→\n    34→  /** @param countryAndLocation Location string. */\n    35→  public UnLocode(String countryAndLocation) {\n    36→    Validate.notNull(countryAndLocation, \"Country and location may not be null.\");\n    37→    Validate.isTrue(\n    38→        VALID_PATTERN.matcher(countryAndLocation).matches(),\n    39→        countryAndLocation + \" is not a valid UN/LOCODE (does not match pattern)\");\n    40→\n    41→    this.unlocode = countryAndLocation.toUpperCase();\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  /** @return country code and location code concatenated, always upper case. */\n    45→  public String getIdString() {\n    46→    return unlocode;\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  @Override\n    50→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    51→    if (this == o) {\n    52→      return true;\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof UnLocode)) {\n    56→      return false;\n    57→    }\n    58→\n    59→    UnLocode other = (UnLocode) o;\n    60→\n    61→    return sameValueAs(other);\n    62→  }\n    63→\n    64→  @Override\n    65→  public int hashCode() {\n    66→    return unlocode.hashCode();\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  boolean sameValueAs(UnLocode other) {\n    70→    return other != null && this.unlocode.equals(other.unlocode);\n    71→  }\n    72→\n    73→  @Override\n    74→  public String toString() {\n    75→    return getIdString();\n    76→  }\n    77→}\n    78→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"5f0007e2-8f1c-4c04-801d-e6e9d83e5a0c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01F6D6KuCyqLj1kcVg9FtJy6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location;\n     2→\n     3→/** Sample locations, for test purposes. */\n     4→public class SampleLocations {\n     5→\n     6→  public static final Location HONGKONG = new Location(new UnLocode(\"CNHKG\"), \"Hong Kong\");\n     7→  public static final Location MELBOURNE = new Location(new UnLocode(\"AUMEL\"), \"Melbourne\");\n     8→  public static final Location STOCKHOLM = new Location(new UnLocode(\"SESTO\"), \"Stockholm\");\n     9→  public static final Location HELSINKI = new Location(new UnLocode(\"FIHEL\"), \"Helsinki\");\n    10→  public static final Location CHICAGO = new Location(new UnLocode(\"USCHI\"), \"Chicago\");\n    11→  public static final Location TOKYO = new Location(new UnLocode(\"JNTKO\"), \"Tokyo\");\n    12→  public static final Location HAMBURG = new Location(new UnLocode(\"DEHAM\"), \"Hamburg\");\n    13→  public static final Location SHANGHAI = new Location(new UnLocode(\"CNSHA\"), \"Shanghai\");\n    14→  public static final Location ROTTERDAM = new Location(new UnLocode(\"NLRTM\"), \"Rotterdam\");\n    15→  public static final Location GOTHENBURG = new Location(new UnLocode(\"SEGOT\"), \"Gothenburg\");\n    16→  public static final Location HANGZOU = new Location(new UnLocode(\"CNHGH\"), \"Hangzhou\");\n    17→  public static final Location NEWYORK = new Location(new UnLocode(\"USNYC\"), \"New York\");\n    18→  public static final Location DALLAS = new Location(new UnLocode(\"USDAL\"), \"Dallas\");\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"a1c9ae00-3813-4089-9df3-de4582948c5f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015VxNHMx5qAPyjq4MabFZAG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→\n     5→public interface LocationRepository {\n     6→\n     7→  Location find(UnLocode unLocode);\n     8→\n     9→  List<Location> findAll();\n    10→}\n    11→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"f25ed847-eef3-4473-94a2-f3db1c00bba1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019syC6Ra5EbjCcPQqzHXbFg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.service;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\n     6→\n     7→public interface RoutingService {\n     8→\n     9→  /**\n    10→   * @param routeSpecification Route specification\n    11→   * @return A list of itineraries that satisfy the specification. May be an empty list if no route\n    12→   *     is found.\n    13→   */\n    14→  List<Itinerary> fetchRoutesForSpecification(RouteSpecification routeSpecification);\n    15→}\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"0c96f82b-c90c-4dbd-a2ed-88698347f24b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016Y1JUZExZEv6L9SFdcLSCa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * Specification interface.\n     5→ *\n     6→ * <p>Use {@link AbstractSpecification} as base for creating specifications, and only the method\n     7→ * {@link #isSatisfiedBy(Object)} must be implemented.\n     8→ */\n     9→public interface Specification<T> {\n    10→\n    11→  /**\n    12→   * Check if {@code t} is satisfied by the specification.\n    13→   *\n    14→   * @param t Object to test.\n    15→   * @return {@code true} if {@code t} satisfies the specification.\n    16→   */\n    17→  boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t);\n    18→\n    19→  /**\n    20→   * Create a new specification that is the AND operation of {@code this} specification and another\n    21→   * specification.\n    22→   *\n    23→   * @param specification Specification to AND.\n    24→   * @return A new specification.\n    25→   */\n    26→  Specification<T> and(Specification<T> specification);\n    27→\n    28→  /**\n    29→   * Create a new specification that is the OR operation of {@code this} specification and another\n    30→   * specification.\n    31→   *\n    32→   * @param specification Specification to OR.\n    33→   * @return A new specification.\n    34→   */\n    35→  Specification<T> or(Specification<T> specification);\n    36→\n    37→  /**\n    38→   * Create a new specification that is the NOT operation of {@code this} specification.\n    39→   *\n    40→   * @param specification Specification to NOT.\n    41→   * @return A new specification.\n    42→   */\n    43→  Specification<T> not(Specification<T> specification);\n    44→}\n    45→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"c9a26631-1a32-4aa5-b298-33c8d02d182c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012aKebeHrSUHyFRKNUCrxLw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * Abstract base implementation of composite {@link Specification} with default implementations for\n     5→ * {@code and}, {@code or} and {@code not}.\n     6→ */\n     7→public abstract class AbstractSpecification<T> implements Specification<T> {\n     8→\n     9→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    10→  @Override\n    11→  public abstract boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t);\n    12→\n    13→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    14→  @Override\n    15→  public Specification<T> and(Specification<T> specification) {\n    16→    return new AndSpecification<>(this, specification);\n    17→  }\n    18→\n    19→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    20→  @Override\n    21→  public Specification<T> or(Specification<T> specification) {\n    22→    return new OrSpecification<>(this, specification);\n    23→  }\n    24→\n    25→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    26→  @Override\n    27→  public Specification<T> not(Specification<T> specification) {\n    28→    return new NotSpecification<>(specification);\n    29→  }\n    30→}\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"1d80d194-6be1-4ebf-a4b6-5bf097991138"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014uiD97dqM1NtTp3r6LmB9p","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * AND specification, used to create a new specification that is the AND of two other\n     5→ * specifications.\n     6→ */\n     7→public class AndSpecification<T> extends AbstractSpecification<T> {\n     8→\n     9→  private final Specification<T> spec1;\n    10→  private final Specification<T> spec2;\n    11→\n    12→  /**\n    13→   * Create a new AND specification based on two other spec.\n    14→   *\n    15→   * @param spec1 Specification one.\n    16→   * @param spec2 Specification two.\n    17→   */\n    18→  public AndSpecification(Specification<T> spec1, Specification<T> spec2) {\n    19→    this.spec1 = spec1;\n    20→    this.spec2 = spec2;\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    24→  @Override\n    25→  public boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t) {\n    26→    return spec1.isSatisfiedBy(t) && spec2.isSatisfiedBy(t);\n    27→  }\n    28→}\n    29→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"4191e403-4c92-441f-bbc8-ed1121b051ce"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01K7PjqBS4iAH5Tk2jtS1qhi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * OR specification, used to create a new specification that is the OR of two other specifications.\n     5→ */\n     6→public class OrSpecification<T> extends AbstractSpecification<T> {\n     7→\n     8→  private final Specification<T> spec1;\n     9→  private final Specification<T> spec2;\n    10→\n    11→  /**\n    12→   * Create a new OR specification based on two other spec.\n    13→   *\n    14→   * @param spec1 Specification one.\n    15→   * @param spec2 Specification two.\n    16→   */\n    17→  public OrSpecification(Specification<T> spec1, Specification<T> spec2) {\n    18→    this.spec1 = spec1;\n    19→    this.spec2 = spec2;\n    20→  }\n    21→\n    22→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    23→  @Override\n    24→  public boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t) {\n    25→    return spec1.isSatisfiedBy(t) || spec2.isSatisfiedBy(t);\n    26→  }\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"c8cf0754-bd11-4f71-b0e8-5ef08adb9a71"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KAyhMbiYRc7Zq3hq4ZD83m","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/** NOT decorator, used to create a new specifcation that is the inverse (NOT) of the given spec. */\n     4→public class NotSpecification<T> extends AbstractSpecification<T> {\n     5→\n     6→  private final Specification<T> spec1;\n     7→\n     8→  /**\n     9→   * Create a new NOT specification based on another spec.\n    10→   *\n    11→   * @param spec1 Specification instance to not.\n    12→   */\n    13→  public NotSpecification(Specification<T> spec1) {\n    14→    this.spec1 = spec1;\n    15→  }\n    16→\n    17→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    18→  @Override\n    19→  public boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t) {\n    20→    return !spec1.isSatisfiedBy(t);\n    21→  }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"623a0306-6bbc-42cc-987c-955706a4254a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01X2oacRBCJqxT3eBgdUdQgA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→// TODO [Clean Code] Make this a CDI singleton?\n     4→public class DomainObjectUtils {\n     5→\n     6→  /** Prevent instantiation. */\n     7→  private DomainObjectUtils() {}\n     8→\n     9→  /**\n    10→   * @param actual actual value\n    11→   * @param safe a null-safe value\n    12→   * @param <T> type\n    13→   * @return actual value, if it's not null, or safe value if the actual value is null.\n    14→   */\n    15→  public static <T> T nullSafe(T actual, T safe) {\n    16→    return actual == null ? safe : actual;\n    17→  }\n    18→}\n    19→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CZ1N85KfumjsxYjPf7Cgdg","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"6288eb32-53bb-459a-b678-5cc8e6dcbc1e"}
