{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013fzdtL46XDTwk2LDZr6Yp4","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have successfully read all 34 Java files. Here is the complete content with full file paths for each:\n\n---\n\n## 1. BookingServiceFacade.java\n**File Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/BookingServiceFacade.java`\n\nThis is the main facade interface that shields the domain layer from UI concerns. It defines operations for booking cargo, loading cargo information, assigning routes, changing destinations/deadlines, and listing shipping locations.\n\n**Lines 1-37:** Interface definition with methods for booking operations including `bookNewCargo()`, `loadCargoForRouting()`, `loadCargoForTracking()`, `assignCargoToRoute()`, `changeDestination()`, `changeDeadline()`, `requestPossibleRoutesForCargo()`, `listShippingLocations()`, `listAllCargos()`, and `listAllTrackingIds()`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. DefaultBookingServiceFacade.java\n**File Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/internal/DefaultBookingServiceFacade.java`\n\nDefault implementation of BookingServiceFacade using CDI for dependency injection.\n\n**Lines 1-137:** ApplicationScoped implementation that coordinates between the BookingService, repositories, and DTO assemblers. Translates domain objects to DTOs and vice versa.\n\n---\n\n## 3. TrackingEvents.java\n**File Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/dto/TrackingEvents.java`\n\nSimple DTO for tracking events.\n\n**Lines 1-27:** Contains `expected` (boolean), `description` (String), and `time` (String) fields with constructor and getters.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Location.java\n**File Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/dto/Location.java`\n\nLocation DTO with UN Location Code and name.\n\n**Lines 1-31:** Serializable class with `unLocode` and `name` fields. Includes `toString()` that formats as \"name (unLocode)\".\n\n---\n\n## 5. RouteCandidate.java\n**File Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/dto/RouteCandidate.java`\n\nDTO for presenting and selecting itinerary candidates.\n\n**Lines 1-27:** Contains list of `Leg` objects and returns unmodifiable list via `getLegs()`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. CargoRoute.java\n**File Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/dto/CargoRoute.java`\n\nDTO for registering and routing cargo.\n\n**Lines 1-115:** Comprehensive DTO with trackingId, origin, finalDestination, arrivalDeadline, misrouted flag, legs, claimed status, lastKnownLocation, and transportStatus. Includes numerous getter methods for different representations of the same data.\n\n---\n\n## 7. CargoStatus.java\n**File Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/dto/CargoStatus.java`\n\nDTO for cargo status tracking.\n\n**Lines 1-65:** Contains trackingId, destination, statusText, misdirected flag, eta, nextExpectedActivity, and list of tracking events