{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DrmqAqZzk9BPjYS22wNhWq","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/shared/OrSpecification.java has been updated. Here's the result of running `cat -n` on a snippet of the edited file:\n     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * OR specification, used to create a new specification that is the OR of two other specifications.\n     5→ */\n     6→public class OrSpecification<T> extends AbstractSpecification<T> {\n     7→\n     8→  private final Specification<T> spec1;\n     9→  private final Specification<T> spec2;\n    10→\n    11→  /**\n    12→   * Create a new OR specification based on two other spec.\n    13→   *\n    14→   * @param spec1 Specification one.\n    15→   * @param spec2 Specification two.\n    16→   */\n    17→  public OrSpecification(Specification<T> spec1, Specification<T> spec2) {\n    18→    this.spec1 = spec1;\n    19→    this.spec2 = spec2;\n    20→  }\n    21→\n    22→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    23→  @Override\n    24→  public boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t) {\n    25→    return spec1.isSatisfiedBy(t) || spec2.isSatisfiedBy(t);\n    26→  }\n    27→}\n    28→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DAbb751bLM9vT33d25x5vB","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"b6615136-5b87-48f7-b838-f27e6dbd8112"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RWesWoFRcTG1qPbr6EUNSH","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/shared/NotSpecification.java has been updated. Here's the result of running `cat -n` on a snippet of the edited file:\n     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→/** NOT decorator, used to create a new specifcation that is the inverse (NOT) of the given spec. */\n     4→public class NotSpecification<T> extends AbstractSpecification<T> {\n     5→\n     6→  private final Specification<T> spec1;\n     7→\n     8→  /**\n     9→   * Create a new NOT specification based on another spec.\n    10→   *\n    11→   * @param spec1 Specification instance to not.\n    12→   */\n    13→  public NotSpecification(Specification<T> spec1) {\n    14→    this.spec1 = spec1;\n    15→  }\n    16→\n    17→  /** {@inheritDoc} */\n    18→  @Override\n    19→  public boolean isSatisfiedBy(T t) {\n    20→    return !spec1.isSatisfiedBy(t);\n    21→  }\n    22→}\n    23→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DAbb751bLM9vT33d25x5vB","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"98edfdc9-61f1-4465-874a-89c71923a633"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0196xbc64zvHSNuuJ8rAEn8e","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/shared/DomainObjectUtils.java has been updated. Here's the result of running `cat -n` on a snippet of the edited file:\n     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared;\n     2→\n     3→// TODO [Clean Code] Make this a CDI singleton?\n     4→public class DomainObjectUtils {\n     5→\n     6→  /** Prevent instantiation. */\n     7→  private DomainObjectUtils() {}\n     8→\n     9→  /**\n    10→   * @param actual actual value\n    11→   * @param safe a null-safe value\n    12→   * @param <T> type\n    13→   * @return actual value, if it's not null, or safe value if the actual value is null.\n    14→   */\n    15→  public static <T> T nullSafe(T actual, T safe) {\n    16→    return actual == null ? safe : actual;\n    17→  }\n    18→}\n    19→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DAbb751bLM9vT33d25x5vB","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"81ef51bb-08e0-49d2-af77-1775ef8b6626"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DAbb751bLM9vT33d25x5vB","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have successfully migrated all 25 Java files from Jakarta EE to Spring Boot 2.7.x. Let me provide a comprehensive summary of the changes made:\n\n## Migration Summary: Jakarta EE to Spring Boot 2.7.x\n\n### Files Modified with Actual Changes:\n\n**1. HandlingEventFactory.java** (/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/HandlingEventFactory.java)\n- Changed `@ApplicationScoped` to `@Component`\n- Changed `@Inject` to `@Autowired` (3 occurrences)\n- Changed imports from `javax.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped` and `javax.inject.Inject` to Spring equivalents\n\n**2. CannotCreateHandlingEventException.java** (/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/domain/model/handling/CannotCreateHandlingEventException.java)\n- Removed `@ApplicationException(rollback = true)` annotation\n- Removed import for `javax.ejb.ApplicationException`\n\n### Files Written with No Changes (remain compatible):\n\n**Handling Domain (No changes needed):**\n3. HandlingEvent.java - JPA entity with javax.persistence annotations (compatible)\n4. HandlingHistory.java - Value object with no Jakarta/Spring dependencies\n5. HandlingEventRepository.java - Interface, no framework annotations\n6. UnknownVoyageException.java - Exception class, no @ApplicationException needed\n7. UnknownCargoException.java - Exception class, no @ApplicationException needed\n8. UnknownLocationException.java - Exception class, no @ApplicationException needed\n\n**Voyage Domain (No changes needed):**\n9. Voyage.java - JPA entity with javax.persistence annotations\n10. VoyageNumber.java - Embeddable value object\n11. VoyageRepository.java - Interface\n12. Schedule.java - Embeddable with javax.persistence annotations\n13. CarrierMovement.java - JPA entity\n14. SampleVoyages.java - Utility class with no framework dependencies\n\n**Location Domain (No changes needed):**\n15. Location.java - JPA entity with javax.persistence annotations\n16. UnLocode.java - Embeddable value object\n17. SampleLocations.java - Utility class\n18. LocationRepository.java - Interface\n\n**Domain Service and Shared (No changes needed):**\n19. RoutingService.java - Interface\n20. Specification.java - Interface\n21. AbstractSpecification.java - Abstract class\n22. AndSpecification.java - Specification implementation\n23. OrSpecification.java - Specification implementation\n24. NotSpecification.java - Specification implementation\n25. DomainObjectUtils.java - Utility class\n\n### Key Migration Points:\n\n1. **JPA Annotations**: All JPA annotations remain as `javax.persistence.*` (correct for Spring Boot 2.7.x, which still uses the javax namespace, not jakarta)\n\n2. **Validation Annotations**: All validation annotations remain as `javax.validation.*` (correct for Spring Boot 2.7.x)\n\n3. **CDI to Spring**: \n   - `@ApplicationScoped` → `@Component`\n   - `@Inject` → `@Autowired`\n\n4. **EJB Annotations Removed**: \n   - `@ApplicationException` removed from exception classes (EJB-specific, not needed in Spring)\n\n5. **Repository Interfaces**: Remain as plain Java interfaces (will be implemented by Spring Data JPA or custom implementations)\n\n6. **Domain Model**: Unchanged - follows DDD principles and remains framework-agnostic where possible\n\nAll files have been successfully written to the output directory and are ready for use in a Spring Boot 2.7.x application."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"06c16165-26b0-4daa-9dfb-469e287e951d"}
