{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_011a7tK6NLM5jvDPqWGWCZgA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01Sza7KWb2edyqtgJwhieoCR","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Migrate application layer to Spring","prompt":"I am migrating a Jakarta EE Cargo Tracker application to Spring Boot 2.7.x. I need you to read existing files and write migrated versions for the APPLICATION LAYER.\n\nBase directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\nKey migration rules:\n- Spring Boot 2.7.x uses javax.persistence.*, javax.validation.* (NOT jakarta.*)\n- @Stateless (EJB) -> @Service + @Transactional\n- @Singleton @Startup -> @Component with @PostConstruct or CommandLineRunner\n- @Inject -> @Autowired (or keep @Inject, Spring supports both)\n- @ApplicationScoped -> @Component or @Service\n- @Resource -> @Value or @Autowired\n- javax.enterprise.event.Event -> Spring ApplicationEventPublisher\n- javax.enterprise.event.Observes -> Spring @EventListener\n- No more JNDI lookups\n- Replace JMS with Spring ApplicationEvents for async messaging\n\nFILES TO MIGRATE:\n\n### 1. BookingService.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/BookingService.java)\n- Interface, should need no changes. Read and verify.\n\n### 2. CargoInspectionService.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/CargoInspectionService.java)\n- Interface, should need no changes. Read and verify.\n\n### 3. HandlingEventService.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/HandlingEventService.java)\n- Interface, should need no changes. Read and verify.\n\n### 4. ApplicationEvents.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/ApplicationEvents.java)\n- Interface, should need no changes. Read and verify.\n\n### 5. DefaultBookingService.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultBookingService.java)\n- Read the file first, then write migrated version:\n  - Change @Stateless to @Service + @Transactional\n  - Change @Inject to @Autowired\n  - Remove EJB imports, add Spring imports\n  - Keep business logic identical\n\n### 6. DefaultCargoInspectionService.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultCargoInspectionService.java)\n- Read the file first, then write migrated version:\n  - Change @Stateless to @Service + @Transactional\n  - Change @Inject to @Autowired\n  - Remove EJB imports, add Spring imports\n\n### 7. DefaultHandlingEventService.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultHandlingEventService.java)\n- Read the file first, then write migrated version:\n  - Change @Stateless to @Service + @Transactional\n  - Change @Inject to @Autowired\n\n### 8. ApplicationSettings.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/ApplicationSettings.java)\n- JPA Entity, should need no changes. Read and verify.\n\n### 9. DateConverter.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/DateConverter.java)\n- Utility class, should need no changes. Read and verify.\n\n### 10. RestConfiguration.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/RestConfiguration.java)\n- DELETE or completely rewrite this file. In Spring Boot, REST is auto-configured.\n- WRITE a new version that is empty/no-op or delete it by writing a minimal version:\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n\n// In Spring Boot, REST configuration is handled automatically.\n// This class is kept for structural compatibility.\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\n\n@Configuration\npublic class RestConfiguration {\n    // Spring Boot auto-configures REST endpoints via @RestController annotations\n}\n```\n\n### 11. SampleDataGenerator.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/SampleDataGenerator.java)\n- This is a @Singleton @Startup bean that loads sample data.\n- Read the file first. It uses @PersistenceContext EntityManager for raw JPA operations.\n- Write migrated version:\n  - Replace @Singleton @Startup with @Component\n  - Replace @Inject with @Autowired  \n  - Add implements CommandLineRunner\n  - Replace @PostConstruct loadSampleData() with run(String... args) method\n  - Replace @PersistenceContext EntityManager with @Autowired EntityManager (or use @PersistenceContext, Spring supports it)\n  - Keep @Transactional on methods that do DB operations\n  - Remove javax.ejb imports, add Spring imports\n  - The method annotated @PostConstruct should be renamed or called from run()\n\nIMPORTANT: Read each file FIRST before writing the migrated version. Keep all business logic exactly the same.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4679,"cache_read_input_tokens":81527,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4679,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5978},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"3651d213-0705-4fe0-9a14-289aa2baf9fb"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_011a7tK6NLM5jvDPqWGWCZgA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_014FNHC1EwVT2yLV4ie2q9aJ","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Migrate infrastructure layer to Spring","prompt":"I am migrating a Jakarta EE Cargo Tracker application to Spring Boot 2.7.x. I need you to read existing files and write migrated versions for the INFRASTRUCTURE LAYER.\n\nBase directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\nKey migration rules:\n- Spring Boot 2.7.x uses javax.persistence.*, javax.validation.* (NOT jakarta.*)\n- @ApplicationScoped -> @Component or @Repository or @Service\n- @Inject -> @Autowired\n- @PersistenceContext -> @PersistenceContext (Spring supports this) or use @Autowired EntityManager\n- javax.enterprise.event.Event<T> -> Spring ApplicationEventPublisher\n- javax.enterprise.event.Observes -> Spring @EventListener\n- @MessageDriven (JMS) -> Replace with Spring @EventListener methods\n- @Resource(lookup=...) JNDI -> @Value for properties\n- JMSContext/JMS messaging -> Spring ApplicationEventPublisher\n- @Stateless -> @Service\n- @Qualifier annotations -> Spring @Qualifier\n- CDI @Produces -> Spring @Bean methods in @Configuration\n\nFILES TO MIGRATE:\n\n### 1. CargoUpdated.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/events/cdi/CargoUpdated.java)\n- This is a CDI @Qualifier annotation. In Spring, we can keep it as a marker or remove it.\n- Since Spring event system works differently, write a simplified version - just keep it as a simple custom annotation or marker interface:\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi;\n\nimport java.lang.annotation.ElementType;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Retention;\nimport java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Target;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;\n\n@Qualifier\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.FIELD, ElementType.PARAMETER, ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD})\npublic @interface CargoUpdated {}\n```\n\n### 2. LoggerProducer.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/logging/LoggerProducer.java)\n- CDI @Produces for Logger -> Not needed in Spring (use @Slf4j or direct Logger creation)\n- Read existing file, then write a Spring @Configuration version that provides a Logger bean, OR simply remove it since Spring applications typically use SLF4J directly.\n- Best approach: Keep a minimal version for backward compatibility, but note in Spring each class should get its own Logger via LoggerFactory. Write:\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.logging;\n\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\n\n@Configuration\npublic class LoggerProducer {\n    // In Spring Boot, logging is configured automatically.\n    // Each class should use: private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(MyClass.class);\n    // or use @Slf4j annotation from Lombok.\n}\n```\n\n### 3. JpaCargoRepository.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/persistence/jpa/JpaCargoRepository.java)\n- Read the file first, then migrate:\n  - @ApplicationScoped -> @Repository\n  - @Inject -> @Autowired\n  - @PersistenceContext -> @PersistenceContext (Spring supports this)\n  - Remove CDI Event<Cargo> cargoUpdated -> use ApplicationEventPublisher\n  - cargoUpdated.fireAsync(cargo) -> eventPublisher.publishEvent(cargo)\n  - Remove @Inject Logger -> use private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(...)\n  - Remove Serializable (not needed in Spring)\n  - Remove @CargoUpdated qualifier on event\n\n### 4. JpaVoyageRepository.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/persistence/jpa/JpaVoyageRepository.java)\n- Read first, then migrate:\n  - @ApplicationScoped -> @Repository\n  - @PersistenceContext stays\n  - Remove Serializable\n  - Remove @Inject Logger if present\n\n### 5. JpaLocationRepository.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/persistence/jpa/JpaLocationRepository.java)\n- Same as above\n\n### 6. JpaHandlingEventRepository.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/persistence/jpa/JpaHandlingEventRepository.java)\n- Same as above\n\n### 7. JmsApplicationEvents.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/jms/JmsApplicationEvents.java)\n- This is the MOST complex migration. JMS queues become Spring ApplicationEvents.\n- Read the file first, then write a completely new Spring-based implementation:\n  - Replace class with SpringApplicationEvents implements ApplicationEvents\n  - @ApplicationScoped -> @Service\n  - Replace all JMS queue sending with ApplicationEventPublisher or direct service calls\n  - For cargoWasHandled: publish a Spring event or directly call CargoInspectionService\n  - For cargoWasMisdirected: just log (original just logs)\n  - For cargoHasArrived: just log (original just logs)\n  - For receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt: use @Async to process asynchronously\n  - Remove all JMS imports and dependencies\n\nWrite the new file as:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\nimport org.springframework.context.ApplicationEventPublisher;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Service;\n\n@Service\npublic class JmsApplicationEvents implements ApplicationEvents {\n\n    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(JmsApplicationEvents.class.getName());\n\n    @Autowired\n    private ApplicationEventPublisher eventPublisher;\n\n    @Override\n    public void cargoWasHandled(HandlingEvent event) {\n        Cargo cargo = event.getCargo();\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo was handled {0}\", cargo);\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new CargoHandledEvent(cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString()));\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void cargoWasMisdirected(Cargo cargo) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo was misdirected {0}\", cargo);\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new CargoMisdirectedEvent(cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString()));\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void cargoHasArrived(Cargo cargo) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo has arrived {0}\", cargo);\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new CargoDeliveredEvent(cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString()));\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Received handling event registration attempt {0}\", attempt);\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptEvent(attempt));\n    }\n\n    // Spring Event classes\n    public static class CargoHandledEvent {\n        private final String trackingId;\n        public CargoHandledEvent(String trackingId) { this.trackingId = trackingId; }\n        public String getTrackingId() { return trackingId; }\n    }\n\n    public static class CargoMisdirectedEvent {\n        private final String trackingId;\n        public CargoMisdirectedEvent(String trackingId) { this.trackingId = trackingId; }\n        public String getTrackingId() { return trackingId; }\n    }\n\n    public static class CargoDeliveredEvent {\n        private final String trackingId;\n        public CargoDeliveredEvent(String trackingId) { this.trackingId = trackingId; }\n        public String getTrackingId() { return trackingId; }\n    }\n\n    public static class HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptEvent {\n        private final HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt;\n        public HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptEvent(HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt) { this.attempt = attempt; }\n        public HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt getAttempt() { return attempt; }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 8-12. JMS Consumer classes - Replace with Spring @EventListener:\n\n**CargoHandledConsumer.java** - Read, then write:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.CargoInspectionService;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Async;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\n@Component\npublic class CargoHandledConsumer {\n\n    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(CargoHandledConsumer.class.getName());\n\n    @Autowired\n    private CargoInspectionService cargoInspectionService;\n\n    @Async\n    @EventListener\n    public void onCargoHandled(JmsApplicationEvents.CargoHandledEvent event) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Processing cargo handled event for {0}\", event.getTrackingId());\n        cargoInspectionService.inspectCargo(new TrackingId(event.getTrackingId()));\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**MisdirectedCargoConsumer.java** - Read, then write:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Async;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\n@Component\npublic class MisdirectedCargoConsumer {\n\n    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(MisdirectedCargoConsumer.class.getName());\n\n    @Async\n    @EventListener\n    public void onCargoMisdirected(JmsApplicationEvents.CargoMisdirectedEvent event) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo with tracking ID {0} misdirected.\", event.getTrackingId());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**DeliveredCargoConsumer.java** - Read, then write:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Async;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\n@Component\npublic class DeliveredCargoConsumer {\n\n    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(DeliveredCargoConsumer.class.getName());\n\n    @Async\n    @EventListener\n    public void onCargoDelivered(JmsApplicationEvents.CargoDeliveredEvent event) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo with tracking ID {0} delivered.\", event.getTrackingId());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**RejectedRegistrationAttemptsConsumer.java** - Read, then write similar pattern with logging only.\n\n**HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptConsumer.java** - Read, then write:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.HandlingEventService;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.CannotCreateHandlingEventException;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Async;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\n@Component\npublic class HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptConsumer {\n\n    @Autowired\n    private HandlingEventService handlingEventService;\n\n    @Async\n    @EventListener\n    public void onHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(JmsApplicationEvents.HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptEvent event) {\n        try {\n            HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt = event.getAttempt();\n            handlingEventService.registerHandlingEvent(\n                attempt.getCompletionTime(),\n                attempt.getTrackingId(),\n                attempt.getVoyageNumber(),\n                attempt.getUnLocode(),\n                attempt.getType());\n        } catch (CannotCreateHandlingEventException e) {\n            throw new RuntimeException(\"Error occurred processing event\", e);\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 13. ExternalRoutingService.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/routing/ExternalRoutingService.java)\n- Read the file first, then migrate:\n  - @Stateless -> @Service\n  - @Inject -> @Autowired\n  - @Resource(lookup = \"java:app/configuration/GraphTraversalUrl\") -> @Value(\"${app.graphTraversalUrl}\")\n  - javax.ws.rs.client.ClientBuilder -> Spring RestTemplate\n  - @PostConstruct init() can stay\n  - Replace JAX-RS client calls with RestTemplate calls\n\nWrite the migrated version using Spring's RestTemplate:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.routing;\n\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\nimport javax.annotation.PostConstruct;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Leg;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.service.RoutingService;\nimport org.eclipse.pathfinder.api.TransitEdge;\nimport org.eclipse.pathfinder.api.TransitPath;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Value;\nimport org.springframework.core.ParameterizedTypeReference;\nimport org.springframework.http.HttpMethod;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Service;\nimport org.springframework.web.client.RestTemplate;\nimport org.springframework.web.util.UriComponentsBuilder;\n\n@Service\npublic class ExternalRoutingService implements RoutingService {\n\n    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(ExternalRoutingService.class.getName());\n\n    @Value(\"${app.graphTraversalUrl}\")\n    private String graphTraversalUrl;\n\n    @Autowired\n    private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n\n    @Autowired\n    private VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n\n    private RestTemplate restTemplate;\n\n    @PostConstruct\n    public void init() {\n        restTemplate = new RestTemplate();\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public List<Itinerary> fetchRoutesForSpecification(RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n        String origin = routeSpecification.getOrigin().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n        String destination = routeSpecification.getDestination().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n\n        String url = UriComponentsBuilder.fromHttpUrl(graphTraversalUrl)\n            .queryParam(\"origin\", origin)\n            .queryParam(\"destination\", destination)\n            .toUriString();\n\n        ResponseEntity<List<TransitPath>> response = restTemplate.exchange(\n            url,\n            HttpMethod.GET,\n            null,\n            new ParameterizedTypeReference<List<TransitPath>>() {});\n\n        List<TransitPath> transitPaths = response.getBody();\n        if (transitPaths == null) {\n            return new ArrayList<>();\n        }\n\n        List<Itinerary> itineraries = new ArrayList<>();\n        transitPaths.stream()\n            .map(this::toItinerary)\n            .forEach(itinerary -> {\n                if (routeSpecification.isSatisfiedBy(itinerary)) {\n                    itineraries.add(itinerary);\n                } else {\n                    logger.log(Level.FINE, \"Received itinerary that did not satisfy the route specification\");\n                }\n            });\n\n        return itineraries;\n    }\n\n    private Itinerary toItinerary(TransitPath transitPath) {\n        List<Leg> legs = transitPath.getTransitEdges().stream()\n            .map(this::toLeg)\n            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n        return new Itinerary(legs);\n    }\n\n    private Leg toLeg(TransitEdge edge) {\n        return new Leg(\n            voyageRepository.find(new VoyageNumber(edge.getVoyageNumber())),\n            locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(edge.getFromUnLocode())),\n            locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(edge.getToUnLocode())),\n            edge.getFromDate(),\n            edge.getToDate());\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIMPORTANT: Read each file first, then write the migrated version. Keep all business logic exactly the same. Only change framework-specific code.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4679,"cache_read_input_tokens":81527,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4679,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5978},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"637d85ff-7ca0-4c62-a5f7-d069bcbe5b35"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I am migrating a Jakarta EE Cargo Tracker application to Spring Boot 2.7.x. I need you to read existing files and write migrated versions for the APPLICATION LAYER.\n\nBase directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\nKey migration rules:\n- Spring Boot 2.7.x uses javax.persistence.*, javax.validation.* (NOT jakarta.*)\n- @Stateless (EJB) -> @Service + @Transactional\n- @Singleton @Startup -> @Component with @PostConstruct or CommandLineRunner\n- @Inject -> @Autowired (or keep @Inject, Spring supports both)\n- @ApplicationScoped -> @Component or @Service\n- @Resource -> @Value or @Autowired\n- javax.enterprise.event.Event -> Spring ApplicationEventPublisher\n- javax.enterprise.event.Observes -> Spring @EventListener\n- No more JNDI lookups\n- Replace JMS with Spring ApplicationEvents for async messaging\n\nFILES TO MIGRATE:\n\n### 1. BookingService.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/BookingService.java)\n- Interface, should need no changes. Read and verify.\n\n### 2. CargoInspectionService.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/CargoInspectionService.java)\n- Interface, should need no changes. Read and verify.\n\n### 3. HandlingEventService.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/HandlingEventService.java)\n- Interface, should need no changes. Read and verify.\n\n### 4. ApplicationEvents.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/ApplicationEvents.java)\n- Interface, should need no changes. Read and verify.\n\n### 5. DefaultBookingService.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultBookingService.java)\n- Read the file first, then write migrated version:\n  - Change @Stateless to @Service + @Transactional\n  - Change @Inject to @Autowired\n  - Remove EJB imports, add Spring imports\n  - Keep business logic identical\n\n### 6. DefaultCargoInspectionService.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultCargoInspectionService.java)\n- Read the file first, then write migrated version:\n  - Change @Stateless to @Service + @Transactional\n  - Change @Inject to @Autowired\n  - Remove EJB imports, add Spring imports\n\n### 7. DefaultHandlingEventService.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/internal/DefaultHandlingEventService.java)\n- Read the file first, then write migrated version:\n  - Change @Stateless to @Service + @Transactional\n  - Change @Inject to @Autowired\n\n### 8. ApplicationSettings.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/ApplicationSettings.java)\n- JPA Entity, should need no changes. Read and verify.\n\n### 9. DateConverter.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/DateConverter.java)\n- Utility class, should need no changes. Read and verify.\n\n### 10. RestConfiguration.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/RestConfiguration.java)\n- DELETE or completely rewrite this file. In Spring Boot, REST is auto-configured.\n- WRITE a new version that is empty/no-op or delete it by writing a minimal version:\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n\n// In Spring Boot, REST configuration is handled automatically.\n// This class is kept for structural compatibility.\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\n\n@Configuration\npublic class RestConfiguration {\n    // Spring Boot auto-configures REST endpoints via @RestController annotations\n}\n```\n\n### 11. SampleDataGenerator.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/application/util/SampleDataGenerator.java)\n- This is a @Singleton @Startup bean that loads sample data.\n- Read the file first. It uses @PersistenceContext EntityManager for raw JPA operations.\n- Write migrated version:\n  - Replace @Singleton @Startup with @Component\n  - Replace @Inject with @Autowired  \n  - Add implements CommandLineRunner\n  - Replace @PostConstruct loadSampleData() with run(String... args) method\n  - Replace @PersistenceContext EntityManager with @Autowired EntityManager (or use @PersistenceContext, Spring supports it)\n  - Keep @Transactional on methods that do DB operations\n  - Remove javax.ejb imports, add Spring imports\n  - The method annotated @PostConstruct should be renamed or called from run()\n\nIMPORTANT: Read each file FIRST before writing the migrated version. Keep all business logic exactly the same."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Sza7KWb2edyqtgJwhieoCR","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"0a643317-cb8a-4a58-aa44-43c52a1f6c03"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I am migrating a Jakarta EE Cargo Tracker application to Spring Boot 2.7.x. I need you to read existing files and write migrated versions for the INFRASTRUCTURE LAYER.\n\nBase directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\nKey migration rules:\n- Spring Boot 2.7.x uses javax.persistence.*, javax.validation.* (NOT jakarta.*)\n- @ApplicationScoped -> @Component or @Repository or @Service\n- @Inject -> @Autowired\n- @PersistenceContext -> @PersistenceContext (Spring supports this) or use @Autowired EntityManager\n- javax.enterprise.event.Event<T> -> Spring ApplicationEventPublisher\n- javax.enterprise.event.Observes -> Spring @EventListener\n- @MessageDriven (JMS) -> Replace with Spring @EventListener methods\n- @Resource(lookup=...) JNDI -> @Value for properties\n- JMSContext/JMS messaging -> Spring ApplicationEventPublisher\n- @Stateless -> @Service\n- @Qualifier annotations -> Spring @Qualifier\n- CDI @Produces -> Spring @Bean methods in @Configuration\n\nFILES TO MIGRATE:\n\n### 1. CargoUpdated.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/events/cdi/CargoUpdated.java)\n- This is a CDI @Qualifier annotation. In Spring, we can keep it as a marker or remove it.\n- Since Spring event system works differently, write a simplified version - just keep it as a simple custom annotation or marker interface:\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi;\n\nimport java.lang.annotation.ElementType;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Retention;\nimport java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Target;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Qualifier;\n\n@Qualifier\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.FIELD, ElementType.PARAMETER, ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD})\npublic @interface CargoUpdated {}\n```\n\n### 2. LoggerProducer.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/logging/LoggerProducer.java)\n- CDI @Produces for Logger -> Not needed in Spring (use @Slf4j or direct Logger creation)\n- Read existing file, then write a Spring @Configuration version that provides a Logger bean, OR simply remove it since Spring applications typically use SLF4J directly.\n- Best approach: Keep a minimal version for backward compatibility, but note in Spring each class should get its own Logger via LoggerFactory. Write:\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.logging;\n\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\n\n@Configuration\npublic class LoggerProducer {\n    // In Spring Boot, logging is configured automatically.\n    // Each class should use: private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(MyClass.class);\n    // or use @Slf4j annotation from Lombok.\n}\n```\n\n### 3. JpaCargoRepository.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/persistence/jpa/JpaCargoRepository.java)\n- Read the file first, then migrate:\n  - @ApplicationScoped -> @Repository\n  - @Inject -> @Autowired\n  - @PersistenceContext -> @PersistenceContext (Spring supports this)\n  - Remove CDI Event<Cargo> cargoUpdated -> use ApplicationEventPublisher\n  - cargoUpdated.fireAsync(cargo) -> eventPublisher.publishEvent(cargo)\n  - Remove @Inject Logger -> use private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(...)\n  - Remove Serializable (not needed in Spring)\n  - Remove @CargoUpdated qualifier on event\n\n### 4. JpaVoyageRepository.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/persistence/jpa/JpaVoyageRepository.java)\n- Read first, then migrate:\n  - @ApplicationScoped -> @Repository\n  - @PersistenceContext stays\n  - Remove Serializable\n  - Remove @Inject Logger if present\n\n### 5. JpaLocationRepository.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/persistence/jpa/JpaLocationRepository.java)\n- Same as above\n\n### 6. JpaHandlingEventRepository.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/persistence/jpa/JpaHandlingEventRepository.java)\n- Same as above\n\n### 7. JmsApplicationEvents.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/messaging/jms/JmsApplicationEvents.java)\n- This is the MOST complex migration. JMS queues become Spring ApplicationEvents.\n- Read the file first, then write a completely new Spring-based implementation:\n  - Replace class with SpringApplicationEvents implements ApplicationEvents\n  - @ApplicationScoped -> @Service\n  - Replace all JMS queue sending with ApplicationEventPublisher or direct service calls\n  - For cargoWasHandled: publish a Spring event or directly call CargoInspectionService\n  - For cargoWasMisdirected: just log (original just logs)\n  - For cargoHasArrived: just log (original just logs)\n  - For receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt: use @Async to process asynchronously\n  - Remove all JMS imports and dependencies\n\nWrite the new file as:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\nimport org.springframework.context.ApplicationEventPublisher;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Service;\n\n@Service\npublic class JmsApplicationEvents implements ApplicationEvents {\n\n    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(JmsApplicationEvents.class.getName());\n\n    @Autowired\n    private ApplicationEventPublisher eventPublisher;\n\n    @Override\n    public void cargoWasHandled(HandlingEvent event) {\n        Cargo cargo = event.getCargo();\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo was handled {0}\", cargo);\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new CargoHandledEvent(cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString()));\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void cargoWasMisdirected(Cargo cargo) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo was misdirected {0}\", cargo);\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new CargoMisdirectedEvent(cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString()));\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void cargoHasArrived(Cargo cargo) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo has arrived {0}\", cargo);\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new CargoDeliveredEvent(cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString()));\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Received handling event registration attempt {0}\", attempt);\n        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptEvent(attempt));\n    }\n\n    // Spring Event classes\n    public static class CargoHandledEvent {\n        private final String trackingId;\n        public CargoHandledEvent(String trackingId) { this.trackingId = trackingId; }\n        public String getTrackingId() { return trackingId; }\n    }\n\n    public static class CargoMisdirectedEvent {\n        private final String trackingId;\n        public CargoMisdirectedEvent(String trackingId) { this.trackingId = trackingId; }\n        public String getTrackingId() { return trackingId; }\n    }\n\n    public static class CargoDeliveredEvent {\n        private final String trackingId;\n        public CargoDeliveredEvent(String trackingId) { this.trackingId = trackingId; }\n        public String getTrackingId() { return trackingId; }\n    }\n\n    public static class HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptEvent {\n        private final HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt;\n        public HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptEvent(HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt) { this.attempt = attempt; }\n        public HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt getAttempt() { return attempt; }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 8-12. JMS Consumer classes - Replace with Spring @EventListener:\n\n**CargoHandledConsumer.java** - Read, then write:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.CargoInspectionService;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Async;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\n@Component\npublic class CargoHandledConsumer {\n\n    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(CargoHandledConsumer.class.getName());\n\n    @Autowired\n    private CargoInspectionService cargoInspectionService;\n\n    @Async\n    @EventListener\n    public void onCargoHandled(JmsApplicationEvents.CargoHandledEvent event) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Processing cargo handled event for {0}\", event.getTrackingId());\n        cargoInspectionService.inspectCargo(new TrackingId(event.getTrackingId()));\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**MisdirectedCargoConsumer.java** - Read, then write:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Async;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\n@Component\npublic class MisdirectedCargoConsumer {\n\n    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(MisdirectedCargoConsumer.class.getName());\n\n    @Async\n    @EventListener\n    public void onCargoMisdirected(JmsApplicationEvents.CargoMisdirectedEvent event) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo with tracking ID {0} misdirected.\", event.getTrackingId());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**DeliveredCargoConsumer.java** - Read, then write:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Async;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\n@Component\npublic class DeliveredCargoConsumer {\n\n    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(DeliveredCargoConsumer.class.getName());\n\n    @Async\n    @EventListener\n    public void onCargoDelivered(JmsApplicationEvents.CargoDeliveredEvent event) {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Cargo with tracking ID {0} delivered.\", event.getTrackingId());\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**RejectedRegistrationAttemptsConsumer.java** - Read, then write similar pattern with logging only.\n\n**HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptConsumer.java** - Read, then write:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.messaging.jms;\n\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.HandlingEventService;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.CannotCreateHandlingEventException;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Async;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\n@Component\npublic class HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptConsumer {\n\n    @Autowired\n    private HandlingEventService handlingEventService;\n\n    @Async\n    @EventListener\n    public void onHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(JmsApplicationEvents.HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptEvent event) {\n        try {\n            HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt = event.getAttempt();\n            handlingEventService.registerHandlingEvent(\n                attempt.getCompletionTime(),\n                attempt.getTrackingId(),\n                attempt.getVoyageNumber(),\n                attempt.getUnLocode(),\n                attempt.getType());\n        } catch (CannotCreateHandlingEventException e) {\n            throw new RuntimeException(\"Error occurred processing event\", e);\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 13. ExternalRoutingService.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/infrastructure/routing/ExternalRoutingService.java)\n- Read the file first, then migrate:\n  - @Stateless -> @Service\n  - @Inject -> @Autowired\n  - @Resource(lookup = \"java:app/configuration/GraphTraversalUrl\") -> @Value(\"${app.graphTraversalUrl}\")\n  - javax.ws.rs.client.ClientBuilder -> Spring RestTemplate\n  - @PostConstruct init() can stay\n  - Replace JAX-RS client calls with RestTemplate calls\n\nWrite the migrated version using Spring's RestTemplate:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.routing;\n\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\nimport javax.annotation.PostConstruct;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Leg;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.service.RoutingService;\nimport org.eclipse.pathfinder.api.TransitEdge;\nimport org.eclipse.pathfinder.api.TransitPath;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Value;\nimport org.springframework.core.ParameterizedTypeReference;\nimport org.springframework.http.HttpMethod;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Service;\nimport org.springframework.web.client.RestTemplate;\nimport org.springframework.web.util.UriComponentsBuilder;\n\n@Service\npublic class ExternalRoutingService implements RoutingService {\n\n    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(ExternalRoutingService.class.getName());\n\n    @Value(\"${app.graphTraversalUrl}\")\n    private String graphTraversalUrl;\n\n    @Autowired\n    private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n\n    @Autowired\n    private VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n\n    private RestTemplate restTemplate;\n\n    @PostConstruct\n    public void init() {\n        restTemplate = new RestTemplate();\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public List<Itinerary> fetchRoutesForSpecification(RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n        String origin = routeSpecification.getOrigin().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n        String destination = routeSpecification.getDestination().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n\n        String url = UriComponentsBuilder.fromHttpUrl(graphTraversalUrl)\n            .queryParam(\"origin\", origin)\n            .queryParam(\"destination\", destination)\n            .toUriString();\n\n        ResponseEntity<List<TransitPath>> response = restTemplate.exchange(\n            url,\n            HttpMethod.GET,\n            null,\n            new ParameterizedTypeReference<List<TransitPath>>() {});\n\n        List<TransitPath> transitPaths = response.getBody();\n        if (transitPaths == null) {\n            return new ArrayList<>();\n        }\n\n        List<Itinerary> itineraries = new ArrayList<>();\n        transitPaths.stream()\n            .map(this::toItinerary)\n            .forEach(itinerary -> {\n                if (routeSpecification.isSatisfiedBy(itinerary)) {\n                    itineraries.add(itinerary);\n                } else {\n                    logger.log(Level.FINE, \"Received itinerary that did not satisfy the route specification\");\n                }\n            });\n\n        return itineraries;\n    }\n\n    private Itinerary toItinerary(TransitPath transitPath) {\n        List<Leg> legs = transitPath.getTransitEdges().stream()\n            .map(this::toLeg)\n            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n        return new Itinerary(legs);\n    }\n\n    private Leg toLeg(TransitEdge edge) {\n        return new Leg(\n            voyageRepository.find(new VoyageNumber(edge.getVoyageNumber())),\n            locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(edge.getFromUnLocode())),\n            locationRepository.find(new UnLocode(edge.getToUnLocode())),\n            edge.getFromDate(),\n            edge.getToDate());\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIMPORTANT: Read each file first, then write the migrated version. Keep all business logic exactly the same. Only change framework-specific code."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014FNHC1EwVT2yLV4ie2q9aJ","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"6372c9d0-e103-4180-85de-53b7360eab9c"}
