{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01FgYWSQnsa2zUcmFFuDZDJh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01P9o4BPvGfqGgpY4qAiCPkX","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Migrate interfaces layer to Spring","prompt":"I am migrating a Jakarta EE Cargo Tracker application to Spring Boot 2.7.x. I need you to read existing files and write migrated versions for the INTERFACES LAYER.\n\nBase directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\nCRITICAL: The original app uses JSF/PrimeFaces for web UI, which is NOT compatible with Spring Boot. ALL JSF backing beans need to be converted to Spring REST controllers that return JSON.\n\nKey migration rules:\n- Spring Boot 2.7.x uses javax.* (NOT jakarta.*)\n- @Named / @RequestScoped / @ViewScoped / @SessionScoped / @FlowScoped JSF beans -> @RestController Spring beans\n- JSF actions -> REST API endpoints returning JSON\n- @Inject -> @Autowired\n- @ApplicationScoped -> @Component or @Service\n- Keep all business logic the same, just expose via REST API instead of JSF pages\n- SSE via JAX-RS -> Spring SseEmitter\n\nFILES TO MIGRATE:\n\n### 1. Coordinates.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/Coordinates.java)\n- Pure POJO, no changes needed. Read and verify.\n\n### 2. CoordinatesFactory.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/CoordinatesFactory.java)  \n- Static utility class, no changes needed. Read and verify.\n\n### 3. FacesConfiguration.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/FacesConfiguration.java)\n- JSF config class - no longer needed. Replace with minimal Spring config:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces;\n\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\n\n@Configuration\npublic class FacesConfiguration {\n    // JSF configuration replaced by Spring MVC auto-configuration\n}\n```\n\n### 4. BookingServiceFacade.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/BookingServiceFacade.java)\n- Interface, should need no changes. Read and verify.\n\n### 5. DefaultBookingServiceFacade.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/internal/DefaultBookingServiceFacade.java)\n- Read first, then migrate:\n  - @ApplicationScoped -> @Service\n  - @Inject -> @Autowired\n\n### 6-11. DTO classes (all in src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/dto/)\n- Read all DTOs (CargoRoute.java, CargoStatus.java, Leg.java, Location.java, RouteCandidate.java, TrackingEvents.java)\n- These are pure POJOs/DTOs. Should need no changes. Verify.\n\n### 12-16. Assembler classes (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/internal/assembler/)\n- Read all assemblers (CargoRouteDtoAssembler.java, CargoStatusDtoAssembler.java, ItineraryCandidateDtoAssembler.java, LocationDtoAssembler.java, TrackingEventsDtoAssembler.java)\n- Migrate: @ApplicationScoped -> @Component, @Inject -> @Autowired\n\n### 17. HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt.java)\n- Read and verify - Serializable transfer object, might need no changes.\n\n### NOW THE BIG ONES - Replace JSF backing beans with REST controllers:\n\n### 18. ListCargo.java -> Convert from JSF @RequestScoped bean to methods in a new REST controller\n### 19. CargoDetails.java -> Convert to REST endpoint  \n### 20. Track.java -> Convert to REST endpoint\n### 21. Booking.java -> Convert to REST endpoints\n### 22. ItinerarySelection.java -> Convert to REST endpoint\n### 23. ChangeDestination.java -> Convert to REST endpoint\n### 24. ChangeDestinationDialog.java -> Remove (dialog is UI-only concept)\n### 25. ChangeArrivalDeadline.java -> Convert to REST endpoint\n### 26. ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog.java -> Remove (dialog is UI-only concept)\n### 27. EventLogger.java -> Convert from JSF to REST endpoint\n\nFor the JSF backing beans, I want you to create TWO new REST controller files that consolidate the functionality:\n\n**File 1: CargoAdminController.java** at src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/CargoAdminController.java\n\nThis consolidates all cargo admin operations (list, details, booking, routing, change destination, change deadline):\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDate;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoStatus;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.RouteCandidate;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/cargo\")\npublic class CargoAdminController {\n\n    @Autowired\n    private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/list\")\n    public ResponseEntity<List<CargoRoute>> listAllCargo() {\n        List<CargoRoute> cargos = bookingServiceFacade.listAllCargos();\n        return ResponseEntity.ok(cargos);\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/{trackingId}\")\n    public ResponseEntity<CargoRoute> getCargo(@PathVariable String trackingId) {\n        CargoRoute cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n        return ResponseEntity.ok(cargo);\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/{trackingId}/track\")\n    public ResponseEntity<CargoStatus> trackCargo(@PathVariable String trackingId) {\n        CargoStatus status = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForTracking(trackingId);\n        if (status == null) {\n            return ResponseEntity.notFound().build();\n        }\n        return ResponseEntity.ok(status);\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/book\")\n    public ResponseEntity<String> bookCargo(\n            @RequestParam String originUnLocode,\n            @RequestParam String destinationUnLocode,\n            @RequestParam String arrivalDeadline) {\n        LocalDate deadline = LocalDate.parse(arrivalDeadline);\n        String trackingId = bookingServiceFacade.bookNewCargo(originUnLocode, destinationUnLocode, deadline);\n        return ResponseEntity.ok(trackingId);\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/locations\")\n    public ResponseEntity<List<Location>> listLocations() {\n        List<Location> locations = bookingServiceFacade.listShippingLocations();\n        return ResponseEntity.ok(locations);\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/{trackingId}/routes\")\n    public ResponseEntity<List<RouteCandidate>> requestRoutes(@PathVariable String trackingId) {\n        List<RouteCandidate> routes = bookingServiceFacade.requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(trackingId);\n        return ResponseEntity.ok(routes);\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/{trackingId}/assignRoute\")\n    public ResponseEntity<Void> assignRoute(\n            @PathVariable String trackingId,\n            @RequestBody RouteCandidate route) {\n        bookingServiceFacade.assignCargoToRoute(trackingId, route);\n        return ResponseEntity.ok().build();\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/{trackingId}/changeDestination\")\n    public ResponseEntity<Void> changeDestination(\n            @PathVariable String trackingId,\n            @RequestParam String destinationUnLocode) {\n        bookingServiceFacade.changeDestination(trackingId, destinationUnLocode);\n        return ResponseEntity.ok().build();\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/{trackingId}/changeDeadline\")\n    public ResponseEntity<Void> changeDeadline(\n            @PathVariable String trackingId,\n            @RequestParam String deadline) {\n        LocalDate newDeadline = LocalDate.parse(deadline);\n        bookingServiceFacade.changeDeadline(trackingId, newDeadline);\n        return ResponseEntity.ok().build();\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/trackingIds\")\n    public ResponseEntity<List<String>> listTrackingIds() {\n        List<String> trackingIds = bookingServiceFacade.listAllTrackingIds();\n        return ResponseEntity.ok(trackingIds);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**File 2: HandlingEventController.java** at src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/HandlingEventController.java\n\nThis replaces the EventLogger JSF bean and provides REST API for handling events:\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDateTime;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/handling\")\npublic class HandlingEventController {\n\n    @Autowired\n    private ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/register\")\n    public ResponseEntity<Void> registerHandlingEvent(\n            @RequestParam String completionTime,\n            @RequestParam String trackingId,\n            @RequestParam String voyageNumber,\n            @RequestParam String unLocode,\n            @RequestParam String eventType) {\n\n        LocalDateTime completionDateTime = DateConverter.toDateTime(completionTime);\n        TrackingId tid = new TrackingId(trackingId);\n        VoyageNumber vn = new VoyageNumber(voyageNumber);\n        UnLocode loc = new UnLocode(unLocode);\n        HandlingEvent.Type type = HandlingEvent.Type.valueOf(eventType);\n\n        HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt = new HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(\n            LocalDateTime.now(), completionDateTime, tid, vn, type, loc);\n\n        applicationEvents.receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(attempt);\n\n        return ResponseEntity.ok().build();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### SSE Service - RealtimeCargoTrackingService.java\nRead the original file. Migrate from JAX-RS SSE to Spring SseEmitter:\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.sse;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.concurrent.CopyOnWriteArrayList;\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi.CargoUpdated;\nimport org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Controller;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestMapping;\nimport org.springframework.web.servlet.mvc.method.annotation.SseEmitter;\n\n@Controller\n@RequestMapping(\"/rest/tracking\")\npublic class RealtimeCargoTrackingService {\n\n    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(RealtimeCargoTrackingService.class.getName());\n\n    private final List<SseEmitter> emitters = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<>();\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/cargo\")\n    public SseEmitter trackCargo() {\n        SseEmitter emitter = new SseEmitter(Long.MAX_VALUE);\n        emitters.add(emitter);\n        emitter.onCompletion(() -> emitters.remove(emitter));\n        emitter.onTimeout(() -> emitters.remove(emitter));\n        emitter.onError(e -> emitters.remove(emitter));\n        return emitter;\n    }\n\n    @EventListener\n    public void onCargoUpdated(Cargo cargo) {\n        RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter adapter = new RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter(cargo);\n        for (SseEmitter emitter : emitters) {\n            try {\n                emitter.send(SseEmitter.event()\n                    .name(\"N/A\")\n                    .data(adapter.toJson()));\n            } catch (IOException e) {\n                emitters.remove(emitter);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter.java\nRead the original file. In Spring context, add a toJson() method or ensure it's Jackson-serializable.\n\n### LocationViewAdapter.java\nRead the original file. Should be mostly unchanged.\n\n### File processing batch job files (UploadDirectoryScanner, EventItemReader, EventItemWriter, EventFilesCheckpoint, LineParseExceptionListener, EventLineParseException, FileProcessorJobListener)\nThese use Jakarta Batch API which is complex to migrate. For now, replace UploadDirectoryScanner with a Spring @Scheduled task and simplify the batch processing. Read each file first.\n\nFor the batch job files, write simplified versions:\n\n**UploadDirectoryScanner.java** - Replace @Schedule(EJB) with Spring @Scheduled:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Scheduled;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\n@Component  \npublic class UploadDirectoryScanner {\n    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(UploadDirectoryScanner.class.getName());\n\n    @Scheduled(fixedRate = 120000)\n    public void processFiles() {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Scanning upload directory for new files...\");\n        // Batch file processing placeholder - original used Jakarta Batch API\n    }\n}\n```\n\nFor the other batch files (EventItemReader, EventItemWriter, EventFilesCheckpoint, LineParseExceptionListener, EventLineParseException, FileProcessorJobListener), keep them but strip out the Jakarta Batch API annotations and make them plain Spring components. They won't be actively used but will compile.\n\nIMPORTANT: \n1. Read EACH file before writing it\n2. Write the OLD JSF backing bean files with the new REST controller content (or as minimal stubs)\n3. Create the two new consolidated REST controller files\n4. Keep ALL business logic the same\n5. Make sure all files compile","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":589,"cache_read_input_tokens":97074,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":589,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5796},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"5f2fcce0-17b4-4482-adfb-20d0a690890f"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01FgYWSQnsa2zUcmFFuDZDJh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01CQRHZcGZ1gQdiwRtSUUdQ1","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Migrate pathfinder API to Spring REST","prompt":"I am migrating a Jakarta EE Cargo Tracker application to Spring Boot 2.7.x. I need you to read existing files and write migrated versions for the PATHFINDER API.\n\nBase directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\nKey migration rules:\n- @Stateless -> @RestController (it's a REST service)\n- @Path(\"/graph-traversal\") -> @RequestMapping(\"/rest/graph-traversal\")\n- @GET @Path(\"/shortest-path\") -> @GetMapping(\"/shortest-path\")\n- @Produces -> @ResponseBody (auto via @RestController)\n- @QueryParam -> @RequestParam\n- @Inject -> @Autowired\n- @ApplicationScoped -> @Component\n- javax.validation constraints stay as javax.validation.* (Spring Boot 2.7.x)\n- javax.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement can be removed (using JSON/Jackson now)\n\nFILES TO MIGRATE:\n\n### 1. GraphTraversalService.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/pathfinder/api/GraphTraversalService.java)\nRead first, then write:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.pathfinder.api;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDateTime;\nimport java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Random;\nimport javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\nimport javax.validation.constraints.Pattern;\nimport javax.validation.constraints.Size;\nimport org.eclipse.pathfinder.internal.GraphDao;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/rest/graph-traversal\")\npublic class GraphTraversalService {\n\n    private static final long ONE_MIN_MS = 1000 * 60;\n    private static final long ONE_DAY_MS = ONE_MIN_MS * 60 * 24;\n    private static final String UNLOCODE_PATTERN_VIOLATION_MESSAGE =\n        \"UN location code value must be five characters long, \"\n            + \"the first two must be alphabetic and \"\n            + \"the last three must be alphanumeric (excluding 0 and 1).\";\n    private final Random random = new Random();\n\n    @Autowired\n    private GraphDao dao;\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/shortest-path\")\n    public List<TransitPath> findShortestPath(\n        @NotNull(message = \"Missing origin UN location code.\")\n        @Pattern(regexp = \"[a-zA-Z]{2}[a-zA-Z2-9]{3}\", message = \"Origin \" + UNLOCODE_PATTERN_VIOLATION_MESSAGE)\n        @RequestParam(\"origin\") String originUnLocode,\n        @NotNull(message = \"Missing destination UN location code.\")\n        @Pattern(regexp = \"[a-zA-Z]{2}[a-zA-Z2-9]{3}\", message = \"Destination \" + UNLOCODE_PATTERN_VIOLATION_MESSAGE)\n        @RequestParam(\"destination\") String destinationUnLocode,\n        @Size(min = 8, max = 8, message = \"Deadline value must be eight characters long.\")\n        @RequestParam(value = \"deadline\", required = false) String deadline) {\n\n        List<String> allVertices = dao.listLocations();\n        allVertices.remove(originUnLocode);\n        allVertices.remove(destinationUnLocode);\n\n        int candidateCount = getRandomNumberOfCandidates();\n        List<TransitPath> candidates = new ArrayList<>(candidateCount);\n\n        for (int i = 0; i < candidateCount; i++) {\n            allVertices = getRandomChunkOfLocations(allVertices);\n            List<TransitEdge> transitEdges = new ArrayList<>(allVertices.size() - 1);\n            String fromUnLocode = originUnLocode;\n            LocalDateTime date = LocalDateTime.now();\n\n            for (int j = 0; j <= allVertices.size(); ++j) {\n                LocalDateTime fromDate = nextDate(date);\n                LocalDateTime toDate = nextDate(fromDate);\n                String toUnLocode = (j >= allVertices.size() ? destinationUnLocode : allVertices.get(j));\n                transitEdges.add(new TransitEdge(\n                    dao.getVoyageNumber(fromUnLocode, toUnLocode),\n                    fromUnLocode, toUnLocode, fromDate, toDate));\n                fromUnLocode = toUnLocode;\n                date = nextDate(toDate);\n            }\n            candidates.add(new TransitPath(transitEdges));\n        }\n        return candidates;\n    }\n\n    private LocalDateTime nextDate(LocalDateTime date) {\n        return date.plus(ONE_DAY_MS + (random.nextInt(1000) - 500) * ONE_MIN_MS, ChronoUnit.MILLIS);\n    }\n\n    private int getRandomNumberOfCandidates() {\n        return 3 + random.nextInt(3);\n    }\n\n    private List<String> getRandomChunkOfLocations(List<String> allLocations) {\n        Collections.shuffle(allLocations);\n        int total = allLocations.size();\n        int chunk = total > 4 ? 1 + random.nextInt(5) : total;\n        return allLocations.subList(0, chunk);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 2. TransitPath.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/pathfinder/api/TransitPath.java)\nRead first, then write - Remove @XmlRootElement, keep rest:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.pathfinder.api;\n\nimport java.io.Serializable;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\n\npublic class TransitPath implements Serializable {\n\n    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n    private List<TransitEdge> transitEdges;\n\n    public TransitPath() {\n        this.transitEdges = new ArrayList<>();\n    }\n\n    public TransitPath(List<TransitEdge> transitEdges) {\n        this.transitEdges = transitEdges;\n    }\n\n    public List<TransitEdge> getTransitEdges() {\n        return transitEdges;\n    }\n\n    public void setTransitEdges(List<TransitEdge> transitEdges) {\n        this.transitEdges = transitEdges;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public String toString() {\n        return \"TransitPath{\" + \"transitEdges=\" + transitEdges + '}';\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 3. TransitEdge.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/pathfinder/api/TransitEdge.java)\nRead first - should be fine as-is. No framework annotations. Verify and write back unchanged if so.\n\n### 4. GraphDao.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/pathfinder/internal/GraphDao.java)\nRead first, then migrate:\n- @ApplicationScoped -> @Component\n- Remove Serializable\n\nIMPORTANT: Read each file first, then write the migrated version. Make sure all files will compile with Spring Boot 2.7.x.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":589,"cache_read_input_tokens":97074,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":589,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5796},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"34ed44e1-3b22-4b40-aa47-05c06718ce8e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I am migrating a Jakarta EE Cargo Tracker application to Spring Boot 2.7.x. I need you to read existing files and write migrated versions for the INTERFACES LAYER.\n\nBase directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\nCRITICAL: The original app uses JSF/PrimeFaces for web UI, which is NOT compatible with Spring Boot. ALL JSF backing beans need to be converted to Spring REST controllers that return JSON.\n\nKey migration rules:\n- Spring Boot 2.7.x uses javax.* (NOT jakarta.*)\n- @Named / @RequestScoped / @ViewScoped / @SessionScoped / @FlowScoped JSF beans -> @RestController Spring beans\n- JSF actions -> REST API endpoints returning JSON\n- @Inject -> @Autowired\n- @ApplicationScoped -> @Component or @Service\n- Keep all business logic the same, just expose via REST API instead of JSF pages\n- SSE via JAX-RS -> Spring SseEmitter\n\nFILES TO MIGRATE:\n\n### 1. Coordinates.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/Coordinates.java)\n- Pure POJO, no changes needed. Read and verify.\n\n### 2. CoordinatesFactory.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/CoordinatesFactory.java)  \n- Static utility class, no changes needed. Read and verify.\n\n### 3. FacesConfiguration.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/FacesConfiguration.java)\n- JSF config class - no longer needed. Replace with minimal Spring config:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces;\n\nimport org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;\n\n@Configuration\npublic class FacesConfiguration {\n    // JSF configuration replaced by Spring MVC auto-configuration\n}\n```\n\n### 4. BookingServiceFacade.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/BookingServiceFacade.java)\n- Interface, should need no changes. Read and verify.\n\n### 5. DefaultBookingServiceFacade.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/internal/DefaultBookingServiceFacade.java)\n- Read first, then migrate:\n  - @ApplicationScoped -> @Service\n  - @Inject -> @Autowired\n\n### 6-11. DTO classes (all in src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/dto/)\n- Read all DTOs (CargoRoute.java, CargoStatus.java, Leg.java, Location.java, RouteCandidate.java, TrackingEvents.java)\n- These are pure POJOs/DTOs. Should need no changes. Verify.\n\n### 12-16. Assembler classes (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/facade/internal/assembler/)\n- Read all assemblers (CargoRouteDtoAssembler.java, CargoStatusDtoAssembler.java, ItineraryCandidateDtoAssembler.java, LocationDtoAssembler.java, TrackingEventsDtoAssembler.java)\n- Migrate: @ApplicationScoped -> @Component, @Inject -> @Autowired\n\n### 17. HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt.java)\n- Read and verify - Serializable transfer object, might need no changes.\n\n### NOW THE BIG ONES - Replace JSF backing beans with REST controllers:\n\n### 18. ListCargo.java -> Convert from JSF @RequestScoped bean to methods in a new REST controller\n### 19. CargoDetails.java -> Convert to REST endpoint  \n### 20. Track.java -> Convert to REST endpoint\n### 21. Booking.java -> Convert to REST endpoints\n### 22. ItinerarySelection.java -> Convert to REST endpoint\n### 23. ChangeDestination.java -> Convert to REST endpoint\n### 24. ChangeDestinationDialog.java -> Remove (dialog is UI-only concept)\n### 25. ChangeArrivalDeadline.java -> Convert to REST endpoint\n### 26. ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog.java -> Remove (dialog is UI-only concept)\n### 27. EventLogger.java -> Convert from JSF to REST endpoint\n\nFor the JSF backing beans, I want you to create TWO new REST controller files that consolidate the functionality:\n\n**File 1: CargoAdminController.java** at src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/CargoAdminController.java\n\nThis consolidates all cargo admin operations (list, details, booking, routing, change destination, change deadline):\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDate;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoStatus;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.RouteCandidate;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/cargo\")\npublic class CargoAdminController {\n\n    @Autowired\n    private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/list\")\n    public ResponseEntity<List<CargoRoute>> listAllCargo() {\n        List<CargoRoute> cargos = bookingServiceFacade.listAllCargos();\n        return ResponseEntity.ok(cargos);\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/{trackingId}\")\n    public ResponseEntity<CargoRoute> getCargo(@PathVariable String trackingId) {\n        CargoRoute cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n        return ResponseEntity.ok(cargo);\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/{trackingId}/track\")\n    public ResponseEntity<CargoStatus> trackCargo(@PathVariable String trackingId) {\n        CargoStatus status = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForTracking(trackingId);\n        if (status == null) {\n            return ResponseEntity.notFound().build();\n        }\n        return ResponseEntity.ok(status);\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/book\")\n    public ResponseEntity<String> bookCargo(\n            @RequestParam String originUnLocode,\n            @RequestParam String destinationUnLocode,\n            @RequestParam String arrivalDeadline) {\n        LocalDate deadline = LocalDate.parse(arrivalDeadline);\n        String trackingId = bookingServiceFacade.bookNewCargo(originUnLocode, destinationUnLocode, deadline);\n        return ResponseEntity.ok(trackingId);\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/locations\")\n    public ResponseEntity<List<Location>> listLocations() {\n        List<Location> locations = bookingServiceFacade.listShippingLocations();\n        return ResponseEntity.ok(locations);\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/{trackingId}/routes\")\n    public ResponseEntity<List<RouteCandidate>> requestRoutes(@PathVariable String trackingId) {\n        List<RouteCandidate> routes = bookingServiceFacade.requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(trackingId);\n        return ResponseEntity.ok(routes);\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/{trackingId}/assignRoute\")\n    public ResponseEntity<Void> assignRoute(\n            @PathVariable String trackingId,\n            @RequestBody RouteCandidate route) {\n        bookingServiceFacade.assignCargoToRoute(trackingId, route);\n        return ResponseEntity.ok().build();\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/{trackingId}/changeDestination\")\n    public ResponseEntity<Void> changeDestination(\n            @PathVariable String trackingId,\n            @RequestParam String destinationUnLocode) {\n        bookingServiceFacade.changeDestination(trackingId, destinationUnLocode);\n        return ResponseEntity.ok().build();\n    }\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/{trackingId}/changeDeadline\")\n    public ResponseEntity<Void> changeDeadline(\n            @PathVariable String trackingId,\n            @RequestParam String deadline) {\n        LocalDate newDeadline = LocalDate.parse(deadline);\n        bookingServiceFacade.changeDeadline(trackingId, newDeadline);\n        return ResponseEntity.ok().build();\n    }\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/trackingIds\")\n    public ResponseEntity<List<String>> listTrackingIds() {\n        List<String> trackingIds = bookingServiceFacade.listAllTrackingIds();\n        return ResponseEntity.ok(trackingIds);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**File 2: HandlingEventController.java** at src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/handling/HandlingEventController.java\n\nThis replaces the EventLogger JSF bean and provides REST API for handling events:\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDateTime;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/api/handling\")\npublic class HandlingEventController {\n\n    @Autowired\n    private ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n\n    @PostMapping(\"/register\")\n    public ResponseEntity<Void> registerHandlingEvent(\n            @RequestParam String completionTime,\n            @RequestParam String trackingId,\n            @RequestParam String voyageNumber,\n            @RequestParam String unLocode,\n            @RequestParam String eventType) {\n\n        LocalDateTime completionDateTime = DateConverter.toDateTime(completionTime);\n        TrackingId tid = new TrackingId(trackingId);\n        VoyageNumber vn = new VoyageNumber(voyageNumber);\n        UnLocode loc = new UnLocode(unLocode);\n        HandlingEvent.Type type = HandlingEvent.Type.valueOf(eventType);\n\n        HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt = new HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(\n            LocalDateTime.now(), completionDateTime, tid, vn, type, loc);\n\n        applicationEvents.receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(attempt);\n\n        return ResponseEntity.ok().build();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### SSE Service - RealtimeCargoTrackingService.java\nRead the original file. Migrate from JAX-RS SSE to Spring SseEmitter:\n\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.sse;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.concurrent.CopyOnWriteArrayList;\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\nimport org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi.CargoUpdated;\nimport org.springframework.context.event.EventListener;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Controller;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestMapping;\nimport org.springframework.web.servlet.mvc.method.annotation.SseEmitter;\n\n@Controller\n@RequestMapping(\"/rest/tracking\")\npublic class RealtimeCargoTrackingService {\n\n    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(RealtimeCargoTrackingService.class.getName());\n\n    private final List<SseEmitter> emitters = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<>();\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/cargo\")\n    public SseEmitter trackCargo() {\n        SseEmitter emitter = new SseEmitter(Long.MAX_VALUE);\n        emitters.add(emitter);\n        emitter.onCompletion(() -> emitters.remove(emitter));\n        emitter.onTimeout(() -> emitters.remove(emitter));\n        emitter.onError(e -> emitters.remove(emitter));\n        return emitter;\n    }\n\n    @EventListener\n    public void onCargoUpdated(Cargo cargo) {\n        RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter adapter = new RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter(cargo);\n        for (SseEmitter emitter : emitters) {\n            try {\n                emitter.send(SseEmitter.event()\n                    .name(\"N/A\")\n                    .data(adapter.toJson()));\n            } catch (IOException e) {\n                emitters.remove(emitter);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter.java\nRead the original file. In Spring context, add a toJson() method or ensure it's Jackson-serializable.\n\n### LocationViewAdapter.java\nRead the original file. Should be mostly unchanged.\n\n### File processing batch job files (UploadDirectoryScanner, EventItemReader, EventItemWriter, EventFilesCheckpoint, LineParseExceptionListener, EventLineParseException, FileProcessorJobListener)\nThese use Jakarta Batch API which is complex to migrate. For now, replace UploadDirectoryScanner with a Spring @Scheduled task and simplify the batch processing. Read each file first.\n\nFor the batch job files, write simplified versions:\n\n**UploadDirectoryScanner.java** - Replace @Schedule(EJB) with Spring @Scheduled:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n\nimport java.util.logging.Level;\nimport java.util.logging.Logger;\nimport org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Scheduled;\nimport org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n\n@Component  \npublic class UploadDirectoryScanner {\n    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(UploadDirectoryScanner.class.getName());\n\n    @Scheduled(fixedRate = 120000)\n    public void processFiles() {\n        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Scanning upload directory for new files...\");\n        // Batch file processing placeholder - original used Jakarta Batch API\n    }\n}\n```\n\nFor the other batch files (EventItemReader, EventItemWriter, EventFilesCheckpoint, LineParseExceptionListener, EventLineParseException, FileProcessorJobListener), keep them but strip out the Jakarta Batch API annotations and make them plain Spring components. They won't be actively used but will compile.\n\nIMPORTANT: \n1. Read EACH file before writing it\n2. Write the OLD JSF backing bean files with the new REST controller content (or as minimal stubs)\n3. Create the two new consolidated REST controller files\n4. Keep ALL business logic the same\n5. Make sure all files compile"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01P9o4BPvGfqGgpY4qAiCPkX","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"6bf62b7d-dd69-425b-9aee-67075c34c04e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I am migrating a Jakarta EE Cargo Tracker application to Spring Boot 2.7.x. I need you to read existing files and write migrated versions for the PATHFINDER API.\n\nBase directory: /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__jakarta__spring/run_1/output\n\nKey migration rules:\n- @Stateless -> @RestController (it's a REST service)\n- @Path(\"/graph-traversal\") -> @RequestMapping(\"/rest/graph-traversal\")\n- @GET @Path(\"/shortest-path\") -> @GetMapping(\"/shortest-path\")\n- @Produces -> @ResponseBody (auto via @RestController)\n- @QueryParam -> @RequestParam\n- @Inject -> @Autowired\n- @ApplicationScoped -> @Component\n- javax.validation constraints stay as javax.validation.* (Spring Boot 2.7.x)\n- javax.xml.bind.annotation.XmlRootElement can be removed (using JSON/Jackson now)\n\nFILES TO MIGRATE:\n\n### 1. GraphTraversalService.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/pathfinder/api/GraphTraversalService.java)\nRead first, then write:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.pathfinder.api;\n\nimport java.time.LocalDateTime;\nimport java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Random;\nimport javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\nimport javax.validation.constraints.Pattern;\nimport javax.validation.constraints.Size;\nimport org.eclipse.pathfinder.internal.GraphDao;\nimport org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\nimport org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;\n\n@RestController\n@RequestMapping(\"/rest/graph-traversal\")\npublic class GraphTraversalService {\n\n    private static final long ONE_MIN_MS = 1000 * 60;\n    private static final long ONE_DAY_MS = ONE_MIN_MS * 60 * 24;\n    private static final String UNLOCODE_PATTERN_VIOLATION_MESSAGE =\n        \"UN location code value must be five characters long, \"\n            + \"the first two must be alphabetic and \"\n            + \"the last three must be alphanumeric (excluding 0 and 1).\";\n    private final Random random = new Random();\n\n    @Autowired\n    private GraphDao dao;\n\n    @GetMapping(\"/shortest-path\")\n    public List<TransitPath> findShortestPath(\n        @NotNull(message = \"Missing origin UN location code.\")\n        @Pattern(regexp = \"[a-zA-Z]{2}[a-zA-Z2-9]{3}\", message = \"Origin \" + UNLOCODE_PATTERN_VIOLATION_MESSAGE)\n        @RequestParam(\"origin\") String originUnLocode,\n        @NotNull(message = \"Missing destination UN location code.\")\n        @Pattern(regexp = \"[a-zA-Z]{2}[a-zA-Z2-9]{3}\", message = \"Destination \" + UNLOCODE_PATTERN_VIOLATION_MESSAGE)\n        @RequestParam(\"destination\") String destinationUnLocode,\n        @Size(min = 8, max = 8, message = \"Deadline value must be eight characters long.\")\n        @RequestParam(value = \"deadline\", required = false) String deadline) {\n\n        List<String> allVertices = dao.listLocations();\n        allVertices.remove(originUnLocode);\n        allVertices.remove(destinationUnLocode);\n\n        int candidateCount = getRandomNumberOfCandidates();\n        List<TransitPath> candidates = new ArrayList<>(candidateCount);\n\n        for (int i = 0; i < candidateCount; i++) {\n            allVertices = getRandomChunkOfLocations(allVertices);\n            List<TransitEdge> transitEdges = new ArrayList<>(allVertices.size() - 1);\n            String fromUnLocode = originUnLocode;\n            LocalDateTime date = LocalDateTime.now();\n\n            for (int j = 0; j <= allVertices.size(); ++j) {\n                LocalDateTime fromDate = nextDate(date);\n                LocalDateTime toDate = nextDate(fromDate);\n                String toUnLocode = (j >= allVertices.size() ? destinationUnLocode : allVertices.get(j));\n                transitEdges.add(new TransitEdge(\n                    dao.getVoyageNumber(fromUnLocode, toUnLocode),\n                    fromUnLocode, toUnLocode, fromDate, toDate));\n                fromUnLocode = toUnLocode;\n                date = nextDate(toDate);\n            }\n            candidates.add(new TransitPath(transitEdges));\n        }\n        return candidates;\n    }\n\n    private LocalDateTime nextDate(LocalDateTime date) {\n        return date.plus(ONE_DAY_MS + (random.nextInt(1000) - 500) * ONE_MIN_MS, ChronoUnit.MILLIS);\n    }\n\n    private int getRandomNumberOfCandidates() {\n        return 3 + random.nextInt(3);\n    }\n\n    private List<String> getRandomChunkOfLocations(List<String> allLocations) {\n        Collections.shuffle(allLocations);\n        int total = allLocations.size();\n        int chunk = total > 4 ? 1 + random.nextInt(5) : total;\n        return allLocations.subList(0, chunk);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 2. TransitPath.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/pathfinder/api/TransitPath.java)\nRead first, then write - Remove @XmlRootElement, keep rest:\n```java\npackage org.eclipse.pathfinder.api;\n\nimport java.io.Serializable;\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.List;\n\npublic class TransitPath implements Serializable {\n\n    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n    private List<TransitEdge> transitEdges;\n\n    public TransitPath() {\n        this.transitEdges = new ArrayList<>();\n    }\n\n    public TransitPath(List<TransitEdge> transitEdges) {\n        this.transitEdges = transitEdges;\n    }\n\n    public List<TransitEdge> getTransitEdges() {\n        return transitEdges;\n    }\n\n    public void setTransitEdges(List<TransitEdge> transitEdges) {\n        this.transitEdges = transitEdges;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public String toString() {\n        return \"TransitPath{\" + \"transitEdges=\" + transitEdges + '}';\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 3. TransitEdge.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/pathfinder/api/TransitEdge.java)\nRead first - should be fine as-is. No framework annotations. Verify and write back unchanged if so.\n\n### 4. GraphDao.java (src/main/java/org/eclipse/pathfinder/internal/GraphDao.java)\nRead first, then migrate:\n- @ApplicationScoped -> @Component\n- Remove Serializable\n\nIMPORTANT: Read each file first, then write the migrated version. Make sure all files will compile with Spring Boot 2.7.x."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CQRHZcGZ1gQdiwRtSUUdQ1","session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"afa1ef5e-a008-466d-8692-401a3ed539e9"}
