{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Rqb22THvKXMR6nrwDPUfuB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.internal;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.CargoInspectionService;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventRepository;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingHistory;\n    12→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    13→import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;\n    14→import org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n    15→\n    16→@Service\n    17→@Transactional\n    18→public class DefaultCargoInspectionService implements CargoInspectionService {\n    19→\n    20→  @Autowired private Logger logger;\n    21→  @Autowired private ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n    22→  @Autowired private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    23→  @Autowired private HandlingEventRepository handlingEventRepository;\n    24→\n    25→  @Override\n    26→  public void inspectCargo(TrackingId trackingId) {\n    27→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    28→\n    29→    if (cargo == null) {\n    30→      logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"Can't inspect non-existing cargo {0}\", trackingId);\n    31→      return;\n    32→    }\n    33→\n    34→    HandlingHistory handlingHistory =\n    35→        handlingEventRepository.lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(trackingId);\n    36→\n    37→    cargo.deriveDeliveryProgress(handlingHistory);\n    38→\n    39→    if (cargo.getDelivery().isMisdirected()) {\n    40→      applicationEvents.cargoWasMisdirected(cargo);\n    41→    }\n    42→\n    43→    if (cargo.getDelivery().isUnloadedAtDestination()) {\n    44→      applicationEvents.cargoHasArrived(cargo);\n    45→    }\n    46→\n    47→    cargoRepository.store(cargo);\n    48→  }\n    49→}\n    50→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"8480543d-f626-44f8-9b4d-c8ce1ce29979"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013HP6rtQUb8eRYtnmUwBpVx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.internal;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.HandlingEventService;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.CannotCreateHandlingEventException;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventFactory;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventRepository;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    14→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    15→import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;\n    16→import org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n    17→\n    18→@Service\n    19→@Transactional\n    20→public class DefaultHandlingEventService implements HandlingEventService {\n    21→\n    22→  @Autowired private ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n    23→  @Autowired private HandlingEventRepository handlingEventRepository;\n    24→  @Autowired private HandlingEventFactory handlingEventFactory;\n    25→  @Autowired private Logger logger;\n    26→\n    27→  @Override\n    28→  public void registerHandlingEvent(\n    29→      LocalDateTime completionTime,\n    30→      TrackingId trackingId,\n    31→      VoyageNumber voyageNumber,\n    32→      UnLocode unLocode,\n    33→      HandlingEvent.Type type)\n    34→      throws CannotCreateHandlingEventException {\n    35→    LocalDateTime registrationTime = LocalDateTime.now();\n    36→\n    37→    /*\n    38→     * Using a factory to create a HandlingEvent (aggregate). This is where it is\n    39→     * determined wether the incoming data, the attempt, actually is capable of\n    40→     * representing a real handling event.\n    41→     */\n    42→    HandlingEvent event =\n    43→        handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n    44→            registrationTime, completionTime, trackingId, voyageNumber, unLocode, type);\n    45→\n    46→    /*\n    47→     * Store the new handling event, which updates the persistent state of the\n    48→     * handling event aggregate (but not the cargo aggregate - that happens\n    49→     * asynchronously!)\n    50→     */\n    51→    handlingEventRepository.store(event);\n    52→\n    53→    /* Publish an event stating that a cargo has been handled. */\n    54→    applicationEvents.cargoWasHandled(event);\n    55→\n    56→    logger.info(\"Registered handling event\");\n    57→  }\n    58→}\n    59→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"556c2fd8-c416-444c-b82f-7c929c09add4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JCpt7Sh1cPU5sG7oiSD5oP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.util.Arrays;\n     6→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     7→import javax.persistence.EntityManager;\n     8→import javax.persistence.LockModeType;\n     9→import javax.persistence.NoResultException;\n    10→import javax.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Itinerary;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Leg;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.RouteSpecification;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.CannotCreateHandlingEventException;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventFactory;\n    19→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventRepository;\n    20→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingHistory;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations;\n    22→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.SampleVoyages;\n    23→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    24→import org.springframework.boot.CommandLineRunner;\n    25→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    26→import org.springframework.transaction.annotation.Transactional;\n    27→\n    28→/** Loads sample data for demo. */\n    29→@Component\n    30→public class SampleDataGenerator implements CommandLineRunner {\n    31→\n    32→  @Autowired private Logger logger;\n    33→\n    34→  @PersistenceContext private EntityManager entityManager;\n    35→  @Autowired private HandlingEventFactory handlingEventFactory;\n    36→  @Autowired private HandlingEventRepository handlingEventRepository;\n    37→\n    38→  @Override\n    39→  @Transactional\n    40→  public void run(String... args) {\n    41→    loadSampleData();\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  private void loadSampleData() {\n    45→    if (!isSampleLoaded()) {\n    46→      logger.info(\"Loading sample data.\");\n    47→      loadSampleLocations();\n    48→      loadSampleVoyages();\n    49→      loadSampleCargos();\n    50→    } else {\n    51→      logger.info(\"Sample data already loaded, skipping.\");\n    52→    }\n    53→  }\n    54→\n    55→  private boolean isSampleLoaded() {\n    56→    boolean sampleLoaded = false;\n    57→\n    58→    try {\n    59→      ApplicationSettings settings =\n    60→          entityManager.find(ApplicationSettings.class, 1L, LockModeType.PESSIMISTIC_WRITE);\n    61→      sampleLoaded = settings.isSampleLoaded();\n    62→      settings.setSampleLoaded(true);\n    63→    } catch (NoResultException e) {\n    64→      throw new RuntimeException(\"Could not retrieve application settings.\", e);\n    65→    }\n    66→\n    67→    return sampleLoaded;\n    68→  }\n    69→\n    70→  private void loadSampleLocations() {\n    71→    logger.info(\"Loading sample locations.\");\n    72→\n    73→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.HONGKONG);\n    74→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.MELBOURNE);\n    75→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM);\n    76→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.HELSINKI);\n    77→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.CHICAGO);\n    78→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.TOKYO);\n    79→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.HAMBURG);\n    80→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.SHANGHAI);\n    81→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.ROTTERDAM);\n    82→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.GOTHENBURG);\n    83→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.HANGZOU);\n    84→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.NEWYORK);\n    85→    entityManager.persist(SampleLocations.DALLAS);\n    86→  }\n    87→\n    88→  private void loadSampleVoyages() {\n    89→    logger.info(\"Loading sample voyages.\");\n    90→\n    91→    entityManager.persist(SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK);\n    92→    entityManager.persist(SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS);\n    93→    entityManager.persist(SampleVoyages.DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI);\n    94→    entityManager.persist(SampleVoyages.HELSINKI_TO_HONGKONG);\n    95→    entityManager.persist(SampleVoyages.DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI_ALT);\n    96→  }\n    97→\n    98→  private void loadSampleCargos() {\n    99→    logger.info(\"Loading sample cargo data.\");\n   100→\n   101→    // Cargo ABC123. This one is en-route.\n   102→    TrackingId trackingId1 = new TrackingId(\"ABC123\");\n   103→\n   104→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification1 =\n   105→        new RouteSpecification(\n   106→            SampleLocations.HONGKONG, SampleLocations.HELSINKI, LocalDate.now().plusDays(15));\n   107→    Cargo abc123 = new Cargo(trackingId1, routeSpecification1);\n   108→\n   109→    Itinerary itinerary1 =\n   110→        new Itinerary(\n   111→            Arrays.asList(\n   112→                new Leg(\n   113→                    SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK,\n   114→                    SampleLocations.HONGKONG,\n   115→                    SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n   116→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(7).minusHours(2).minusMinutes(4),\n   117→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(1).minusHours(10).minusMinutes(52)),\n   118→                new Leg(\n   119→                    SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS,\n   120→                    SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n   121→                    SampleLocations.DALLAS,\n   122→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(2).minusHours(18).minusMinutes(38),\n   123→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(6).minusHours(3).minusMinutes(22)),\n   124→                new Leg(\n   125→                    SampleVoyages.DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI,\n   126→                    SampleLocations.DALLAS,\n   127→                    SampleLocations.HELSINKI,\n   128→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(8).minusHours(8).minusMinutes(18),\n   129→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(14).minusHours(12).minusMinutes(29))));\n   130→    abc123.assignToRoute(itinerary1);\n   131→\n   132→    entityManager.persist(abc123);\n   133→\n   134→    try {\n   135→      HandlingEvent event1 =\n   136→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   137→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(5).minusMinutes(5),\n   138→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(10).minusHours(9).minusMinutes(11),\n   139→              trackingId1,\n   140→              null,\n   141→              SampleLocations.HONGKONG.getUnLocode(),\n   142→              HandlingEvent.Type.RECEIVE);\n   143→      entityManager.persist(event1);\n   144→\n   145→      HandlingEvent event2 =\n   146→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   147→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(6).minusMinutes(46),\n   148→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(7).minusHours(2).minusMinutes(50),\n   149→              trackingId1,\n   150→              SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK.getVoyageNumber(),\n   151→              SampleLocations.HONGKONG.getUnLocode(),\n   152→              HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD);\n   153→      entityManager.persist(event2);\n   154→\n   155→      HandlingEvent event3 =\n   156→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   157→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(15).minusMinutes(26),\n   158→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(1).minusHours(4).minusMinutes(32),\n   159→              trackingId1,\n   160→              SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK.getVoyageNumber(),\n   161→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK.getUnLocode(),\n   162→              HandlingEvent.Type.UNLOAD);\n   163→      entityManager.persist(event3);\n   164→    } catch (CannotCreateHandlingEventException e) {\n   165→      throw new RuntimeException(e);\n   166→    }\n   167→\n   168→    HandlingHistory handlingHistory1 =\n   169→        handlingEventRepository.lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(trackingId1);\n   170→    abc123.deriveDeliveryProgress(handlingHistory1);\n   171→\n   172→    entityManager.persist(abc123);\n   173→\n   174→    // Cargo JKL567. This one was loaded on the wrong voyage.\n   175→    TrackingId trackingId2 = new TrackingId(\"JKL567\");\n   176→\n   177→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification2 =\n   178→        new RouteSpecification(\n   179→            SampleLocations.HANGZOU, SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM, LocalDate.now().plusDays(18));\n   180→    Cargo jkl567 = new Cargo(trackingId2, routeSpecification2);\n   181→\n   182→    Itinerary itinerary2 =\n   183→        new Itinerary(\n   184→            Arrays.asList(\n   185→                new Leg(\n   186→                    SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK,\n   187→                    SampleLocations.HANGZOU,\n   188→                    SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n   189→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(10).minusHours(1).minusMinutes(19),\n   190→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(3).minusHours(7).minusMinutes(2)),\n   191→                new Leg(\n   192→                    SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS,\n   193→                    SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n   194→                    SampleLocations.DALLAS,\n   195→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(2).minusHours(17).minusMinutes(3),\n   196→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(2).minusHours(5).minusMinutes(20)),\n   197→                new Leg(\n   198→                    SampleVoyages.DALLAS_TO_HELSINKI,\n   199→                    SampleLocations.DALLAS,\n   200→                    SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM,\n   201→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(6).minusHours(11).minusMinutes(38),\n   202→                    LocalDateTime.now().plusDays(15).minusHours(4).minusMinutes(1))));\n   203→    jkl567.assignToRoute(itinerary2);\n   204→\n   205→    entityManager.persist(jkl567);\n   206→\n   207→    try {\n   208→      HandlingEvent event1 =\n   209→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   210→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(2).minusMinutes(44),\n   211→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(15).minusHours(14).minusMinutes(33),\n   212→              trackingId2,\n   213→              null,\n   214→              SampleLocations.HANGZOU.getUnLocode(),\n   215→              HandlingEvent.Type.RECEIVE);\n   216→      entityManager.persist(event1);\n   217→\n   218→      HandlingEvent event2 =\n   219→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   220→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(3).minusMinutes(12),\n   221→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(10).minusHours(3).minusMinutes(17),\n   222→              trackingId2,\n   223→              SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK.getVoyageNumber(),\n   224→              SampleLocations.HANGZOU.getUnLocode(),\n   225→              HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD);\n   226→      entityManager.persist(event2);\n   227→\n   228→      HandlingEvent event3 =\n   229→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   230→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(3).minusMinutes(21),\n   231→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(3).minusHours(22).minusMinutes(1),\n   232→              trackingId2,\n   233→              SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK.getVoyageNumber(),\n   234→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK.getUnLocode(),\n   235→              HandlingEvent.Type.UNLOAD);\n   236→      entityManager.persist(event3);\n   237→\n   238→      // The wrong voyage!\n   239→      HandlingEvent event4 =\n   240→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   241→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(18).minusMinutes(36),\n   242→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(2).minusHours(8).minusMinutes(7),\n   243→              trackingId2,\n   244→              SampleVoyages.HONGKONG_TO_NEW_YORK.getVoyageNumber(),\n   245→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK.getUnLocode(),\n   246→              HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD);\n   247→      entityManager.persist(event4);\n   248→    } catch (CannotCreateHandlingEventException e) {\n   249→      throw new RuntimeException(e);\n   250→    }\n   251→\n   252→    HandlingHistory handlingHistory2 =\n   253→        handlingEventRepository.lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(trackingId2);\n   254→    jkl567.deriveDeliveryProgress(handlingHistory2);\n   255→\n   256→    entityManager.persist(jkl567);\n   257→\n   258→    // Cargo definition DEF789. This one will remain un-routed.\n   259→    TrackingId trackingId3 = new TrackingId(\"DEF789\");\n   260→\n   261→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification3 =\n   262→        new RouteSpecification(\n   263→            SampleLocations.HONGKONG, SampleLocations.MELBOURNE, LocalDate.now().plusMonths(2));\n   264→\n   265→    Cargo def789 = new Cargo(trackingId3, routeSpecification3);\n   266→    entityManager.persist(def789);\n   267→\n   268→    // Cargo definition MNO456. This one will be claimed properly.\n   269→    TrackingId trackingId4 = new TrackingId(\"MNO456\");\n   270→    RouteSpecification routeSpecification4 =\n   271→        new RouteSpecification(\n   272→            SampleLocations.NEWYORK, SampleLocations.DALLAS, LocalDate.now().minusDays(24));\n   273→\n   274→    Cargo mno456 = new Cargo(trackingId4, routeSpecification4);\n   275→\n   276→    Itinerary itinerary4 =\n   277→        new Itinerary(\n   278→            Arrays.asList(\n   279→                new Leg(\n   280→                    SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS,\n   281→                    SampleLocations.NEWYORK,\n   282→                    SampleLocations.DALLAS,\n   283→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(34).minusHours(1).minusMinutes(1),\n   284→                    LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(28).minusHours(10).minusMinutes(1))));\n   285→\n   286→    mno456.assignToRoute(itinerary4);\n   287→    entityManager.persist(mno456);\n   288→\n   289→    try {\n   290→      HandlingEvent event1 =\n   291→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   292→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(16).minusMinutes(9),\n   293→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(37).minusHours(2).minusMinutes(21),\n   294→              trackingId4,\n   295→              null,\n   296→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK.getUnLocode(),\n   297→              HandlingEvent.Type.RECEIVE);\n   298→\n   299→      entityManager.persist(event1);\n   300→\n   301→      HandlingEvent event2 =\n   302→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   303→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(3).minusMinutes(9),\n   304→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(34).minusHours(3).minusMinutes(8),\n   305→              trackingId4,\n   306→              SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS.getVoyageNumber(),\n   307→              SampleLocations.NEWYORK.getUnLocode(),\n   308→              HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD);\n   309→\n   310→      entityManager.persist(event2);\n   311→\n   312→      HandlingEvent event3 =\n   313→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   314→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(14).minusMinutes(10),\n   315→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(28).minusHours(7).minusMinutes(7),\n   316→              trackingId4,\n   317→              SampleVoyages.NEW_YORK_TO_DALLAS.getVoyageNumber(),\n   318→              SampleLocations.DALLAS.getUnLocode(),\n   319→              HandlingEvent.Type.UNLOAD);\n   320→\n   321→      entityManager.persist(event3);\n   322→\n   323→      HandlingEvent event4 =\n   324→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   325→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(22).minusMinutes(1),\n   326→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(27).minusHours(18).minusMinutes(3),\n   327→              trackingId4,\n   328→              null,\n   329→              SampleLocations.DALLAS.getUnLocode(),\n   330→              HandlingEvent.Type.CUSTOMS);\n   331→\n   332→      entityManager.persist(event4);\n   333→\n   334→      HandlingEvent event5 =\n   335→          handlingEventFactory.createHandlingEvent(\n   336→              LocalDateTime.now().minusHours(9).minusMinutes(30),\n   337→              LocalDateTime.now().minusDays(26).minusHours(14).minusMinutes(15),\n   338→              trackingId4,\n   339→              null,\n   340→              SampleLocations.DALLAS.getUnLocode(),\n   341→              HandlingEvent.Type.CLAIM);\n   342→\n   343→      entityManager.persist(event5);\n   344→\n   345→      HandlingHistory handlingHistory3 =\n   346→          handlingEventRepository.lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(trackingId4);\n   347→\n   348→      mno456.deriveDeliveryProgress(handlingHistory3);\n   349→\n   350→      entityManager.persist(mno456);\n   351→    } catch (CannotCreateHandlingEventException e) {\n   352→      throw new RuntimeException(e);\n   353→    }\n   354→  }\n   355→}\n   356→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"3592e837-bc3d-4076-ab90-bf05adf04c80"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BfrGAKh64EdFvWNx1zu7US","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoStatus;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.RouteCandidate;\n    10→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    11→import org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity;\n    12→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;\n    13→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.PathVariable;\n    14→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.PostMapping;\n    15→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestBody;\n    16→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestMapping;\n    17→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestParam;\n    18→import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestController;\n    19→\n    20→/**\n    21→ * REST API controller for cargo administration operations.\n    22→ * Replaces JSF backing beans (ListCargo, CargoDetails, Track, Booking, ItinerarySelection,\n    23→ * ChangeDestination, ChangeArrivalDeadline) with REST API endpoints.\n    24→ */\n    25→@RestController\n    26→@RequestMapping(\"/api/cargo\")\n    27→public class CargoAdminController {\n    28→\n    29→    @Autowired\n    30→    private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    31→\n    32→    @GetMapping(\"/list\")\n    33→    public ResponseEntity<List<CargoRoute>> listAllCargo() {\n    34→        List<CargoRoute> cargos = bookingServiceFacade.listAllCargos();\n    35→        return ResponseEntity.ok(cargos);\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    @GetMapping(\"/{trackingId}\")\n    39→    public ResponseEntity<CargoRoute> getCargo(@PathVariable String trackingId) {\n    40→        CargoRoute cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    41→        return ResponseEntity.ok(cargo);\n    42→    }\n    43→\n    44→    @GetMapping(\"/{trackingId}/track\")\n    45→    public ResponseEntity<CargoStatus> trackCargo(@PathVariable String trackingId) {\n    46→        CargoStatus status = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForTracking(trackingId);\n    47→        if (status == null) {\n    48→            return ResponseEntity.notFound().build();\n    49→        }\n    50→        return ResponseEntity.ok(status);\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    @PostMapping(\"/book\")\n    54→    public ResponseEntity<String> bookCargo(\n    55→            @RequestParam String originUnLocode,\n    56→            @RequestParam String destinationUnLocode,\n    57→            @RequestParam String arrivalDeadline) {\n    58→        LocalDate deadline = LocalDate.parse(arrivalDeadline);\n    59→        String trackingId = bookingServiceFacade.bookNewCargo(originUnLocode, destinationUnLocode, deadline);\n    60→        return ResponseEntity.ok(trackingId);\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    @GetMapping(\"/locations\")\n    64→    public ResponseEntity<List<Location>> listLocations() {\n    65→        List<Location> locations = bookingServiceFacade.listShippingLocations();\n    66→        return ResponseEntity.ok(locations);\n    67→    }\n    68→\n    69→    @GetMapping(\"/{trackingId}/routes\")\n    70→    public ResponseEntity<List<RouteCandidate>> requestRoutes(@PathVariable String trackingId) {\n    71→        List<RouteCandidate> routes = bookingServiceFacade.requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(trackingId);\n    72→        return ResponseEntity.ok(routes);\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    @PostMapping(\"/{trackingId}/assignRoute\")\n    76→    public ResponseEntity<Void> assignRoute(\n    77→            @PathVariable String trackingId,\n    78→            @RequestBody RouteCandidate route) {\n    79→        bookingServiceFacade.assignCargoToRoute(trackingId, route);\n    80→        return ResponseEntity.ok().build();\n    81→    }\n    82→\n    83→    @PostMapping(\"/{trackingId}/changeDestination\")\n    84→    public ResponseEntity<Void> changeDestination(\n    85→            @PathVariable String trackingId,\n    86→            @RequestParam String destinationUnLocode) {\n    87→        bookingServiceFacade.changeDestination(trackingId, destinationUnLocode);\n    88→        return ResponseEntity.ok().build();\n    89→    }\n    90→\n    91→    @PostMapping(\"/{trackingId}/changeDeadline\")\n    92→    public ResponseEntity<Void> changeDeadline(\n    93→            @PathVariable String trackingId,\n    94→            @RequestParam String deadline) {\n    95→        LocalDate newDeadline = LocalDate.parse(deadline);\n    96→        bookingServiceFacade.changeDeadline(trackingId, newDeadline);\n    97→        return ResponseEntity.ok().build();\n    98→    }\n    99→\n   100→    @GetMapping(\"/trackingIds\")\n   101→    public ResponseEntity<List<String>> listTrackingIds() {\n   102→        List<String> trackingIds = bookingServiceFacade.listAllTrackingIds();\n   103→        return ResponseEntity.ok(trackingIds);\n   104→    }\n   105→}\n   106→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cb64f649-59c6-4f3a-a73b-f24ff02d923c","uuid":"81bac514-6f57-477b-9f74-58545a5ccfd3"}
